{"type":"message","id":"dfa15d41","parentId":"462d4122","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:11.994Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-10 14:20:11 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a [msg:om_x100b52bd2765493cc2c95e245ebc57d]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52bd2765493cc2c95e245ebc57d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-10 14:20 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\"\n}\n```\n\n你先帮我学习一下 Harness 工程，包括它的 CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理这些内容。学完之后，按照不同岗位给我创建智能体 Agent，比如开发经理 Agent、产品经理 Agent、测试 Agent、运维 Agent。"}],"timestamp":1775802011992}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a895d4a","parentId":"dfa15d41","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:27.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to:\n1. Learn about Harness engineering - specifically CI/CD, pipelines, deployment, environment management\n2. After learning, create different agent personas for different roles: Dev Manager Agent, Product Manager Agent, Test Agent, Ops Agent\n\nThis is a significant task. Let me first search for information about Harness engineering related to CI/CD, pipelines, deployment, and environment management.\n\nNote: \"Harness\" here could refer to two things:\n1. Harness Engineering (the AI agent framework we've been studying)\n2. Harness.io (a CI/CD and continuous delivery platform)\n\nGiven the context - \"CI/CD, 流水线, 部署, 环境管理\" - the user is likely asking about Harness.io, the CI/CD platform. Let me search for this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，先搞清楚你说的是哪个 Harness —— \"CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理\" 听起来像是在说 **Harness.io**（CD平台），跟我之前学的 Harness Engineering（AI Agent 驾驭工程）不是同一个东西。\n\n两个都帮你查清楚，然后你说清楚到底要哪个：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2nz39ry8t9dm_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Harness.io CI/CD platform continuous delivery pipelines deployment 2026"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2nz39ry8t9dm_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Harness 工程 AI Agent 驾驭工程 CI/CD 流水线 部署 环境管理 区别"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":44317,"output":292,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44609,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775802011998,"responseId":"chatcmpl-dc5aa8da-009a-4ebf-9979-ecba04217ffe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f3fbd7a","parentId":"7a895d4a","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:29.463Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2nz39ry8t9dm_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Harness.io CI/CD platform continuous delivery pipelines deployment 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"miaoda\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness: AI for DevOps, Testing, AppSec, and Cost Optimization\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.harness.io/\",\n      \"description\": \"unleash developer productivity with ai that understands your devops ecosystem . harness combines the industry 's fastest , most secure ci/cd with developer self-service to automate pipelines , infrastructure , and the entire path from code to production . ...\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Getting Started with Deployments\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/\",\n      \"description\": \"From your Harness project, select Pipelines from the left navigation menu.\\nClick + Create a Pipeline.\\n2. Configure Pipeline Basics\\nProvide a Name for your pipeline (e.g., \\\"Deploy to Production\\\")\\nChoose Inline for Pipeline Storage (stores configuration in Harness)\\nClick Start\\ninfo\\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using Remote storage. Learn more in the Pipelines documentation.\\nStep 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://toolradar.com/tools/harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness Unclaimed\\nModern software delivery platform\\nTesting & QA\\nCI/CD\\nInfrastructure as Code\\n4.6\\nTL;...\\nHarness is a comprehensive DevOps platform providing continuous delivery, CI/CD pipelines, GitOps, infrastructure as code management, and security testing orchestration in one platform.\\nHow does Harness pricing work?\\nHarness offers a free tier for small teams. Essentials bundles modules together for growing organizations. Enterprise offers modular pick-and-choose pricing. \",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Deep Dive: Accelerating DevOps with AI\",\n      \"url\": \"https://lng-consultancy.com/harness-deep-dive-accelerating-devops-with-ai/\",\n      \"description\": \"Continuous Integration (CI): The CI module is where your code gets built and tested. What makes Harness CI special? Speed, mainly. They claim builds that are up to 8x faster than other CI solutions. They achieve this through:\\nThis means you spend less time maintaining build servers and more time shipping code.\\nContinuous Delivery and GitOps (CD): The CD module automates the entire deployment process across any environment: cloud, on-premise, or hybrid. Here’s...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"4. Deployment Pipeline Modeling Overview\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/cd-pipeline-modeling-overview/\",\n      \"description\": \"apply machine learning to every deployment to identify and flag anomalies in future deployments . summary this topic provided a high - level overview of how you can model your software delivery process in harness continuous delivery pipelines ...\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析:架构设计、核心功能与实战指南_harness开源项目-CSDN博客\",\n      \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\\n1. 持续集成（CI）\\n智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\\n智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\\n并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\\n容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\\n2. 持续交付（CD）\\n多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\\n自动化...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Platform - Intelligent Software Delivery for AWS Marketplace\",\n      \"url\": \"https://aws.amazon.com/marketplace/pp/prodview-wrmqdjrxjdrf2\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness automates every stage of the SDLC, from code integration and testing to deployment and verification, using AI for advanced deployment strategies, automated rollbacks, and real-time analytics.\\nWith Harness, teams benefit from:\\nFaster Builds: Run only tests affected by code changes, thus accelerating build time by up to 4x.\\nRapid, Reliable Deployments: Build and execute complex deployment pipelines in minutes, supporting blue/green, canary, and rolling updates...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"How to Create a Harness Pipeline and integrate with Azure\",\n      \"url\": \"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/azureinfrastructureblog/how-to-create-a-harness-pipeline-and-integrate-with-azure/4499862\",\n      \"description\": \"You can choose:\\nRun Step → execute shell or PowerShell commands\\nBuild & Push → build container images\\nPlugin Step → use pre-built plugins\\nTest Step → run automated testsStep 7: Save and Run the Pipeline\\nExecute your pipeline using the Harness Delegate and infrastructure you configured.\\nClick Save\\nClick RunHarness will now:\\nSpin up a pod or VM (based on your infrastructure selection)\\nPull the container image you selected\\nExecute your CI steps one by...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://simplify.jobs/c/Harness\",\n      \"description\": \"It also offers a Cloud Cost Management tool that detects and stops cost anomalies in real time to optimize cloud spending. The self-managed Enterprise edition can be installed on a customer’s Kubernetes cluster. What sets Harness apart is its combination of intelligent automation across the software delivery lifecycle with real-time cloud cost control, plus an enterprise-grade, flexible deployment model. Its goal is to help organizations deliver software faster and more reliably while keeping cloud costs under control.\\nAutonomous CI/CD: Harness AI &...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"GitHub - harness/harness: Harness Open Source is an end-to-end developer platform with Source Control Management, CI/CD Pipelines, Hosted Developer Environments, and Artifact Registries. · GitHub\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/harness/harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness Open Source is an open source development platform packed with the power of code hosting, automated DevOps pipelines, hosted development environments (Gitspaces), and artifact registries.\\nOverview\\nHarness Open source is an open source development platform packed with the power of code hosting, automated Dev...\\nWhere Drone focused solely on continuous integration, Harness adds source code hosting, developer environments (gitspaces), and artifact registries; providing teams with an end-to-end, open source DevOps platform.\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Harness.io CI/CD platform continuous delivery pipelines deployment 2026","provider":"miaoda","count":10,"results":[{"title":"Harness: AI for DevOps, Testing, AppSec, and Cost Optimization","url":"https://www.harness.io/","description":"unleash developer productivity with ai that understands your devops ecosystem . harness combines the industry 's fastest , most secure ci/cd with developer self-service to automate pipelines , infrastructure , and the entire path from code to production . ...","siteName":""},{"title":"Getting Started with Deployments","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/","description":"From your Harness project, select Pipelines from the left navigation menu.\nClick + Create a Pipeline.\n2. Configure Pipeline Basics\nProvide a Name for your pipeline (e.g., \"Deploy to Production\")\nChoose Inline for Pipeline Storage (stores configuration in Harness)\nClick Start\ninfo\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using Remote storage. Learn more in the Pipelines documentation.\nStep 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness","url":"https://toolradar.com/tools/harness","description":"Harness Unclaimed\nModern software delivery platform\nTesting & QA\nCI/CD\nInfrastructure as Code\n4.6\nTL;...\nHarness is a comprehensive DevOps platform providing continuous delivery, CI/CD pipelines, GitOps, infrastructure as code management, and security testing orchestration in one platform.\nHow does Harness pricing work?\nHarness offers a free tier for small teams. Essentials bundles modules together for growing organizations. Enterprise offers modular pick-and-choose pricing. ","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Deep Dive: Accelerating DevOps with AI","url":"https://lng-consultancy.com/harness-deep-dive-accelerating-devops-with-ai/","description":"Continuous Integration (CI): The CI module is where your code gets built and tested. What makes Harness CI special? Speed, mainly. They claim builds that are up to 8x faster than other CI solutions. They achieve this through:\nThis means you spend less time maintaining build servers and more time shipping code.\nContinuous Delivery and GitOps (CD): The CD module automates the entire deployment process across any environment: cloud, on-premise, or hybrid. Here’s...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"4. Deployment Pipeline Modeling Overview","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/cd-pipeline-modeling-overview/","description":"apply machine learning to every deployment to identify and flag anomalies in future deployments . summary this topic provided a high - level overview of how you can model your software delivery process in harness continuous delivery pipelines ...","siteName":""},{"title":"【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析:架构设计、核心功能与实战指南_harness开源项目-CSDN博客","url":"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586","description":"Harness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\n1. 持续集成（CI）\n智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\n智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\n并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\n容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\n2. 持续交付（CD）\n多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\n自动化...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Platform - Intelligent Software Delivery for AWS Marketplace","url":"https://aws.amazon.com/marketplace/pp/prodview-wrmqdjrxjdrf2","description":"Harness automates every stage of the SDLC, from code integration and testing to deployment and verification, using AI for advanced deployment strategies, automated rollbacks, and real-time analytics.\nWith Harness, teams benefit from:\nFaster Builds: Run only tests affected by code changes, thus accelerating build time by up to 4x.\nRapid, Reliable Deployments: Build and execute complex deployment pipelines in minutes, supporting blue/green, canary, and rolling updates...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"How to Create a Harness Pipeline and integrate with Azure","url":"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/azureinfrastructureblog/how-to-create-a-harness-pipeline-and-integrate-with-azure/4499862","description":"You can choose:\nRun Step → execute shell or PowerShell commands\nBuild & Push → build container images\nPlugin Step → use pre-built plugins\nTest Step → run automated testsStep 7: Save and Run the Pipeline\nExecute your pipeline using the Harness Delegate and infrastructure you configured.\nClick Save\nClick RunHarness will now:\nSpin up a pod or VM (based on your infrastructure selection)\nPull the container image you selected\nExecute your CI steps one by...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness","url":"https://simplify.jobs/c/Harness","description":"It also offers a Cloud Cost Management tool that detects and stops cost anomalies in real time to optimize cloud spending. The self-managed Enterprise edition can be installed on a customer’s Kubernetes cluster. What sets Harness apart is its combination of intelligent automation across the software delivery lifecycle with real-time cloud cost control, plus an enterprise-grade, flexible deployment model. Its goal is to help organizations deliver software faster and more reliably while keeping cloud costs under control.\nAutonomous CI/CD: Harness AI &...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"GitHub - harness/harness: Harness Open Source is an end-to-end developer platform with Source Control Management, CI/CD Pipelines, Hosted Developer Environments, and Artifact Registries. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/harness/harness","description":"Harness Open Source is an open source development platform packed with the power of code hosting, automated DevOps pipelines, hosted development environments (Gitspaces), and artifact registries.\nOverview\nHarness Open source is an open source development platform packed with the power of code hosting, automated Dev...\nWhere Drone focused solely on continuous integration, Harness adds source code hosting, developer environments (gitspaces), and artifact registries; providing teams with an end-to-end, open source DevOps platform.\n","siteName":""}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802029461}}
{"type":"message","id":"9251eb1a","parentId":"6f3fbd7a","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:29.464Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2nz39ry8t9dm_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Harness 工程 AI Agent 驾驭工程 CI/CD 流水线 部署 环境管理 区别\",\n  \"provider\": \"miaoda\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"AI大模型领域，什么是Harness Engineering(驾驭工程/缰绳工程) - 鱼皮AI导航\",\n      \"url\": \"https://ai.codefather.cn/post/2039343973285261313\",\n      \"description\": \"<tr><th>概念</th><th>核心定位</th><th>核心目标</th><th>与Harness Engineering的关系</th></tr><tr><td>Harness Engineering</td><td>Agent的全链路运行操作系统与管控体系</td><td>驾驭模型，解决不确定性，实现生产级可靠落地</td><td>顶层系统架构，包含以下所有模块的标准化管控</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>Prompt Engineering</...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"1_Harness驾驭工程基础:AI原生持续交付平台架构全景_harness engineering-CSDN博客\",\n      \"url\": \"https://wayle.blog.csdn.net/article/details/159517830\",\n      \"description\": \"你用CI的时候，AI在选测试；你用CD的时候，AI在验证部署；你管成本的时候，AI在分析浪费。\\n第二，全生命周期覆盖。 大多数CI/CD工具只管\\\"构建→部署\\\"这段，而Harness从代码提交前（安全扫描）管到部署后（持续验证、混沌工程），再到运维阶段（云成本管理）。\\n第三，数据打通。 通过\\\"软件交付知识图谱\\\"，所有模块...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Engineering(驾驭工程)技术文档:从入门到全栈实践-CSDN博客\",\n      \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/zhanggongzichu/article/details/159757481\",\n      \"description\": \"<table>\\n<tr><th>维度</th><th>传统开发</th><th>提示词工程</th><th>Harness Engineering</th></tr><tr><td>核心对象</td><td>人类写代码</td><td>优化单次提示</td><td>构建 AI 运行环境与管控系统</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>人类角色</td><td>代码...\\n运维：Docker、CI/CD、监控、安全\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Engineering 综述 – Tingde Liu – Personal Blog & Research Notes\",\n      \"url\": \"https://tingdeliu.github.io/Harness-Engineering-Survey/\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness Engineering（Agent工程化） 是指围绕 AI 模型/Agent 构建基础设施、约束体系和反馈循环，使 Agent 能够在生产规模下可靠地完成代码编写、测试和部署等软件工程任务的工程学科。\\n与 上下文工程（Context Engineering） 关注”给 Agent 喂什么信息”不同，Harness Engineering 是更上位的概念，涵盖环境、约束、反馈和生命周期管理的全貌。\\n③ 熵管理\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Engineering:重塑Al Agent时代的软件工程Harness Engineering:重塑A - 掘金\",\n      \"url\": \"https://juejin.cn/post/7617728986828177435\",\n      \"description\": \"5.1 Prompt / Context / Harness Engineering 三角关系\\n这三种范式不是替代关系，而是嵌套包含的关系：\\n🏗️ Harness Engineering（最外层）\\n管理：环境、约束、验证、生命周期\\n🧠 Context Engineering（中间层）\\n管理：信息注入、RAG、记忆、上下文优化\\n✏️ Prompt Engineering（核心层）\\n管理：单次调用的指令质量\\n<table>\\n<tr><th>对比维度</th...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"驾驭工程(Harness Engineering)实践落地案例剖析-AI.x-AIGC专属社区-51CTO.COM\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.51cto.com/aigc/11114.html\",\n      \"description\": \"行业共识：2025 年 6 月，Andrej Karpathy 明确表态\\\"上下文工程比提示工程重要得多\\\"\\n阶段 3：驾驭工程（Harness Engineering）\\n核心问题：整个环境应该如何运作？\\n实践特征：角色从 Builder 交还到用户手中。通过设计完整的运行环境：约束、反馈回路、自动验证、熵管理、生命周期治理等，让 AI 在受控边界内自主发挥\\n与 OpenClaw...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Engineering:AI Agent 时代，工程师的新核心能力Harness Engineering - 掘金\",\n      \"url\": \"https://aicoding.juejin.cn/post/7622124594794627081\",\n      \"description\": \"<tr><th>对比维度</th><th>传统软件工程</th><th>Prompt Engineering</th><th>Harness Engineering 驾驭工程</th></tr><tr><td>核心主体</td><td>人</td><td>人+LLM辅助</td><td>LLM为主，人为驾驭者</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>核心工作</td><td>人亲手写每一行代码，实现需求</td><td>...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"OpenClaw 之后，Harness Engineering 又是什么?-AI.x-AIGC专属社区-51CTO.COM\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.51cto.com/aigc/11037.html\",\n      \"description\": \"AI 的任务（马）：阅读业务代码，为其补充详尽的单元测试和集成测试。\\nHarness 系统（马具）：变异测试（Mutation Testing）框架。Harness 系统会像黑客一样，故意在源码里随机制造一些小 Bug（比如把加号改成减号）。如果 AI 写的测试用例居然“通过”了这些带有 Bug 的代码，Harness 就会判定 AI 的测试是无效的（在...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"一文读懂Harness Engineering_AI趣知研习社\",\n      \"url\": \"http://m.toutiao.com/group/7623600589453001256/\",\n      \"description\": \"四、与Prompt Engineering、Context Engineering的精准区别\\n维度\\nPrompt Engineering(提示词工程)\\nContext Engineering(上下文工程)\\nHarness Engineering(驾驭工程)\\n核心聚焦\\n优化AI的指令输入方式\\n优化AI的信息供给范围\\n构建AI的全生命周期运行系统\\n作用范围\\n单次交互，静态指令模板\\n单会话，动态信息注入\\n系统级，全生命周期、多Agent\\n解决问题\\nAI理解偏差、输出方向错误\\n信息...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness与OpenClaw:当企业级DevOps遇见个人AI助手_opendotnet\",\n      \"url\": \"http://m.toutiao.com/group/7626923662632895027/\",\n      \"description\": \"这种选择背后是对目标用户和核心价值的深刻理解。\\nHarness选择闭源SaaS模式，是因为它的核心价值在于「企业级可靠性」和「持续优化」。作为DevOps平台，Harness需要保证7x24小时的稳定运行，需要快速响应客户的安全需求，需要持续更新Knowledge Graph的数据模型。闭源模式使得Harness能够控制产品质量，确保每个客户获得一致的体验。\\n更重要的是...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Harness 工程 AI Agent 驾驭工程 CI/CD 流水线 部署 环境管理 区别","provider":"miaoda","count":10,"results":[{"title":"AI大模型领域，什么是Harness Engineering(驾驭工程/缰绳工程) - 鱼皮AI导航","url":"https://ai.codefather.cn/post/2039343973285261313","description":"<tr><th>概念</th><th>核心定位</th><th>核心目标</th><th>与Harness Engineering的关系</th></tr><tr><td>Harness Engineering</td><td>Agent的全链路运行操作系统与管控体系</td><td>驾驭模型，解决不确定性，实现生产级可靠落地</td><td>顶层系统架构，包含以下所有模块的标准化管控</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Prompt Engineering</...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"1_Harness驾驭工程基础:AI原生持续交付平台架构全景_harness engineering-CSDN博客","url":"https://wayle.blog.csdn.net/article/details/159517830","description":"你用CI的时候，AI在选测试；你用CD的时候，AI在验证部署；你管成本的时候，AI在分析浪费。\n第二，全生命周期覆盖。 大多数CI/CD工具只管\"构建→部署\"这段，而Harness从代码提交前（安全扫描）管到部署后（持续验证、混沌工程），再到运维阶段（云成本管理）。\n第三，数据打通。 通过\"软件交付知识图谱\"，所有模块...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Engineering(驾驭工程)技术文档:从入门到全栈实践-CSDN博客","url":"https://blog.csdn.net/zhanggongzichu/article/details/159757481","description":"<table>\n<tr><th>维度</th><th>传统开发</th><th>提示词工程</th><th>Harness Engineering</th></tr><tr><td>核心对象</td><td>人类写代码</td><td>优化单次提示</td><td>构建 AI 运行环境与管控系统</td></tr>\n<tr><td>人类角色</td><td>代码...\n运维：Docker、CI/CD、监控、安全\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Engineering 综述 – Tingde Liu – Personal Blog & Research Notes","url":"https://tingdeliu.github.io/Harness-Engineering-Survey/","description":"Harness Engineering（Agent工程化） 是指围绕 AI 模型/Agent 构建基础设施、约束体系和反馈循环，使 Agent 能够在生产规模下可靠地完成代码编写、测试和部署等软件工程任务的工程学科。\n与 上下文工程（Context Engineering） 关注”给 Agent 喂什么信息”不同，Harness Engineering 是更上位的概念，涵盖环境、约束、反馈和生命周期管理的全貌。\n③ 熵管理\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Engineering:重塑Al Agent时代的软件工程Harness Engineering:重塑A - 掘金","url":"https://juejin.cn/post/7617728986828177435","description":"5.1 Prompt / Context / Harness Engineering 三角关系\n这三种范式不是替代关系，而是嵌套包含的关系：\n🏗️ Harness Engineering（最外层）\n管理：环境、约束、验证、生命周期\n🧠 Context Engineering（中间层）\n管理：信息注入、RAG、记忆、上下文优化\n✏️ Prompt Engineering（核心层）\n管理：单次调用的指令质量\n<table>\n<tr><th>对比维度</th...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"驾驭工程(Harness Engineering)实践落地案例剖析-AI.x-AIGC专属社区-51CTO.COM","url":"https://www.51cto.com/aigc/11114.html","description":"行业共识：2025 年 6 月，Andrej Karpathy 明确表态\"上下文工程比提示工程重要得多\"\n阶段 3：驾驭工程（Harness Engineering）\n核心问题：整个环境应该如何运作？\n实践特征：角色从 Builder 交还到用户手中。通过设计完整的运行环境：约束、反馈回路、自动验证、熵管理、生命周期治理等，让 AI 在受控边界内自主发挥\n与 OpenClaw...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Engineering:AI Agent 时代，工程师的新核心能力Harness Engineering - 掘金","url":"https://aicoding.juejin.cn/post/7622124594794627081","description":"<tr><th>对比维度</th><th>传统软件工程</th><th>Prompt Engineering</th><th>Harness Engineering 驾驭工程</th></tr><tr><td>核心主体</td><td>人</td><td>人+LLM辅助</td><td>LLM为主，人为驾驭者</td></tr>\n<tr><td>核心工作</td><td>人亲手写每一行代码，实现需求</td><td>...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"OpenClaw 之后，Harness Engineering 又是什么?-AI.x-AIGC专属社区-51CTO.COM","url":"https://www.51cto.com/aigc/11037.html","description":"AI 的任务（马）：阅读业务代码，为其补充详尽的单元测试和集成测试。\nHarness 系统（马具）：变异测试（Mutation Testing）框架。Harness 系统会像黑客一样，故意在源码里随机制造一些小 Bug（比如把加号改成减号）。如果 AI 写的测试用例居然“通过”了这些带有 Bug 的代码，Harness 就会判定 AI 的测试是无效的（在...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"一文读懂Harness Engineering_AI趣知研习社","url":"http://m.toutiao.com/group/7623600589453001256/","description":"四、与Prompt Engineering、Context Engineering的精准区别\n维度\nPrompt Engineering(提示词工程)\nContext Engineering(上下文工程)\nHarness Engineering(驾驭工程)\n核心聚焦\n优化AI的指令输入方式\n优化AI的信息供给范围\n构建AI的全生命周期运行系统\n作用范围\n单次交互，静态指令模板\n单会话，动态信息注入\n系统级，全生命周期、多Agent\n解决问题\nAI理解偏差、输出方向错误\n信息...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness与OpenClaw:当企业级DevOps遇见个人AI助手_opendotnet","url":"http://m.toutiao.com/group/7626923662632895027/","description":"这种选择背后是对目标用户和核心价值的深刻理解。\nHarness选择闭源SaaS模式，是因为它的核心价值在于「企业级可靠性」和「持续优化」。作为DevOps平台，Harness需要保证7x24小时的稳定运行，需要快速响应客户的安全需求，需要持续更新Knowledge Graph的数据模型。闭源模式使得Harness能够控制产品质量，确保每个客户获得一致的体验。\n更重要的是...\n","siteName":""}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802029463}}
{"type":"message","id":"45c3a181","parentId":"9251eb1a","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:53.716Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. The user is asking about TWO different things:\n\n1. **Harness Engineering** (AI Agent 驾驭工程) - what we've been studying\n2. **Harness.io** - a CI/CD and DevOps platform\n\nThe user mentions \"CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理\" which maps to Harness.io (the CD platform). But they also say \"学习 Harness 工程\" which could be referring to Harness Engineering.\n\nWait, re-reading: \"你先帮我学习一下 Harness 工程，包括它的 CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理这些内容\"\n\nThis is confusing because:\n\n\n- Harness Engineering (AI) doesn't have CI/CD pipelines or deployment environments - that's Harness.io\n- But the user explicitly mentions CI/CD, pipelines, deployment, and environment management\n\nI think the user might be conflating the two, or they might actually want to learn about Harness.io (the DevOps platform) specifically. The most likely scenario is they're asking about Harness.io's CI/CD and deployment capabilities, but I should clarify whether they want to focus on the DevOps platform or the AI Agent framework.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"查完了，情况有点绕，先跟你捋清楚：\n\n---\n\n**两个不同的 Harness：**\n\n| | Harness Engineering（驾驭工程） | Harness.io（CD平台） |\n|---|---|---|\n| 做什么 | 给 AI Agent 构建运行管控系统 | CI/CD 流水线、持续部署 |\n| 四层框架 | 约束层→信息层→验证层→修正层 | Build→Test→Deploy→Verify |\n| 你的需求 | 已学完 | 你的需求指向这里 |\n\n---\n\n你说的「CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理」——这明确是 **Harness.io**（DevOps 平台）的东西，不是 Harness Engineering。\n\n**请确认你要学的是哪个：**\n\n**A. Harness.io**（DevOps 平台）—— 智能 CI/CD、GitOps 流水线、蓝绿/金丝雀部署、环境管理、云成本优化\n\n**B. Harness Engineering**（AI 驾驭工程）—— 我已经学过四层框架了，可以帮你创建不同岗位的 Agent\n\n**C. 两个都要**\n\n确认后我立刻开干。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":3863,"output":440,"cacheRead":43899,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775802029465,"responseId":"chatcmpl-dcb9f25e-b70a-4fd9-9298-e322d833cc45"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f394105","parentId":"45c3a181","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:20:55.512Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-10 14:20:55 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a [msg:om_x100b52bd255864b0c33bf795e17e4a6]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52bd255864b0c33bf795e17e4a6\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-04-10 14:20 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_0b09d73328aba9ee56b8bb871bf3fb3a\"\n}\n```\n\n每个 Agent 要说明它负责什么、怎么用 Harness 干活、能输出什么东西。"}],"timestamp":1775802055508}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c36b276","parentId":"4f394105","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:17.531Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that each Agent should explain what it responsible for, how it uses Harness to work, and what it can output. But they still haven't confirmed which Harness they want - Harness.io or Harness Engineering. \n\nActually, looking at the context again, the user's original request was to learn about \"Harness工程\" (Harness Engineering) and create agents. The mention of \"CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理\" was describing what they wanted to learn WITHIN Harness Engineering. But I've been confused thinking they meant Harness.io.\n\nWait, let me re-read. The user originally said \"学习什么事harness，并创建对应的智能体\" - this was about Harness Engineering. Then later they said \"基于学习到的harness 工程知识，创建对应的agent\" - still Harness Engineering.\n \nI think there was a misunderstanding in my previous response. The user wants to create specialized agents for different roles (开发经理, 产品经理, 测试, 运维) that each explain what they're responsible for, how they leverage Harness to work, and what outputs they produce. The focus is on building out these functional agents within the Harness Engineering framework, not on learning about a separate Harness.io platform.\n\nSince the user specifically referenced \"harness 工程知识\" they already learned, they're asking me to dive into how Harness.io actually works—the CI/CD pipelines, deployment strategies, environment management—so I can create more informed and practical agents based on that understanding.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，明白了。开始干活。\n\n先深入学一下 Harness.io 的核心模块，再创建四个岗位 Agent。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_1","name":"web_crawl","arguments":{"url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_2","name":"web_crawl","arguments":{"url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/cd-pipeline-modeling-overview/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_3","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Harness.io CI/CD modules CI/CD Pipelines Deployment environments GitOps delegate 2026"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":4226,"output":432,"cacheRead":43899,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775802055515,"responseId":"chatcmpl-3eda6474-1071-4a5f-955b-ed0985948ffa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3f1da7e","parentId":"3c36b276","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:17.934Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_1","toolName":"web_crawl","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/\",\n  \"content\": \"- \\n\\n- Getting Started\\n\\n# Getting Started with Deployments\\n\\nLast updated on **Jan 7, 2026** Download as PDF\\n\\ninfo\\n\\n.\\n\\nThis guide walks you through creating your first deployment pipeline in Harness Continuous Delivery (CD). You'll build a complete pipeline from scratch, step by step.\\n\\n### New to Harness CD?\\n\\nStart with the  to understand key concepts, including Services, Environments, Pipelines, and Deployment Strategies.\\n\\n**What you'll accomplish:**\\n\\n1. Create a deployment pipeline\\n\\n2. Configure a service (what to deploy)\\n\\n3. Set up an environment (where to deploy)\\n\\n4. Choose an execution strategy\\n\\n5. Run your first deployment\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\nBefore you begin, ensure you have:\\n\\n- **A Harness account**  - \\n\\n- **Access to a Harness project**  - Use the Default Project or create your own\\n\\n**Platform-Specific Prerequisites**\\n\\nSelect your deployment platform to see all requirements and set up connectors:\\n\\n- Kubernetes\\n\\n- SSH / Traditional\\n\\n- Google Cloud Run\\n\\n- Azure\\n\\n- AWS Lambda\\n\\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\\n\\n- A Kubernetes cluster (local like , or cloud-managed like GKE, EKS, AKS)\\n\\n- `kubectl` access to your cluster\\n\\n- Application deployed to a container registry (Docker Hub, ECR, GCR, etc.)\\n\\n- **A Harness Delegate installed**  - Required to connect to your cluster. Follow the \\n\\n**Quick Verification:**\\n\\n```\\n# Verify kubectl access\\n\\nkubectl cluster-info\\n\\nkubectl get nodes\\n```\\n**Required Connectors:**\\n\\n1. **Kubernetes Cluster Connector**  - Connects Harness to your cluster\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Kubernetes Cluster**\\n\\n    - Choose connection method (Delegate, Service Account, etc.)\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n2. **Git Connector**  - For storing Kubernetes manifests\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket**\\n\\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication (Personal Access Token recommended)\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n3. **Docker Registry Connector**  - For pulling container images\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Docker Registry**\\n\\n    - For Docker Hub: Use `https://registry.hub.docker.com/v2/`\\n\\n    - For ECR/GCR/ACR: Use respective registry URLs\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\\n\\n- Target VMs or servers (on-premises or cloud)\\n\\n- SSH key-based authentication configured\\n\\n- Application artifacts in a repository (Artifactory, Nexus, S3, etc.)\\n\\n- **A Harness Delegate installed**  - Required to execute deployment commands on your servers. Follow the \\n\\n**SSH Key Setup:**\\n\\n```\\n# Generate SSH key if neededssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/harness_deploy# Copy public key to target serversssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/harness_deploy.pub user@server-ip\\n```\\n**Required Connectors:**\\n\\n1. **SSH Key Secret**  - Store your private SSH key\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Secrets**  → **New Secret**  → **File**\\n\\n    - Upload your private SSH key file\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n2. **SSH Connector**  - Connects to your servers\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **SSH**\\n\\n    - Provide host details and select SSH key secret\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n3. **Artifact Repository Connector**  - For application packages\\n\\n    - **For Artifactory** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Artifactory**\\n\\n    - **For Nexus** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Nexus**\\n\\n    - **For S3** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **AWS**  → Configure S3 access\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\\n\\n- A GCP project with billing enabled\\n\\n- For Cloud Run: Cloud Run API enabled\\n\\n- For GKE: A GKE cluster\\n\\n- Container image in GCR or Artifact Registry\\n\\n**Enable Required APIs:**\\n\\n```\\n# Enable Cloud Run APIgcloud services enable run.googleapis.com# Enable Artifact Registrygcloud services enable artifactregistry.googleapis.com# Enable Container Registry (if using GCR)gcloud services enable containerregistry.googleapis.com\\n```\\n**Required Connectors:**\\n\\n1. **GCP Connector**  - Connects Harness to Google Cloud\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GCP**\\n\\n    - Choose authentication: Service Account Key or GCE VM\\n\\n    - Provide service account key (JSON) with required permissions\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Required GCP Permissions:**\\n\\n    - Cloud Run: `roles/run.admin`\\n\\n    - Artifact Registry: `roles/artifactregistry.reader`\\n\\n    - GKE: `roles/container.developer`\\n\\n2. **Git Connector**  (if using Git for manifests)\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\\n\\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n3. **GCR/Artifact Registry Connector**  - For container images\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GCR/GAR**\\n\\n    - Select your GCP connector\\n\\n    - Specify registry hostname\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\\n\\n- An Azure subscription with appropriate permissions\\n\\n- For Functions: Function App created in Azure Portal\\n\\n- For Web Apps: App Service plan configured\\n\\n- Application package or container image ready\\n\\n**Azure CLI Verification:**\\n\\n```\\n# Login to Azureaz login# Verify subscriptionaz account show# List resource groupsaz group list\\n```\\n**Required Connectors:**\\n\\n1. **Azure Connector**  - Connects Harness to Azure\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Azure**\\n\\n    - Choose authentication: Service Principal or Managed Identity\\n\\n    - Provide:\\n\\n        - Application (Client) ID\\n\\n        - Tenant ID\\n\\n        - Client Secret (create as Harness Secret first)\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Required Azure Permissions:**\\n\\n    - Contributor role on resource group\\n\\n    - Or specific: `Microsoft.Web/sites/*` for Web Apps/Functions\\n\\n2. **Git Connector**  (for configuration files)\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\\n\\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n3. **Azure Container Registry Connector**  (for containerized apps)\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Docker Registry**\\n\\n    - Use ACR login server URL (e.g., `myregistry.azurecr.io`)\\n\\n    - Authenticate using Azure credentials or ACR admin credentials\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\\n\\n- An AWS account with appropriate IAM permissions\\n\\n- Lambda execution role with required policies\\n\\n- S3 bucket for deployment packages (or ECR for container images)\\n\\n- Deployment package (ZIP file) uploaded to S3\\n\\n**AWS CLI Verification:**\\n\\n```\\n# Verify AWS credentialsaws sts get-caller-identity# List S3 bucketsaws s3 ls# Verify Lambda accessaws lambda list-functions --region us-east-1\\n```\\n**Required Connectors:**\\n\\n1. **AWS Connector**  - Connects Harness to AWS\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **AWS**\\n\\n    - Choose authentication method:\\n\\n        - **Access Key**  (recommended for getting started)\\n\\n        - **IAM Role**  (recommended for production)\\n\\n        - **IRSA**  (for EKS)\\n\\n    - For Access Key method:\\n\\n        - Create a secret for Access Key ID\\n\\n        - Create a secret for Secret Access Key\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n**Required IAM Policies:**\\n\\n    - `AWSLambda_FullAccess` or `AWSLambdaFullAccess`\\n\\n    - `IAMReadOnlyAccess` (for role verification)\\n\\n    - `AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess` (for artifact retrieval)\\n\\n2. **Git Connector**  - For Lambda function definitions\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\\n\\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\\n\\n    - Example repo: `https://github.com/harness-community/harnesscd-example-apps`\\n\\n    - Follow: \\n\\n3. **AWS Secrets**  - Store AWS credentials\\n\\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Secrets**  → **New Secret**  → **Text**\\n\\n    - Create two secrets:\\n\\n        - `aws_access_key_id`: Your AWS Access Key ID\\n\\n        - `aws_secret_access_key`: Your AWS Secret Access Key\\n\\n    - These will be used in the AWS connector\\n\\n**Pre-Deployment Setup:**\\n\\n- Upload your Lambda deployment package (ZIP) to S3 bucket\\n\\n- Note the bucket name and file path - you'll need these in Step 3\\n\\n- Ensure Lambda execution role ARN is ready - you'll need it in the function definition\\n\\n**Important Notes:**\\n\\n- Complete all connector setups before proceeding - You'll select these connectors in the following steps\\n\\n- Test each connector - Use the \\\"Test Connection\\\" button to verify connectivity\\n\\n- Save connector identifiers - You'll reference these by name when configuring services and environments\\n\\n## Step 1: Create Your Pipeline\\n\\nFollow these steps to create your first deployment pipeline.\\n\\n**1. Navigate to Pipelines**\\n\\n1. From your Harness project, select **Pipelines**  from the left navigation menu.\\n\\n2. Click **+ Create a Pipeline** .\\n\\n\\n\\n**2. Configure Pipeline Basics**\\n\\n1. Provide a **Name**  for your pipeline (e.g., \\\"Deploy to Production\\\")\\n\\n2. Choose **Inline**  for **Pipeline Storage**  (stores configuration in Harness)\\n\\n3. Click **Start**\\n\\n\\n\\ninfo\\n\\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using **Remote**  storage. Learn more in the .\\n\\n## Step 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\\n\\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure your deployment based on your target platform.\\n\\n1. Select the **Deploy**  stage type.\\n\\n\\n\\n1. In the \\\"About your Stage\\\" section:\\n\\n    - Enter a **Stage Name**  (e.g., \\\"Deploy to Dev\\\")\\n\\n    - Select your **Deployment Type**\\n\\n**Select Your Deployment Type**\\n\\nThis guide covers the most common deployment types. Select the one that matches your infrastructure:\\n\\n- **Kubernetes**  - Deploy to any Kubernetes cluster\\n\\n- **AWS Lambda**  - Serverless functions on AWS\\n\\n- **Google Cloud Run**  - Fully managed containers on GCP\\n\\n- **Azure Web Apps**  - PaaS web applications on Azure\\n\\n- **Azure Functions**  - Serverless compute on Azure\\n\\n- **SSH**  - Deploy to Linux/Windows servers\\n\\ntip\\n\\nHarness supports 20+ deployment types including ECS, Helm, SAM, Google Cloud Functions, Spot, Tanzu, and more. For a complete list, see .\\n\\n1. Click **Set Up Stage**  to continue.\\n\\nimportant\\n\\nThe deployment type you select here determines the configuration needed in Service, Environment, and Infrastructure sections. Make sure to follow the same deployment type throughout all configuration steps.\\n\\n## Step 3: Configure Your Service\\n\\nThe Service defines what you're deploying (application, artifacts, manifests). Select your deployment platform below:\\n\\n- Kubernetes\\n\\n- SSH / Traditional\\n\\n- Google Cloud Run\\n\\n- Azure\\n\\n- AWS Lambda\\n\\n**Kubernetes Service Configuration**\\n\\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\\n\\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `nginx-service`) and click **Save**\\n\\n**Add Kubernetes Manifest**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Manifest**  → Select **K8s Manifest**\\n\\n2. Configure:\\n\\n    - **Manifest Identifier** : `k8s-manifest`\\n\\n    - **Git Connector** : Select the Git connector you created in Prerequisites\\n\\n    - **Repository** : Use `https://github.com/harness-community/harnesscd-example-apps`\\n\\n    - **Branch** : `master`\\n\\n    - **File Path** : `guestbook/manifest.yaml`\\n\\n**Sample Manifest:**\\n\\n```\\napiVersion: apps/v1\\n\\nkind: Deployment\\n\\nmetadata:\\n\\n  name: guestbook-ui\\n\\nspec:\\n\\n  replicas: 3\\n\\n  selector:\\n\\n    matchLabels:\\n\\n      app: guestbook-ui\\n\\n  template:\\n\\n    metadata:\\n\\n      labels:\\n\\n        app: guestbook-ui\\n\\n    spec:\\n\\n      containers:\\n\\n      - name: guestbook-ui\\n\\n        image: <+artifact.image>\\n\\n        ports:\\n\\n        - containerPort: 80\\n\\n---\\n\\napiVersion: v1\\n\\nkind: Service\\n\\nmetadata:\\n\\n  name: guestbook-ui\\n\\nspec:\\n\\n  type: LoadBalancer\\n\\n  selector:\\n\\n    app: guestbook-ui\\n\\n  ports:\\n\\n    - protocol: TCP\\n\\n      port: 80\\n\\n      targetPort: 80\\n```\\n**Add Container Image**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**  → Select **Docker Registry**\\n\\n2. Configure:\\n\\n    - **Artifact Source Name** : `nginx`\\n\\n    - **Docker Registry Connector** : Select the Docker Registry connector you created in Prerequisites\\n\\n    - **Image Path** : `library/nginx`\\n\\n    - **Tag** : Select `stable` or use `<+input>` for runtime input\\n\\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\\n\\ninfo\\n\\nYou can also use  or  for Kubernetes deployments.\\n\\n**SSH Deployment Service Configuration**\\n\\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\\n\\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `tomcat-app`) and click **Save**\\n\\n**Add Application Package**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**\\n\\n2. Select artifact source based on what you configured in Prerequisites:\\n\\n    - **Artifactory** : For JARs, WARs, etc.\\n\\n    - **Nexus** : For Maven artifacts\\n\\n    - **Amazon S3** : For packages\\n\\n3. Configure:\\n\\n    - **Connector** : Select the artifact repository connector you created in Prerequisites\\n\\n    - **Artifact Path** : Path to your application package\\n\\n    - **Format** : JAR, WAR, TAR, ZIP, etc.\\n\\n**Example** : For a WAR file from Artifactory\\n\\n- Repository: `libs-release-local`\\n\\n- Artifact Path: `com/example/myapp/1.0/myapp-1.0.war`\\n\\n**Add Deployment Scripts (Optional)**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Config File**  to add installation/startup scripts\\n\\n2. Add pre-deployment and post-deployment scripts as needed\\n\\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\\n\\ninfo\\n\\nHarness also supports  for Windows servers.\\n\\n**Google Cloud Run Service Configuration**\\n\\nSample configuration files are available at the .\\n\\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\\n\\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `cloud-run-service`) and click **Save**\\n\\n**Add Cloud Run Service Definition**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Manifest**  → Select **Google Cloud Run Service Definition**\\n\\n2. Configure:\\n\\n    - **Manifest Source** : Git Repository\\n\\n    - **Git Connector** : Select the Git connector you created in Prerequisites\\n\\n**Sample Cloud Run Service Definition:**\\n\\n```\\napiVersion: serving.knative.dev/v1kind: Servicemetadata:  name: <+service.name>spec:  template:    spec:      containers:      - image: <+artifact.image>        ports:        - containerPort: 8080        env:        - name: ENV          value: \\\"production\\\"\\n```\\n**Add Container Image**\\n\\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**  → Select **Google Artifact Registry**  or **GCR**\\n\\n2. Configure:\\n\\n    - **GCP Connector** : Select the GCP connector you created in Prerequisites\\n\\n    - **Project** : Your GCP project ID\\n\\n    - **Image Path** : Path to your container image\\n\\n    - **Tag** : Select tag or use `<+input>`\\n\\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\\n\\nHarness also supports  and .\\n\\n**Azure Functions Service Configuration**\\n\\nSample configuration files are available at the .\\n\\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\\n\\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g.,\"\n}"}],"details":{"url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/","content":"- \n\n- Getting Started\n\n# Getting Started with Deployments\n\nLast updated on **Jan 7, 2026** Download as PDF\n\ninfo\n\n.\n\nThis guide walks you through creating your first deployment pipeline in Harness Continuous Delivery (CD). You'll build a complete pipeline from scratch, step by step.\n\n### New to Harness CD?\n\nStart with the  to understand key concepts, including Services, Environments, Pipelines, and Deployment Strategies.\n\n**What you'll accomplish:**\n\n1. Create a deployment pipeline\n\n2. Configure a service (what to deploy)\n\n3. Set up an environment (where to deploy)\n\n4. Choose an execution strategy\n\n5. Run your first deployment\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nBefore you begin, ensure you have:\n\n- **A Harness account**  - \n\n- **Access to a Harness project**  - Use the Default Project or create your own\n\n**Platform-Specific Prerequisites**\n\nSelect your deployment platform to see all requirements and set up connectors:\n\n- Kubernetes\n\n- SSH / Traditional\n\n- Google Cloud Run\n\n- Azure\n\n- AWS Lambda\n\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\n\n- A Kubernetes cluster (local like , or cloud-managed like GKE, EKS, AKS)\n\n- `kubectl` access to your cluster\n\n- Application deployed to a container registry (Docker Hub, ECR, GCR, etc.)\n\n- **A Harness Delegate installed**  - Required to connect to your cluster. Follow the \n\n**Quick Verification:**\n\n```\n# Verify kubectl access\n\nkubectl cluster-info\n\nkubectl get nodes\n```\n**Required Connectors:**\n\n1. **Kubernetes Cluster Connector**  - Connects Harness to your cluster\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Kubernetes Cluster**\n\n    - Choose connection method (Delegate, Service Account, etc.)\n\n    - Follow: \n\n2. **Git Connector**  - For storing Kubernetes manifests\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket**\n\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication (Personal Access Token recommended)\n\n    - Follow: \n\n3. **Docker Registry Connector**  - For pulling container images\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Docker Registry**\n\n    - For Docker Hub: Use `https://registry.hub.docker.com/v2/`\n\n    - For ECR/GCR/ACR: Use respective registry URLs\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\n\n- Target VMs or servers (on-premises or cloud)\n\n- SSH key-based authentication configured\n\n- Application artifacts in a repository (Artifactory, Nexus, S3, etc.)\n\n- **A Harness Delegate installed**  - Required to execute deployment commands on your servers. Follow the \n\n**SSH Key Setup:**\n\n```\n# Generate SSH key if neededssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/harness_deploy# Copy public key to target serversssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/harness_deploy.pub user@server-ip\n```\n**Required Connectors:**\n\n1. **SSH Key Secret**  - Store your private SSH key\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Secrets**  → **New Secret**  → **File**\n\n    - Upload your private SSH key file\n\n    - Follow: \n\n2. **SSH Connector**  - Connects to your servers\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **SSH**\n\n    - Provide host details and select SSH key secret\n\n    - Follow: \n\n3. **Artifact Repository Connector**  - For application packages\n\n    - **For Artifactory** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Artifactory**\n\n    - **For Nexus** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Nexus**\n\n    - **For S3** : Go to **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **AWS**  → Configure S3 access\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\n\n- A GCP project with billing enabled\n\n- For Cloud Run: Cloud Run API enabled\n\n- For GKE: A GKE cluster\n\n- Container image in GCR or Artifact Registry\n\n**Enable Required APIs:**\n\n```\n# Enable Cloud Run APIgcloud services enable run.googleapis.com# Enable Artifact Registrygcloud services enable artifactregistry.googleapis.com# Enable Container Registry (if using GCR)gcloud services enable containerregistry.googleapis.com\n```\n**Required Connectors:**\n\n1. **GCP Connector**  - Connects Harness to Google Cloud\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GCP**\n\n    - Choose authentication: Service Account Key or GCE VM\n\n    - Provide service account key (JSON) with required permissions\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Required GCP Permissions:**\n\n    - Cloud Run: `roles/run.admin`\n\n    - Artifact Registry: `roles/artifactregistry.reader`\n\n    - GKE: `roles/container.developer`\n\n2. **Git Connector**  (if using Git for manifests)\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\n\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\n\n    - Follow: \n\n3. **GCR/Artifact Registry Connector**  - For container images\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GCR/GAR**\n\n    - Select your GCP connector\n\n    - Specify registry hostname\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\n\n- An Azure subscription with appropriate permissions\n\n- For Functions: Function App created in Azure Portal\n\n- For Web Apps: App Service plan configured\n\n- Application package or container image ready\n\n**Azure CLI Verification:**\n\n```\n# Login to Azureaz login# Verify subscriptionaz account show# List resource groupsaz group list\n```\n**Required Connectors:**\n\n1. **Azure Connector**  - Connects Harness to Azure\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Azure**\n\n    - Choose authentication: Service Principal or Managed Identity\n\n    - Provide:\n\n        - Application (Client) ID\n\n        - Tenant ID\n\n        - Client Secret (create as Harness Secret first)\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Required Azure Permissions:**\n\n    - Contributor role on resource group\n\n    - Or specific: `Microsoft.Web/sites/*` for Web Apps/Functions\n\n2. **Git Connector**  (for configuration files)\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\n\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\n\n    - Follow: \n\n3. **Azure Container Registry Connector**  (for containerized apps)\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **Docker Registry**\n\n    - Use ACR login server URL (e.g., `myregistry.azurecr.io`)\n\n    - Authenticate using Azure credentials or ACR admin credentials\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Infrastructure Requirements:**\n\n- An AWS account with appropriate IAM permissions\n\n- Lambda execution role with required policies\n\n- S3 bucket for deployment packages (or ECR for container images)\n\n- Deployment package (ZIP file) uploaded to S3\n\n**AWS CLI Verification:**\n\n```\n# Verify AWS credentialsaws sts get-caller-identity# List S3 bucketsaws s3 ls# Verify Lambda accessaws lambda list-functions --region us-east-1\n```\n**Required Connectors:**\n\n1. **AWS Connector**  - Connects Harness to AWS\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **AWS**\n\n    - Choose authentication method:\n\n        - **Access Key**  (recommended for getting started)\n\n        - **IAM Role**  (recommended for production)\n\n        - **IRSA**  (for EKS)\n\n    - For Access Key method:\n\n        - Create a secret for Access Key ID\n\n        - Create a secret for Secret Access Key\n\n    - Follow: \n\n**Required IAM Policies:**\n\n    - `AWSLambda_FullAccess` or `AWSLambdaFullAccess`\n\n    - `IAMReadOnlyAccess` (for role verification)\n\n    - `AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess` (for artifact retrieval)\n\n2. **Git Connector**  - For Lambda function definitions\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Connectors**  → **New Connector**  → **GitHub/GitLab**\n\n    - Provide repository URL and authentication\n\n    - Example repo: `https://github.com/harness-community/harnesscd-example-apps`\n\n    - Follow: \n\n3. **AWS Secrets**  - Store AWS credentials\n\n    - Go to **Project Setup**  → **Secrets**  → **New Secret**  → **Text**\n\n    - Create two secrets:\n\n        - `aws_access_key_id`: Your AWS Access Key ID\n\n        - `aws_secret_access_key`: Your AWS Secret Access Key\n\n    - These will be used in the AWS connector\n\n**Pre-Deployment Setup:**\n\n- Upload your Lambda deployment package (ZIP) to S3 bucket\n\n- Note the bucket name and file path - you'll need these in Step 3\n\n- Ensure Lambda execution role ARN is ready - you'll need it in the function definition\n\n**Important Notes:**\n\n- Complete all connector setups before proceeding - You'll select these connectors in the following steps\n\n- Test each connector - Use the \"Test Connection\" button to verify connectivity\n\n- Save connector identifiers - You'll reference these by name when configuring services and environments\n\n## Step 1: Create Your Pipeline\n\nFollow these steps to create your first deployment pipeline.\n\n**1. Navigate to Pipelines**\n\n1. From your Harness project, select **Pipelines**  from the left navigation menu.\n\n2. Click **+ Create a Pipeline** .\n\n\n\n**2. Configure Pipeline Basics**\n\n1. Provide a **Name**  for your pipeline (e.g., \"Deploy to Production\")\n\n2. Choose **Inline**  for **Pipeline Storage**  (stores configuration in Harness)\n\n3. Click **Start**\n\n\n\ninfo\n\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using **Remote**  storage. Learn more in the .\n\n## Step 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\n\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure your deployment based on your target platform.\n\n1. Select the **Deploy**  stage type.\n\n\n\n1. In the \"About your Stage\" section:\n\n    - Enter a **Stage Name**  (e.g., \"Deploy to Dev\")\n\n    - Select your **Deployment Type**\n\n**Select Your Deployment Type**\n\nThis guide covers the most common deployment types. Select the one that matches your infrastructure:\n\n- **Kubernetes**  - Deploy to any Kubernetes cluster\n\n- **AWS Lambda**  - Serverless functions on AWS\n\n- **Google Cloud Run**  - Fully managed containers on GCP\n\n- **Azure Web Apps**  - PaaS web applications on Azure\n\n- **Azure Functions**  - Serverless compute on Azure\n\n- **SSH**  - Deploy to Linux/Windows servers\n\ntip\n\nHarness supports 20+ deployment types including ECS, Helm, SAM, Google Cloud Functions, Spot, Tanzu, and more. For a complete list, see .\n\n1. Click **Set Up Stage**  to continue.\n\nimportant\n\nThe deployment type you select here determines the configuration needed in Service, Environment, and Infrastructure sections. Make sure to follow the same deployment type throughout all configuration steps.\n\n## Step 3: Configure Your Service\n\nThe Service defines what you're deploying (application, artifacts, manifests). Select your deployment platform below:\n\n- Kubernetes\n\n- SSH / Traditional\n\n- Google Cloud Run\n\n- Azure\n\n- AWS Lambda\n\n**Kubernetes Service Configuration**\n\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\n\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `nginx-service`) and click **Save**\n\n**Add Kubernetes Manifest**\n\n1. Click **Add Manifest**  → Select **K8s Manifest**\n\n2. Configure:\n\n    - **Manifest Identifier** : `k8s-manifest`\n\n    - **Git Connector** : Select the Git connector you created in Prerequisites\n\n    - **Repository** : Use `https://github.com/harness-community/harnesscd-example-apps`\n\n    - **Branch** : `master`\n\n    - **File Path** : `guestbook/manifest.yaml`\n\n**Sample Manifest:**\n\n```\napiVersion: apps/v1\n\nkind: Deployment\n\nmetadata:\n\n  name: guestbook-ui\n\nspec:\n\n  replicas: 3\n\n  selector:\n\n    matchLabels:\n\n      app: guestbook-ui\n\n  template:\n\n    metadata:\n\n      labels:\n\n        app: guestbook-ui\n\n    spec:\n\n      containers:\n\n      - name: guestbook-ui\n\n        image: <+artifact.image>\n\n        ports:\n\n        - containerPort: 80\n\n---\n\napiVersion: v1\n\nkind: Service\n\nmetadata:\n\n  name: guestbook-ui\n\nspec:\n\n  type: LoadBalancer\n\n  selector:\n\n    app: guestbook-ui\n\n  ports:\n\n    - protocol: TCP\n\n      port: 80\n\n      targetPort: 80\n```\n**Add Container Image**\n\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**  → Select **Docker Registry**\n\n2. Configure:\n\n    - **Artifact Source Name** : `nginx`\n\n    - **Docker Registry Connector** : Select the Docker Registry connector you created in Prerequisites\n\n    - **Image Path** : `library/nginx`\n\n    - **Tag** : Select `stable` or use `<+input>` for runtime input\n\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\n\ninfo\n\nYou can also use  or  for Kubernetes deployments.\n\n**SSH Deployment Service Configuration**\n\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\n\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `tomcat-app`) and click **Save**\n\n**Add Application Package**\n\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**\n\n2. Select artifact source based on what you configured in Prerequisites:\n\n    - **Artifactory** : For JARs, WARs, etc.\n\n    - **Nexus** : For Maven artifacts\n\n    - **Amazon S3** : For packages\n\n3. Configure:\n\n    - **Connector** : Select the artifact repository connector you created in Prerequisites\n\n    - **Artifact Path** : Path to your application package\n\n    - **Format** : JAR, WAR, TAR, ZIP, etc.\n\n**Example** : For a WAR file from Artifactory\n\n- Repository: `libs-release-local`\n\n- Artifact Path: `com/example/myapp/1.0/myapp-1.0.war`\n\n**Add Deployment Scripts (Optional)**\n\n1. Click **Add Config File**  to add installation/startup scripts\n\n2. Add pre-deployment and post-deployment scripts as needed\n\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\n\ninfo\n\nHarness also supports  for Windows servers.\n\n**Google Cloud Run Service Configuration**\n\nSample configuration files are available at the .\n\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\n\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g., `cloud-run-service`) and click **Save**\n\n**Add Cloud Run Service Definition**\n\n1. Click **Add Manifest**  → Select **Google Cloud Run Service Definition**\n\n2. Configure:\n\n    - **Manifest Source** : Git Repository\n\n    - **Git Connector** : Select the Git connector you created in Prerequisites\n\n**Sample Cloud Run Service Definition:**\n\n```\napiVersion: serving.knative.dev/v1kind: Servicemetadata:  name: <+service.name>spec:  template:    spec:      containers:      - image: <+artifact.image>        ports:        - containerPort: 8080        env:        - name: ENV          value: \"production\"\n```\n**Add Container Image**\n\n1. Click **Add Primary Artifact**  → Select **Google Artifact Registry**  or **GCR**\n\n2. Configure:\n\n    - **GCP Connector** : Select the GCP connector you created in Prerequisites\n\n    - **Project** : Your GCP project ID\n\n    - **Image Path** : Path to your container image\n\n    - **Tag** : Select tag or use `<+input>`\n\n3. Click **Continue**  to proceed to Environment configuration.\n\nHarness also supports  and .\n\n**Azure Functions Service Configuration**\n\nSample configuration files are available at the .\n\n1. In the **Service**  tab, click **+ Add Service**\n\n2. Provide a **Name**  (e.g.,"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802077932}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b9fd938","parentId":"c3f1da7e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:17.989Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_2","toolName":"web_crawl","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/cd-pipeline-modeling-overview/\",\n  \"content\": \"- \\n\\n    - New to Continuous Delivery?\\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - Use Continuous Delivery\\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - Use GitOps\\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n    - Troubleshooting & Resources\\n\\n    - \\n\\n        - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n            - \\n\\n    - \\n\\n- \\n\\n- \\n\\n- \\n\\n- CD pipeline modeling overview\\n\\n# CD pipeline modeling overview\\n\\nLast updated on **Jan 12, 2026** Download as PDF\\n\\nThis topic describes how you use the Harness Continuous Delivery Abstraction Model.\\n\\n### How do I model my CD practices in Harness?\\n\\nContinuous Delivery is modeled using Pipelines and Stages.\\n\\nIn each Stage, you define **what**  you want to deploy using Services, **where**  you want to deploy it using Environments, and **how**  you want to deploy it using Execution steps.\\n\\nFor example, a **Service**  uses your Kubernetes manifests and Docker image, an **Environment**  connects to your dev cluster, and Harness automatically generates an **Execution**  using a Rolling Deployment step.\\n\\n\\n\\nThe image above shows you the order for modeling a CD stage:\\n\\n1. Create a pipeline.\\n\\n2. Add a CD stage.\\n\\n3. Define a service.\\n\\n4. Target an environment and infrastructure.\\n\\n5. Select execution steps.\\n\\nYou can model visually, using code, or via the REST API.\\n\\n#### Pipeline Studio (Visual)\\n\\nModel your process visually using a guided sequence:\\n\\n\\n\\n#### YAML Builder\\n\\nModel your process in code using a full-featured YAML editor:\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n#### REST API\\n\\nModel your process using a full-featured REST API:\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n### How do I automate my CD process in Harness?\\n\\nHarness Continuous Delivery provides Triggers for automating the execution of Pipelines, multiple settings for adding conditions to how the Pipeline executes and rolls back, and Approvals to ensure that the Pipeline only proceeds when safe to do so.\\n\\n#### Triggers\\n\\nAutomate the execution of a Pipeline in response to changes in manifests/specs, artifacts, or on a schedule:\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n#### Conditions\\n\\nSet when, if, and how a Stage executes and what to do if it fails:\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n#### Approvals\\n\\nAdd checks at any point in your process to ensure that deployments are safe:\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n### Verification\\n\\nHarness' Continuous Verification (CV) approach simplifies verification.\\n\\nHarness CV integrates with your APMs and logging tools to:\\n\\n- Verify that the deployed service is running safely and perform automatic rollbacks.\\n\\n- Apply machine learning to every deployment to identify and flag anomalies in future deployments.\\n\\n\\n\\nFor more details, go to .\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThis topic provided a high-level overview of how you can model your software delivery process in Harness Continuous Delivery Pipelines and Stages.\\n\\nFor more details and examples, go to:\\n\\n- \\n\\n- \\n\\n- \\n\\n- \\n\\n## How Harness Models it's Pipelines?\\n\\n from Harness highlights their journey towards optimizing their Continuous Delivery (CD) pipelines. They address challenges like migration complexities, pipeline management issues, and the lack of standardization across services. By introducing a simplified, unified \\\"Golden K8s Pipeline,\\\" integrating version control through GitHub, and adopting a uniform deployment process, Harness streamlined its deployment strategies. These changes resulted in significant benefits such as enhanced collaboration, consistent deployment practices, and automated workflows, paving the way for further advancements like adopting Helm Charts for better scalability and simplification.\\n\\n### Demo Video\\n\\n0.8×\\n\\n1×\\n\\n### 1.2×\\n\\n1.5×\\n\\n1.7×\\n\\n2×\\n\\n2.5×\\n\\n7 min⚡️5 min 58 sec2 min 51 sec\\n\\n🙌\\n\\n6\\n\\nIntroduction\\n\\n7 Comments\\n\\n- \\nYash Singh0:00\\nNov 27, 2024\\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nApr 29, 2024\\nThank you Rohan! 🙏\\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nDec 21, 2024\\nThanks! Great overview and it makes it clear why this is far superior to GitHub Actions, Azure Devops and Jenkins.\\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nDec 28, 2024\\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 This was helpful \\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nJan 11, 2025\\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nFeb 6, 2025\\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 This was helpful \\n\\n- A\\nAnonymous7:10\\nMar 19, 2025\\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \\n\\n#### Pipeline Template\\n\\nThis YAML describes a pipeline configuration for deploying Kubernetes (K8s) services using a template named \\\"Golden_K8s.\\\" The pipeline, designated as \\\"Golden Harness K8s Deployment,\\\" is structured for deploying services across various environments, including QA, production, and UAT, while ensuring deployment on both primary and failover infrastructures. It incorporates steps for prerequisite checks, applying Kubernetes resources, and post-deployment actions, which may involve updating Jira. The configuration also allows for specifying variables related to deployment types, environments, and integration points such as webhooks, sign-off pages, and Git details, emphasizing flexibility and control in deployment processes.\\n\\n```\\npipeline:\\n\\n  name: Golden Harness K8s Deployment\\n\\n  identifier: Golden_Harness_K8s_Deployment\\n\\n  projectIdentifier: Operations\\n\\n  orgIdentifier: Harness\\n\\n  description: This pipeline is based on a golden stage template to be used for k8s deployment of services. This will implicitly take care of deploying the image on both primary & failover infrastructures. This will handle environments of type qa,qafree,prod1(prod),prod2(free),prod3(compliance) & uat.\\n\\n  tags:\\n\\n    golden: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n    ops_owned: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n    regulated: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n  stages:\\n\\n    - stage:\\n\\n        name: deploy_service\\n\\n        identifier: deploy_service\\n\\n        template:\\n\\n          templateRef: Golden_K8s\\n\\n          templateInputs:\\n\\n            type: Deployment\\n\\n            spec:\\n\\n              services:\\n\\n                values: <+input>\\n\\n              environments:\\n\\n                values: <+input>\\n\\n              execution:\\n\\n                steps:\\n\\n                  - stepGroup:\\n\\n                      identifier: pre_requisite\\n\\n                      steps:\\n\\n                        - step:\\n\\n                            identifier: get_deployed_version\\n\\n                            template:\\n\\n                              templateInputs:\\n\\n                                type: ShellScript\\n\\n                                spec:\\n\\n                                  environmentVariables:\\n\\n                                    - name: deploymentName\\n\\n                                      type: String\\n\\n                                      value: <+input>\\n\\n                                    - name: versionedNs\\n\\n                                      type: String\\n\\n                                      value: <+input>\\n\\n                                    - name: isStatefulSet\\n\\n                                      type: String\\n\\n                                      value: <+input>\\n\\n                  - step:\\n\\n                      identifier: hpa\\n\\n                      type: K8sApply\\n\\n                      when:\\n\\n                        condition: <+input>\\n\\n                  - stepGroup:\\n\\n                      identifier: post_steps_primary\\n\\n                      steps:\\n\\n                        - parallel:\\n\\n                            - step:\\n\\n                                identifier: mark_jira_deployed\\n\\n                                type: ShellScript\\n\\n                                spec:\\n\\n                                  source:\\n\\n                                    type: Inline\\n\\n                                    spec:\\n\\n                                      script: <+input>.default(\\\"Please fill in if applicable script here\\\")\\n\\n                                when:\\n\\n                                  condition: <+input>\\n\\n            variables:\\n\\n              - name: ChangeList\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>\\n\\n              - name: QASignOffPage\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>\\n\\n              - name: DeploymentType\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>.allowedValues(new-rel,hf-feature,hf-regression,rollback,bounce)\\n\\n              - name: If_Regression_Choose_TicketPriority\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>.allowedValues(P0,P1,NA)\\n\\n              - name: sanity_urls\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>\\n\\n              - name: WEBHOOK_LIST_COMMA_SEP\\n\\n                type: String\\n\\n                value: <+input>\\n\\n  variables:\\n\\n    - name: envType\\n\\n      type: String\\n\\n      description: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n      value: <+env.identifier>\\n\\n    - name: availabilityType\\n\\n      type: String\\n\\n      description: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n      value: <+stage.spec.execution.steps.pre_requisite.steps.set_availability_type.output.outputVariables.infraType>\\n\\n    - name: gitConnector\\n\\n      type: String\\n\\n      description: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n      value: <+env.variables.gitConnector>\\n\\n    - name: branchName\\n\\n      type: String\\n\\n      description: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n      value: <+env.variables.branchName>\\n\\n    - name: ENABLE_COVERAGE\\n\\n      type: String\\n\\n      default: \\\"false\\\"\\n\\n      description: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n      value: <+input>.allowedValues(true,false)\\n\\n  delegateSelectors:\\n\\n    - <+env.variables.delegate>\\n```\\n#### Stage Template\\n\\nThe YAML outlines a detailed stage template named \\\"Golden K8s\\\" for deploying Kubernetes services, incorporating various steps to ensure robust and regulated deployments. It checks environmental prerequisites, verifies QA deployments, sets deployment-specific parameters, and includes security scans, mandatory validation, and approval steps. The template also manages notifications, sanity checks post-deployment, and has provisions for rollback in case of failure. This structured approach emphasizes thoroughness, security, and compliance, tailored for diverse environments including production and QA.\\n\\n```\\ntemplate:\\n\\n  name: \\\"Golden K8s \\\"\\n\\n  identifier: Golden_K8s\\n\\n  type: Stage\\n\\n  projectIdentifier: Operations\\n\\n  orgIdentifier: Harness\\n\\n  tags:\\n\\n    regulated: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n    ops_owned: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n    bt_managed: \\\"\\\"\\n\\n  spec:\\n\\n    type: Deployment\\n\\n    spec:\\n\\n      deploymentType: Kubernetes\\n\\n      services:\\n\\n        values: <+input>\\n\\n        metadata:\\n\\n          parallel: true\\n\\n      environments:\\n\\n        metadata:\\n\\n          parallel: false\\n\\n        values: <+input>\\n\\n      execution:\\n\\n        steps:\\n\\n          - stepGroup:\\n\\n              name: PRE_REQUISITE\\n\\n              identifier: pre_requisite\\n\\n              steps:\\n\\n                - step:\\n\\n                    type: ShellScript\\n\\n                    name: Check_namespace_env_mapping\\n\\n                    identifier: Check_namespace_env_mapping\\n\\n                    spec:\\n\\n                      shell: Bash\\n\\n                      onDelegate: true\\n\\n                      source:\\n\\n                        type: Inline\\n\\n                        spec:\\n\\n                          script: |-\\n\\n set -x\\n\\n if [ \\\"<+infra.namespace>\\\" == \\\"NOT_SET_CHECK_WITH_SRE\\\" ]\\n\\n then\\n\\n                              echo \\\" Error!! For the current Env: <+env.name> is not mapped a namespace, as it not an existing deployment\\\"\\n\\n exit 1\\n\\n fi\\n\\n                      environmentVariables: []\\n\\n                      outputVariables: []\\n\\n                    timeout: 10m\\n\\n                    when:\\n\\n                      stageStatus: Success\\n\\n                    failureStrategies: []\\n\\n                - step:\\n\\n                    type: Http\\n\\n                    name: check_image_deployed_in_qa\\n\\n                    identifier: check_image_deployed_in_qa\\n\\n                    spec:\\n\\n                      url: https://stage.harness.io/gateway/pipeline/api/pipelines/execution/summary?routingId=wFHXHD0RRQWoO8tIZT5YVw&accountIdentifier=wFHXHD0RRQWoO8tIZT5YVw&projectIdentifier=Operations&orgIdentifier=Harness&page=0&size=100&sort=startTs%2CDESC&module=cd\\n\\n                      method: POST\\n\\n                      headers:\\n\\n                        - key: x-api-key\\n\\n                          value: <+secrets.getValue('qa_image_check_token')>\\n\\n                        - key: content-type\\n\\n                          value: application/json\\n\\n                      outputVariables:\\n\\n                        - name: qaLastStatus\\n\\n                          value: <+json.select(\\\"data.content[0].status\\\",httpResponseBody)>\\n\\n                          type: String\\n\\n                      requestBody: \\\"{ \\\\\\\"moduleProperties\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"cd\\\\\\\": { \\\\\\\"serviceIdentifiers\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"<+service.identifier>\\\\\\\",\"\n}"}],"details":{"url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/cd-pipeline-modeling-overview/","content":"- \n\n    - New to Continuous Delivery?\n\n    - \n\n    - \n\n    - \n\n    - Use Continuous Delivery\n\n    - \n\n    - \n\n    - \n\n    - Use GitOps\n\n    - \n\n    - \n\n    - Troubleshooting & Resources\n\n    - \n\n        - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n            - \n\n    - \n\n- \n\n- \n\n- \n\n- CD pipeline modeling overview\n\n# CD pipeline modeling overview\n\nLast updated on **Jan 12, 2026** Download as PDF\n\nThis topic describes how you use the Harness Continuous Delivery Abstraction Model.\n\n### How do I model my CD practices in Harness?\n\nContinuous Delivery is modeled using Pipelines and Stages.\n\nIn each Stage, you define **what**  you want to deploy using Services, **where**  you want to deploy it using Environments, and **how**  you want to deploy it using Execution steps.\n\nFor example, a **Service**  uses your Kubernetes manifests and Docker image, an **Environment**  connects to your dev cluster, and Harness automatically generates an **Execution**  using a Rolling Deployment step.\n\n\n\nThe image above shows you the order for modeling a CD stage:\n\n1. Create a pipeline.\n\n2. Add a CD stage.\n\n3. Define a service.\n\n4. Target an environment and infrastructure.\n\n5. Select execution steps.\n\nYou can model visually, using code, or via the REST API.\n\n#### Pipeline Studio (Visual)\n\nModel your process visually using a guided sequence:\n\n\n\n#### YAML Builder\n\nModel your process in code using a full-featured YAML editor:\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n#### REST API\n\nModel your process using a full-featured REST API:\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n### How do I automate my CD process in Harness?\n\nHarness Continuous Delivery provides Triggers for automating the execution of Pipelines, multiple settings for adding conditions to how the Pipeline executes and rolls back, and Approvals to ensure that the Pipeline only proceeds when safe to do so.\n\n#### Triggers\n\nAutomate the execution of a Pipeline in response to changes in manifests/specs, artifacts, or on a schedule:\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n#### Conditions\n\nSet when, if, and how a Stage executes and what to do if it fails:\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n#### Approvals\n\nAdd checks at any point in your process to ensure that deployments are safe:\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n### Verification\n\nHarness' Continuous Verification (CV) approach simplifies verification.\n\nHarness CV integrates with your APMs and logging tools to:\n\n- Verify that the deployed service is running safely and perform automatic rollbacks.\n\n- Apply machine learning to every deployment to identify and flag anomalies in future deployments.\n\n\n\nFor more details, go to .\n\n### Summary\n\nThis topic provided a high-level overview of how you can model your software delivery process in Harness Continuous Delivery Pipelines and Stages.\n\nFor more details and examples, go to:\n\n- \n\n- \n\n- \n\n- \n\n## How Harness Models it's Pipelines?\n\n from Harness highlights their journey towards optimizing their Continuous Delivery (CD) pipelines. They address challenges like migration complexities, pipeline management issues, and the lack of standardization across services. By introducing a simplified, unified \"Golden K8s Pipeline,\" integrating version control through GitHub, and adopting a uniform deployment process, Harness streamlined its deployment strategies. These changes resulted in significant benefits such as enhanced collaboration, consistent deployment practices, and automated workflows, paving the way for further advancements like adopting Helm Charts for better scalability and simplification.\n\n### Demo Video\n\n0.8×\n\n1×\n\n### 1.2×\n\n1.5×\n\n1.7×\n\n2×\n\n2.5×\n\n7 min⚡️5 min 58 sec2 min 51 sec\n\n🙌\n\n6\n\nIntroduction\n\n7 Comments\n\n- \nYash Singh0:00\nNov 27, 2024\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nApr 29, 2024\nThank you Rohan! 🙏\n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nDec 21, 2024\nThanks! Great overview and it makes it clear why this is far superior to GitHub Actions, Azure Devops and Jenkins.\n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nDec 28, 2024\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 This was helpful \n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nJan 11, 2025\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nFeb 6, 2025\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 This was helpful \n\n- A\nAnonymous7:10\nMar 19, 2025\nThank you, Rohan! 🙏 \n\n#### Pipeline Template\n\nThis YAML describes a pipeline configuration for deploying Kubernetes (K8s) services using a template named \"Golden_K8s.\" The pipeline, designated as \"Golden Harness K8s Deployment,\" is structured for deploying services across various environments, including QA, production, and UAT, while ensuring deployment on both primary and failover infrastructures. It incorporates steps for prerequisite checks, applying Kubernetes resources, and post-deployment actions, which may involve updating Jira. The configuration also allows for specifying variables related to deployment types, environments, and integration points such as webhooks, sign-off pages, and Git details, emphasizing flexibility and control in deployment processes.\n\n```\npipeline:\n\n  name: Golden Harness K8s Deployment\n\n  identifier: Golden_Harness_K8s_Deployment\n\n  projectIdentifier: Operations\n\n  orgIdentifier: Harness\n\n  description: This pipeline is based on a golden stage template to be used for k8s deployment of services. This will implicitly take care of deploying the image on both primary & failover infrastructures. This will handle environments of type qa,qafree,prod1(prod),prod2(free),prod3(compliance) & uat.\n\n  tags:\n\n    golden: \"\"\n\n    ops_owned: \"\"\n\n    regulated: \"\"\n\n  stages:\n\n    - stage:\n\n        name: deploy_service\n\n        identifier: deploy_service\n\n        template:\n\n          templateRef: Golden_K8s\n\n          templateInputs:\n\n            type: Deployment\n\n            spec:\n\n              services:\n\n                values: <+input>\n\n              environments:\n\n                values: <+input>\n\n              execution:\n\n                steps:\n\n                  - stepGroup:\n\n                      identifier: pre_requisite\n\n                      steps:\n\n                        - step:\n\n                            identifier: get_deployed_version\n\n                            template:\n\n                              templateInputs:\n\n                                type: ShellScript\n\n                                spec:\n\n                                  environmentVariables:\n\n                                    - name: deploymentName\n\n                                      type: String\n\n                                      value: <+input>\n\n                                    - name: versionedNs\n\n                                      type: String\n\n                                      value: <+input>\n\n                                    - name: isStatefulSet\n\n                                      type: String\n\n                                      value: <+input>\n\n                  - step:\n\n                      identifier: hpa\n\n                      type: K8sApply\n\n                      when:\n\n                        condition: <+input>\n\n                  - stepGroup:\n\n                      identifier: post_steps_primary\n\n                      steps:\n\n                        - parallel:\n\n                            - step:\n\n                                identifier: mark_jira_deployed\n\n                                type: ShellScript\n\n                                spec:\n\n                                  source:\n\n                                    type: Inline\n\n                                    spec:\n\n                                      script: <+input>.default(\"Please fill in if applicable script here\")\n\n                                when:\n\n                                  condition: <+input>\n\n            variables:\n\n              - name: ChangeList\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>\n\n              - name: QASignOffPage\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>\n\n              - name: DeploymentType\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>.allowedValues(new-rel,hf-feature,hf-regression,rollback,bounce)\n\n              - name: If_Regression_Choose_TicketPriority\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>.allowedValues(P0,P1,NA)\n\n              - name: sanity_urls\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>\n\n              - name: WEBHOOK_LIST_COMMA_SEP\n\n                type: String\n\n                value: <+input>\n\n  variables:\n\n    - name: envType\n\n      type: String\n\n      description: \"\"\n\n      value: <+env.identifier>\n\n    - name: availabilityType\n\n      type: String\n\n      description: \"\"\n\n      value: <+stage.spec.execution.steps.pre_requisite.steps.set_availability_type.output.outputVariables.infraType>\n\n    - name: gitConnector\n\n      type: String\n\n      description: \"\"\n\n      value: <+env.variables.gitConnector>\n\n    - name: branchName\n\n      type: String\n\n      description: \"\"\n\n      value: <+env.variables.branchName>\n\n    - name: ENABLE_COVERAGE\n\n      type: String\n\n      default: \"false\"\n\n      description: \"\"\n\n      value: <+input>.allowedValues(true,false)\n\n  delegateSelectors:\n\n    - <+env.variables.delegate>\n```\n#### Stage Template\n\nThe YAML outlines a detailed stage template named \"Golden K8s\" for deploying Kubernetes services, incorporating various steps to ensure robust and regulated deployments. It checks environmental prerequisites, verifies QA deployments, sets deployment-specific parameters, and includes security scans, mandatory validation, and approval steps. The template also manages notifications, sanity checks post-deployment, and has provisions for rollback in case of failure. This structured approach emphasizes thoroughness, security, and compliance, tailored for diverse environments including production and QA.\n\n```\ntemplate:\n\n  name: \"Golden K8s \"\n\n  identifier: Golden_K8s\n\n  type: Stage\n\n  projectIdentifier: Operations\n\n  orgIdentifier: Harness\n\n  tags:\n\n    regulated: \"\"\n\n    ops_owned: \"\"\n\n    bt_managed: \"\"\n\n  spec:\n\n    type: Deployment\n\n    spec:\n\n      deploymentType: Kubernetes\n\n      services:\n\n        values: <+input>\n\n        metadata:\n\n          parallel: true\n\n      environments:\n\n        metadata:\n\n          parallel: false\n\n        values: <+input>\n\n      execution:\n\n        steps:\n\n          - stepGroup:\n\n              name: PRE_REQUISITE\n\n              identifier: pre_requisite\n\n              steps:\n\n                - step:\n\n                    type: ShellScript\n\n                    name: Check_namespace_env_mapping\n\n                    identifier: Check_namespace_env_mapping\n\n                    spec:\n\n                      shell: Bash\n\n                      onDelegate: true\n\n                      source:\n\n                        type: Inline\n\n                        spec:\n\n                          script: |-\n\n set -x\n\n if [ \"<+infra.namespace>\" == \"NOT_SET_CHECK_WITH_SRE\" ]\n\n then\n\n                              echo \" Error!! For the current Env: <+env.name> is not mapped a namespace, as it not an existing deployment\"\n\n exit 1\n\n fi\n\n                      environmentVariables: []\n\n                      outputVariables: []\n\n                    timeout: 10m\n\n                    when:\n\n                      stageStatus: Success\n\n                    failureStrategies: []\n\n                - step:\n\n                    type: Http\n\n                    name: check_image_deployed_in_qa\n\n                    identifier: check_image_deployed_in_qa\n\n                    spec:\n\n                      url: https://stage.harness.io/gateway/pipeline/api/pipelines/execution/summary?routingId=wFHXHD0RRQWoO8tIZT5YVw&accountIdentifier=wFHXHD0RRQWoO8tIZT5YVw&projectIdentifier=Operations&orgIdentifier=Harness&page=0&size=100&sort=startTs%2CDESC&module=cd\n\n                      method: POST\n\n                      headers:\n\n                        - key: x-api-key\n\n                          value: <+secrets.getValue('qa_image_check_token')>\n\n                        - key: content-type\n\n                          value: application/json\n\n                      outputVariables:\n\n                        - name: qaLastStatus\n\n                          value: <+json.select(\"data.content[0].status\",httpResponseBody)>\n\n                          type: String\n\n                      requestBody: \"{ \\\"moduleProperties\\\": { \\\"cd\\\": { \\\"serviceIdentifiers\\\": \\\"<+service.identifier>\\\","},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802077987}}
{"type":"message","id":"91f95e24","parentId":"6b9fd938","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:19.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oyek4gpssun3_3","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Harness.io CI/CD modules CI/CD Pipelines Deployment environments GitOps delegate 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"miaoda\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"1. Harness Deployments Onboarding Path\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/onboarding-path/\",\n      \"description\": \"The Harness Delegate is a service you run in your local network or VPC to connect your artifacts, infrastructure, collaboration, verification, and other providers, with Harness Manager.\\nThe first time you connect Harness to a third-party resource, the Harness Delegate is installed in your target infrastructure, for example, a Kubernetes cluster. After the delegate is installed and registers with Harness, you can Harness connect to third-party resources. The delegate performs all operations, including deployment and...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness GitOps: The Basics and a Quick Tutorial\",\n      \"url\": \"https://codefresh.io/learn/harness-io/harness-gitops/\",\n      \"description\": \"What Are Harness GitOps Pipelines?\\nHarness GitOps pipelines implements GitOps principles by automating deployment workflows and infrastructure provisioning. They work with Argo CD and Flux, allowing teams to manage GitOps deployments from a centralized control plane.\\nOne key feature is pull request pipelines, which automate the propagation of changes across multiple services and environments. Harness also provides rollback capabilities by continuously verifying deployments with observability tools. If an issue is detected, Harness can...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析:架构设计、核心功能与实战指南_harness开源项目-CSDN博客\",\n      \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\\n1. 持续集成（CI）\\n智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\\n智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\\n并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\\n容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\\n2. 持续交付（CD）\\n多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\\n自动化...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Deploy your own microservice application\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/get-started/tutorials/ownapp/\",\n      \"description\": \"Enter the name <beginning of the code>ownapp_bluegreen_pipeline<end of the code>.\\nSelect Inline to store the pipeline in H...\\nYou can switch to the Visual pipeline editor and confirm the pipeline stage and execution steps.\\nCLI Command for Rolling deployment:\\n<beginning of the code>harness pipeline --file rolling-pipeline.yml apply<end of the code>\\nYou can switch to the Visual pipeline editor and confirm the pipeline stage and execution steps.\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Getting Started with Deployments\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/\",\n      \"description\": \"From your Harness project, select Pipelines from the left navigation menu.\\nClick + Create a Pipeline.\\n2. Configure Pipeline Basics\\nProvide a Name for your pipeline (e.g., \\\"Deploy to Production\\\")\\nChoose Inline for Pipeline Storage (stores configuration in Harness)\\nClick Start\\ninfo\\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using Remote storage. Learn more in the Pipelines documentation.\\nStep 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Deploy using Kubernetes Manifest\",\n      \"url\": \"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/get-started/tutorials/kubernetes-container-deployments/manifest/\",\n      \"description\": \"The Harness Delegate is a service that runs in your local network or VPC to establish connections between the Harness Manager and various providers such as artifacts registries, cloud platforms, etc. The delegate is installed in the target infrastructure, for example, a Kubernetes cluster, and performs operations including deployment and integration. Environments define the deployment location, categorized as Production or Pre-Production. Each environment includes infrastructure definitions for VMs, Kubernetes clusters, or other target infrastructures. To learn more about...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"How to Create a Harness Pipeline and integrate with Azure\",\n      \"url\": \"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/azureinfrastructureblog/how-to-create-a-harness-pipeline-and-integrate-with-azure/4499862\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness...\\nHarness Delegate\\nThe Harness Delegate is a lightweight agent you install in your own infrastructure (such as an Azure VM, Kubernetes cluster, or VNet). It acts as a secure bridge between Harness’s SaaS control plane and your internal resources. The Delegate executes pipeline tasks, connects to Azure services, and manages deployments—all while keeping your credentials and secrets within your environment. Delegates communicate outbound over HTTPS, making them firewall-friendly and easy to manage.\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Setup Guide\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/harness-community/reference-architecture-node/blob/main/docs/HARNESS_SETUP.md\",\n      \"description\": \"957 lines (730 loc) · 18.9 KB\\nHarness Setup Guide\\nComplete guide for setting up Harness CI/CD pipelines for the Reference Architecture Node.js application.\\nTable of Contents\\nOverview\\nPrerequisites\\nAccount Setup\\nConnectors Configuration\\nPipeline Setup\\nSecrets Management\\nTriggers and Automation\\nAdvanced Features\\nTroubleshooting\\nOverview\\nThis reference architecture includes two Harness pipelines:\\nBuild Pipeline - Builds, tests,...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"0 - Introduction\",\n      \"url\": \"https://harness-developer-hub.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/labs/Harness_CI_CD_Dev_Days_Lab_Guide.pdf\",\n      \"description\": \"● Understand key CI/CD concepts map them to Harness entities ● Build, test, and push an application image with Harness Continuous Integration ● Configure and deploy a GitOps application using ApplicationSet ● Manage target environments with PR pipelines ● Visualize and test CI, CD, and GitOps in an end-to-end pipeline\\nOn the Instruqt lab environment, execute the following commands (replace the placeholders with your Harness Account ID and the delegate token which you just copied):\\nexport DE...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://toolradar.com/tools/harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Harness Unclaimed\\nModern software delivery platform\\nTesting & QA\\nCI/CD\\nInfrastructure as Code\\n4.6\\nTL;...\\nHarness is a comprehensive DevOps platform providing continuous delivery, CI/CD pipelines, GitOps, infrastructure as code management, and security testing orchestration in one platform.\\nHow does Harness pricing work?\\nHarness offers a free tier for small teams. Essentials bundles modules together for growing organizations. Enterprise offers modular pick-and-choose pricing. \",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Harness.io CI/CD modules CI/CD Pipelines Deployment environments GitOps delegate 2026","provider":"miaoda","count":10,"results":[{"title":"1. Harness Deployments Onboarding Path","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/cd-onboarding/new-user/onboarding-path/","description":"The Harness Delegate is a service you run in your local network or VPC to connect your artifacts, infrastructure, collaboration, verification, and other providers, with Harness Manager.\nThe first time you connect Harness to a third-party resource, the Harness Delegate is installed in your target infrastructure, for example, a Kubernetes cluster. After the delegate is installed and registers with Harness, you can Harness connect to third-party resources. The delegate performs all operations, including deployment and...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness GitOps: The Basics and a Quick Tutorial","url":"https://codefresh.io/learn/harness-io/harness-gitops/","description":"What Are Harness GitOps Pipelines?\nHarness GitOps pipelines implements GitOps principles by automating deployment workflows and infrastructure provisioning. They work with Argo CD and Flux, allowing teams to manage GitOps deployments from a centralized control plane.\nOne key feature is pull request pipelines, which automate the propagation of changes across multiple services and environments. Harness also provides rollback capabilities by continuously verifying deployments with observability tools. If an issue is detected, Harness can...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析:架构设计、核心功能与实战指南_harness开源项目-CSDN博客","url":"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586","description":"Harness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\n1. 持续集成（CI）\n智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\n智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\n并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\n容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\n2. 持续交付（CD）\n多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\n自动化...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Deploy your own microservice application","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/get-started/tutorials/ownapp/","description":"Enter the name <beginning of the code>ownapp_bluegreen_pipeline<end of the code>.\nSelect Inline to store the pipeline in H...\nYou can switch to the Visual pipeline editor and confirm the pipeline stage and execution steps.\nCLI Command for Rolling deployment:\n<beginning of the code>harness pipeline --file rolling-pipeline.yml apply<end of the code>\nYou can switch to the Visual pipeline editor and confirm the pipeline stage and execution steps.\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Getting Started with Deployments","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/getting-started/","description":"From your Harness project, select Pipelines from the left navigation menu.\nClick + Create a Pipeline.\n2. Configure Pipeline Basics\nProvide a Name for your pipeline (e.g., \"Deploy to Production\")\nChoose Inline for Pipeline Storage (stores configuration in Harness)\nClick Start\ninfo\nYou can also store pipelines in Git using Remote storage. Learn more in the Pipelines documentation.\nStep 2: Add a Deploy Stage and Configure Deployment\nAdd a Deploy stage and configure...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Deploy using Kubernetes Manifest","url":"https://developer.harness.io/docs/continuous-delivery/get-started/tutorials/kubernetes-container-deployments/manifest/","description":"The Harness Delegate is a service that runs in your local network or VPC to establish connections between the Harness Manager and various providers such as artifacts registries, cloud platforms, etc. The delegate is installed in the target infrastructure, for example, a Kubernetes cluster, and performs operations including deployment and integration. Environments define the deployment location, categorized as Production or Pre-Production. Each environment includes infrastructure definitions for VMs, Kubernetes clusters, or other target infrastructures. To learn more about...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"How to Create a Harness Pipeline and integrate with Azure","url":"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/azureinfrastructureblog/how-to-create-a-harness-pipeline-and-integrate-with-azure/4499862","description":"Harness...\nHarness Delegate\nThe Harness Delegate is a lightweight agent you install in your own infrastructure (such as an Azure VM, Kubernetes cluster, or VNet). It acts as a secure bridge between Harness’s SaaS control plane and your internal resources. The Delegate executes pipeline tasks, connects to Azure services, and manages deployments—all while keeping your credentials and secrets within your environment. Delegates communicate outbound over HTTPS, making them firewall-friendly and easy to manage.","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Setup Guide","url":"https://github.com/harness-community/reference-architecture-node/blob/main/docs/HARNESS_SETUP.md","description":"957 lines (730 loc) · 18.9 KB\nHarness Setup Guide\nComplete guide for setting up Harness CI/CD pipelines for the Reference Architecture Node.js application.\nTable of Contents\nOverview\nPrerequisites\nAccount Setup\nConnectors Configuration\nPipeline Setup\nSecrets Management\nTriggers and Automation\nAdvanced Features\nTroubleshooting\nOverview\nThis reference architecture includes two Harness pipelines:\nBuild Pipeline - Builds, tests,...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"0 - Introduction","url":"https://harness-developer-hub.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/labs/Harness_CI_CD_Dev_Days_Lab_Guide.pdf","description":"● Understand key CI/CD concepts map them to Harness entities ● Build, test, and push an application image with Harness Continuous Integration ● Configure and deploy a GitOps application using ApplicationSet ● Manage target environments with PR pipelines ● Visualize and test CI, CD, and GitOps in an end-to-end pipeline\nOn the Instruqt lab environment, execute the following commands (replace the placeholders with your Harness Account ID and the delegate token which you just copied):\nexport DE...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness","url":"https://toolradar.com/tools/harness","description":"Harness Unclaimed\nModern software delivery platform\nTesting & QA\nCI/CD\nInfrastructure as Code\n4.6\nTL;...\nHarness is a comprehensive DevOps platform providing continuous delivery, CI/CD pipelines, GitOps, infrastructure as code management, and security testing orchestration in one platform.\nHow does Harness pricing work?\nHarness offers a free tier for small teams. Essentials bundles modules together for growing organizations. Enterprise offers modular pick-and-choose pricing. ","siteName":""}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802079558}}
{"type":"message","id":"eeed1eed","parentId":"91f95e24","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:44.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of both:\n1. Harness.io (the DevOps CI/CD platform) - with its core modules: CI, CD, GitOps, Cloud Cost Management, etc.\n2. The user's original request - they want to learn about Harness Engineering (AI Agent harness) AND create agents for different roles\n\nWait, I think I was overthinking this. The user said \"学习什么事harness，并创建对应的智能体\" initially. They want to learn about Harness Engineering. Then they want to create agents.\n\nBut when they said \"CI/CD、流水线、部署、环境管理\"，I got confused. Looking at this again - maybe they're asking about Harness Engineering's CI/CD? But Harness Engineering doesn't have CI/CD...\n \nActually, I think they're asking about Harness.io as a platform, and they want agents that help them use Harness.io for different roles. So the user wants me to study Harness.io thoroughly and create four specialized agents—one each for development managers, product managers, QA/testers, and operations roles—that each understand their domain, know how to work within Harness.io, and can produce relevant outputs.\n\nLet me dig into the details of Harness.io's module structure so I can build these agents with the right capabilities and knowledge.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uiuangzbh708_1","name":"web_crawl","arguments":{"url":"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uiuangzbh708_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Harness.io modules CI CD GitOps Cloud Cost Management Security Testing Orchestration features 2026"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":9297,"output":335,"cacheRead":47931,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57563,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775802079563,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0ae4e0e6-6c9e-449a-9ad0-64dc87458b19"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed59cfa0","parentId":"eeed1eed","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:45.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uiuangzbh708_1","toolName":"web_crawl","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586\",\n  \"content\": \"# 【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析：架构设计、核心功能与实战指南\\n\\n最新推荐文章于 2026-04-07 14:44:41 发布\\n\\n原创最新推荐文章于 2026-04-07 14:44:41 发布559 阅读\\n\\n 6  \\n\\n 6  \\n\\n文章标签：\\n\\n  \\n\\nGitHub开源项目专栏收录该内容](https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/category_13138177.html)\\n\\n20 篇文章\\n\\n### 引言与背景\\n\\n在云计算和微服务架构普及的今天，传统DevOps工具链的碎片化问题日益凸显。Jenkins、GitLab CI、GitHub Actions等工具虽然功能强大，但也带来了配置复杂、维护成本高、缺乏统一治理的挑战。Harness作为新一代企业级持续交付平台，通过AI驱动的智能自动化、声明式流水线和统一平台理念，正在重塑现代软件交付范式。\\n\\n截至2026年3月，Harness在GitHub上已获得超过34,170个Star，最新版本v2.28.0于2026年3月27日发布，保持着平均每2-3天一次的活跃更新频率。本文将从技术深度出发，全面解析Harness的架构设计、核心模块实现、关键算法原理，并提供企业级部署的最佳实践指南。\\n\\n### 一、项目概述与技术定位\\n\\n#### 1.1 诞生背景与技术演进\\n\\nHarness的诞生源于对传统CI/CD工具链局限性的深刻洞察。在容器化和Kubernetes成为基础设施标准的背景下，传统工具面临着几个核心痛点：\\n\\n- **碎片化配置管理** ：Jenkins Groovy脚本、GitLab CI YAML、GitHub Actions workflow等多种配置语言并存\\n\\n- **运维复杂度高** ：插件依赖、版本冲突、安全更新等维护工作繁重\\n\\n- **缺乏高级部署策略** ：金丝雀发布、蓝绿部署等现代部署策略需要大量自定义脚本\\n\\n- **安全治理困难** ：缺乏统一的策略即代码（Policy as Code）框架\\n\\nHarness的创始人Rohit Gupta及其团队基于多年DevOps实践，提出了\\\"平台化DevOps\\\"的理念：将构建、测试、部署、验证、监控、优化等整个软件交付生命周期统一在一个智能平台中。\\n\\n#### 1.2 核心功能特点\\n\\nHarness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\\n\\n**1. 持续集成（CI）**\\n\\n- 智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\\n\\n- 智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\\n\\n- 并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\\n\\n- 容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\\n\\n**2. 持续交付（CD）**\\n\\n- 多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\\n\\n- 自动化验证：部署后自动执行测试和性能检查\\n\\n- 智能回滚：异常检测与自动回滚机制\\n\\n- GitOps集成：声明式基础设施即代码\\n\\n**3. 功能标记（Feature Flags）**\\n\\n- 渐进式发布：按用户群体、地理位置逐步发布\\n\\n- A/B测试框架：数据驱动的功能决策\\n\\n- 实时开关：无需重新部署的动态功能控制\\n\\n**4. 云成本管理**\\n\\n- 多云成本统一视图：AWS、Azure、GCP成本聚合\\n\\n- 成本标签与分配：团队/项目级成本追踪\\n\\n- AI驱动优化建议：闲置资源识别、预留实例优化\\n\\n**5. 安全测试**\\n\\n- 静态应用安全测试（SAST）：代码级漏洞扫描\\n\\n- 动态应用安全测试（DAST）：运行时安全检测\\n\\n- 软件组分分析（SCA）：依赖库安全扫描\\n\\n**6. 混沌工程**\\n\\n- 故障注入实验：验证系统弹性和容错能力\\n\\n- 自动化实验框架：可编程的实验编排\\n\\n**7. 工程洞察**\\n\\n- DORA指标可视化：部署频率、前置时间、平均修复时间、变更失败率\\n\\n- 团队效率分析：代码审查速度、发布周期、故障恢复能力\\n\\n#### 1.3 与Jenkins、GitLab CI的技术对比\\n\\n| 维度 | Jenkins | GitLab CI | Harness |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| **架构理念** | 插件化自动化服务器 | 集成化CI/CD | 平台化软件交付 |\\n| **配置方式** | Groovy脚本 | YAML配置 | 声明式YAML + 可视化编辑器 |\\n| **部署策略** | 需要自定义脚本 | 基础策略 | 内置高级策略（金丝雀、蓝绿等） |\\n| **智能特性** | 无 | 基础缓存 | AI驱动优化、智能测试选择 |\\n| **安全治理** | 插件依赖 | 基础RBAC | 策略即代码（OPA集成） |\\n| **运维成本** | 高（插件管理） | 中 | 低（统一平台） |\\n| **学习曲线** | 陡峭 | 中等 | 平缓（向导式配置） |\\n\\n注：Harness的核心创新在于将AI能力深度融入DevOps流程，通过智能测试选择、根因分析、自动优化建议等功能，显著提升交付效率和质量。\\n\\n#### 1.4 开源生态与技术价值\\n\\nHarness采用Apache 2.0开源协议，确保了技术透明度和社区参与度。其开源生态包含几个关键组件：\\n\\n- **Harness Core** ：平台核心引擎，包含流水线执行、策略评估等基础能力\\n\\n- **Drone集成** ：基于Drone的CI引擎，提供向后兼容性\\n\\n- **插件市场** ：丰富的第三方集成插件\\n\\n- **社区贡献** ：活跃的GitHub Issues、Discussions、社区论坛\\n\\n从技术价值角度，Harness解决了现代DevOps的三大核心矛盾：\\n\\n1. **速度与质量的矛盾** ：通过自动化测试和验证，确保快速交付不牺牲质量\\n\\n2. **灵活性与治理的矛盾** ：通过策略即代码框架，平衡开发自主性与组织合规性\\n\\n3. **创新与成本的矛盾** ：通过智能成本管理，在技术创新与财务控制之间找到平衡\\n\\n### 二、整体架构全景\\n\\n#### 2.1 微服务架构设计\\n\\nHarness采用现代化的微服务架构，各组件通过gRPC和REST API进行通信。整体架构分为四个主要层次：\\n\\n**基础设施层**\\n\\n- Kubernetes集群管理（支持多种云环境）\\n\\n- Docker运行时集成\\n\\n- 存储系统（PostgreSQL、MongoDB、Redis）\\n\\n- 消息队列（NATS、RabbitMQ）\\n\\n**平台核心层**\\n\\n- 身份认证与授权服务（OAuth2、SAML、LDAP）\\n\\n- 项目管理与组织管理\\n\\n- 审计日志与指标收集\\n\\n- 通知服务（Email、Slack、Webhook）\\n\\n**业务服务层**\\n\\n- CI引擎服务（构建、测试、打包）\\n\\n- CD引擎服务（部署、验证、回滚）\\n\\n- 功能标记服务（A/B测试、渐进发布）\\n\\n- 成本管理服务（成本分析、优化建议）\\n\\n- 安全测试服务（SAST、DAST、SCA）\\n\\n- 混沌工程服务（故障注入、实验编排）\\n\\n**接口层**\\n\\n- Web UI（React + TypeScript）\\n\\n- CLI工具（Go语言开发）\\n\\n- REST API（OpenAPI规范）\\n\\n- SDK库（Python、Java、Go等）\\n\\n#### 2.2 关键组件模块划分\\n\\n##### 2.2.1 流水线引擎（Pipeline Engine）\\n\\n- **解析器** ：YAML语法解析、模板变量替换\\n\\n- **调度器** ：阶段并行调度、依赖关系管理\\n\\n- **执行器** ：步骤执行、环境变量注入、输出收集\\n\\n- **状态机** ：流水线状态流转、超时控制、重试逻辑\\n\\n##### 2.2.2 智能部署模块（Intelligent Deployment）\\n\\n- **策略评估器** ：部署策略条件评估\\n\\n- **流量控制器** ：金丝雀发布流量分割\\n\\n- **健康检查器** ：应用健康状态监控\\n\\n- **自动回滚器** ：异常检测与自动回滚\\n\\n##### 2.2.3 集成框架（Integration Framework）\\n\\n- **连接器管理** ：Git提供商、云平台、容器仓库\\n\\n- **插件运行时** ：动态插件加载与执行\\n\\n- **API适配器** ：第三方服务API封装\\n\\n- **数据同步器** ：配置同步与状态一致性\\n\\n##### 2.2.4 数据存储与缓存\\n\\n- **元数据存储** ：PostgreSQL存储核心实体\\n\\n- **文档存储** ：MongoDB存储非结构化数据\\n\\n- **缓存层** ：Redis缓存热点数据和会话信息\\n\\n- **对象存储** ：S3/兼容存储存储构建产物\\n\\n#### 2.3 数据流设计\\n\\nHarness的数据流设计采用事件驱动架构，核心数据流路径包括：\\n\\n**构建数据流**\\n\\n1. Git Webhook触发构建事件\\n\\n2. 事件总线分发到CI引擎\\n\\n3. CI服务拉取代码、执行构建步骤\\n\\n4. 构建产物上传到制品仓库\\n\\n5. 构建状态更新到数据库\\n\\n**部署数据流**\\n\\n1. 流水线触发部署阶段\\n\\n2. CD服务读取部署配置\\n\\n3. 策略评估器计算部署计划\\n\\n4. 执行器执行实际部署操作\\n\\n5. 验证器监控应用健康状态\\n\\n6. 结果存储到审计日志\\n\\n**配置数据流**\\n\\n1. 用户在UI或YAML中修改配置\\n\\n2. 配置验证器检查语法和语义\\n\\n3. 配置持久化到数据库\\n\\n4. 配置同步到相关服务\\n\\n5. 配置变更触发相关流水线\\n\\n#### 2.4 API接口设计\\n\\nHarness提供全面REST API，采用资源导向设计原则：\\n\\n```\\n# API端点示例\\n/api/v1/projects/{project_id}/pipelines\\n/api/v1/projects/{project_id}/pipelines/{pipeline_id}/execute\\n/api/v1/connectors/{connector_type}/{connector_id}\\n/api/v1/secrets/{secret_id}\\n/api/v1/audit/events\\nyaml\\n```\\nAPI设计特点：\\n\\n- **版本控制** ：URI中包含版本号，确保向后兼容\\n\\n- **认证授权** ：支持API Key、JWT Token等多种认证方式\\n\\n- **分页过滤** ：标准化的分页参数和过滤条件\\n\\n- **错误处理** ：统一的错误响应格式和状态码\\n\\n- **文档自动生成** ：基于Swagger/OpenAPI自动生成文档\\n\\n#### 2.5 声明式流水线设计理念\\n\\nHarness的核心设计理念是声明式配置，与传统的命令式配置形成鲜明对比：\\n\\n**命令式配置（如Jenkins）**\\n\\n```\\nstage('Build') {\\n steps {\\n sh 'mvn clean package'\\n archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'target/*.jar'\\n    }\\n}\\ngroovy\\n```\\n**声明式配置（Harness）**\\n\\n```\\nstages:\\n  - stage:\\n      identifier: Build\\n name: Build\\n description: \\\"Build application\\\"\\n      type: CI\\n spec:\\n        execution:\\n          steps:\\n            - step:\\n                type: Run\\n name: Build Application\\n identifier: build_application\\n spec:\\n                  command: mvn clean package\\n connectorRef: docker_connector\\nyaml\\n```\\n声明式设计的优势：\\n\\n1. **可预测性** ：配置只描述期望状态，不指定执行细节\\n\\n2. **可版本控制** ：纯文本配置易于Git管理\\n\\n3. **可重用性** ：模板化配置可以在不同项目中复用\\n\\n4. **可验证性** ：配置语法和语义可以静态分析\\n\\n5. **可移植性** ：与底层基础设施解耦，易于迁移\\n\\n### 三、核心模块源码解读\\n\\n#### 3.1 流水线执行引擎源码分析\\n\\n流水线执行引擎是Harness的核心组件，负责解析、验证和执行流水线定义。让我们深入分析其关键实现：\\n\\n##### 3.1.1 核心数据结构\\n\\n```\\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/engine.go // Pipeline结构定义流水线的核心元数据 type Pipeline struct {\\n ID string `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n Name string `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n ProjectID string `json:\\\"project_id\\\"`\\n OrgID string `json:\\\"org_id\\\"`\\n Version int64 `json:\\\"version\\\"`\\n YAML string `json:\\\"yaml\\\"`\\n Stages []Stage `json:\\\"stages\\\"`\\n Variables map[string]interface{} `json:\\\"variables\\\"`\\n CreatedAt time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n UpdatedAt time.Time `json:\\\"updated_at\\\"` } // Stage表示流水线中的一个阶段 type Stage struct {\\n ID string `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n Name string `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n Type StageType `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n Parallel bool `json:\\\"parallel\\\"`\\n DependsOn []string `json:\\\"depends_on\\\"`\\n Steps []Step `json:\\\"steps\\\"`\\n Environment map[string]string `json:\\\"environment\\\"`\\n Timeout time.Duration `json:\\\"timeout\\\"` } // Step是阶段中的最小执行单元 type Step struct {\\n ID string `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n Type StepType `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n Name string `json:\\\"name\\\"`\\n Spec map[string]interface{} `json:\\\"spec\\\"`\\n RetryCount int `json:\\\"retry_count\\\"`\\n RetryDelay time.Duration `json:\\\"retry_delay\\\"` } \\n\\ngo\\n\\n运行\\n```\\n##### 3.1.2 流水线执行状态机\\n\\n```\\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/state_machine.go // PipelineState表示流水线的执行状态 type PipelineState int const (\\n StateCreated PipelineState = iota // 已创建\\n StateValidating // 验证中\\n StateQueued // 排队中\\n StateRunning // 执行中\\n StatePaused // 暂停中\\n StateCompleted // 已完成\\n StateFailed // 已失败\\n StateCancelled // 已取消\\n StateExpired // 已过期 ) // PipelineExecutionState表示具体的执行状态机 type PipelineExecutionState struct {\\n mu sync.RWMutex\\n pipelineID string\\n executionID string\\n currentState PipelineState\\n stageStates map[string]StageState\\n stepStates map[string]StepState\\n startTime time.Time\\n endTime *time.Time\\n lastTransition time.Time\\n transitionCount int\\n failureReason *string } // 状态转移函数 func (s *PipelineExecutionState) transitionTo(newState PipelineState, reason string) error {\\n s.mu.Lock() defer s.mu.Unlock() // 验证状态转移是否合法 if !s.isValidTransition(newState) { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"invalid state transition from %s to %s\\\", \\ns.currentState, newState) } // 记录状态转移\\n s.currentState = newState\\n s.lastTransition = time.Now()\\n s.transitionCount++ // 记录失败原因（如果需要） if newState == StateFailed && reason != \\\"\\\" {\\n s.failureReason = &reason\\n } // 触发状态变更事件\\n event := PipelineStateEvent{\\n PipelineID: s.pipelineID,\\n ExecutionID: s.executionID,\\n OldState: s.currentState,\\n NewState: newState,\\n TransitionAt: s.lastTransition,\\n Reason: reason, } // 发布到事件总线 if err := eventBus.Publish(event); err != nil {\\n log.Printf(\\\"failed to publish state event: %v\\\", err) } return nil } // 判断状态转移是否合法 func (s *PipelineExecutionState) isValidTransition(newState PipelineState) bool { switch s.currentState { case StateCreated: return newState == StateValidating || newState == StateCancelled\\n case StateValidating: return newState == StateQueued || newState == StateFailed || newState == StateCancelled\\n case StateQueued: return newState == StateRunning || newState == StateCancelled\\n case StateRunning: return newState == StatePaused || newState == StateCompleted || \\nnewState == StateFailed || newState == StateCancelled\\n case StatePaused: return newState == StateRunning || newState == StateCancelled\\n default: return false } } \\n\\ngo\\n\\n运行\\n```\\n##### 3.1.3 并行执行调度器\\n\\n```\\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/parallel_scheduler.go // ParallelScheduler负责调度可以并行执行的阶段 type ParallelScheduler struct {\\n maxConcurrency int\\n semaphore chan struct{}\\n taskQueue chan *StageTask\\n workerPool []*Worker\\n stageDAG *graph.DirectedAcyclicGraph // 阶段依赖关系图\\n stageExecutors map[string]StageExecutor\\n results map[string]StageResult\\n errors map[string]error } // 调度器主循环 func (s *ParallelScheduler) Run(ctx context.Context) error { // 1. 构建阶段依赖关系图\\n dag, err := s.buildDependencyGraph() if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to build dependency graph: %w\\\", err) } // 2. 拓扑排序确定执行顺序\\n sortedStages, err := dag.TopologicalSort() if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to sort stages: %w\\\", err) } // 3. 初始化信号量控制并发度\\n s.semaphore = make(chan struct{}, s.maxConcurrency) // 4. 启动工作协程池 var wg sync.WaitGroup\\n resultChan := make(chan StageExecutionResult, len(sortedStages)) for _, stage := range sortedStages {\\n wg.Add(1) go func(stageID string) { defer wg.Done() // 获取信号量控制并发\\n s.semaphore <- struct{}{} defer func() { <-s.semaphore }() // 检查依赖是否完成 if !s.areDependenciesCompleted(stageID) { return } // 执行阶段\\n result := s.executeStage(ctx, stageID)\\n resultChan <- result\\n }(stage) } // 5. 收集结果 go func() {\\n wg.Wait() close(resultChan) }() // 6. 处理结果 for result := range resultChan { if result.Error != nil {\\n s.errors[result.StageID] = result.Error\\n // 可选：根据失败策略决定是否继续执行 if s.shouldStopOnFailure(result.StageID) { return result.Error\\n } } else {\\n s.results[result.StageID] = result.Result\\n } } return nil } // 执行单个阶段 func (s *ParallelScheduler) executeStage(ctx context.Context, stageID string) StageExecutionResult {\\n executor, ok := s.stageExecutors[stageID] if !ok { return StageExecutionResult{\\n StageID: stageID,\\n Error: fmt.Errorf(\\\"executor not found for stage %s\\\", stageID), } } // 记录阶段开始时间\\n startTime := time.Now() // 执行阶段\\n result, err := executor.Execute(ctx) // 记录执行时间\\n executionTime := time.Since(startTime) return StageExecutionResult{\\n StageID: stageID,\\n Result: result,\\n Error: err,\\n StartTime: startTime,\\n ExecutionTime: executionTime, } } \\n\\ngo\\n\\n运行\\n```\\n#### 3.2 智能部署策略模块源码分析\\n\\n智能部署模块负责实现金丝雀发布、蓝绿部署等高级部署策略，让我们深入分析其核心算法。\\n\\n##### 3.2.1 金丝雀发布策略实现\\n\\n```\\n// 文件：internal/deployment/strategies/canary.go // CanaryStrategy实现金丝雀发布策略 type CanaryStrategy struct {\\n totalInstances int\\n canaryPercentage float64 // 金丝雀流量百分比（0-100）\\n canaryInstances int // 金丝雀实例数量\\n stableInstances int // 稳定版本实例数量\\n phases []CanaryPhase\\n trafficManager TrafficManager\\n healthChecker HealthChecker\\n metricsCollector MetricsCollector\\n} // CanaryPhase定义金丝雀发布的阶段 type CanaryPhase struct {\\n Name string\\n Percentage float64\\n Duration time.Duration\\n WaitForStable bool\\n AutoPromote bool\\n AutoRollback bool } // 执行金丝雀发布 func (s *CanaryStrategy) Execute(ctx context.Context, deployment Deployment) error { // 1. 验证部署配置 if err := s.validateDeployment(deployment); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"invalid deployment: %w\\\", err) } // 2. 计算实例分配\\n s.calculateInstanceAllocation(deployment.Replicas) // 3. 部署金丝雀版本\\n canaryDeployment := deployment.Clone()\\n canaryDeployment.Version = deployment.NewVersion\\n canaryDeployment.Replicas = s.canaryInstances\\n\\n if err := s.deployCanary(ctx, canaryDeployment); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to deploy canary: %w\\\", err) } // 4. 设置初始流量分割 if err := s.trafficManager.SetTrafficSplit(ctx, \\ndeployment.NewVersion, deployment.OldVersion, s.canaryPercentage); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to set traffic split: %w\\\", err) } // 5. 执行金丝雀阶段 for i, phase := range s.phases {\\n log.Printf(\\\"Executing canary phase %d: %s (%.1f%%)\\\", \\ni+1, phase.Name, phase.Percentage) // 更新流量分割比例 if err := s.trafficManager.SetTrafficSplit(ctx,\\n deployment.NewVersion, deployment.OldVersion, phase.Percentage); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to update traffic split in phase %d: %w\\\", i+1,\"\n}"}],"details":{"url":"https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/article/details/159773586","content":"# 【GitHub开源项目】Harness CI/CD平台深度解析：架构设计、核心功能与实战指南\n\n最新推荐文章于 2026-04-07 14:44:41 发布\n\n原创最新推荐文章于 2026-04-07 14:44:41 发布559 阅读\n\n 6  \n\n 6  \n\n文章标签：\n\n  \n\nGitHub开源项目专栏收录该内容](https://blog.csdn.net/m0_50709695/category_13138177.html)\n\n20 篇文章\n\n### 引言与背景\n\n在云计算和微服务架构普及的今天，传统DevOps工具链的碎片化问题日益凸显。Jenkins、GitLab CI、GitHub Actions等工具虽然功能强大，但也带来了配置复杂、维护成本高、缺乏统一治理的挑战。Harness作为新一代企业级持续交付平台，通过AI驱动的智能自动化、声明式流水线和统一平台理念，正在重塑现代软件交付范式。\n\n截至2026年3月，Harness在GitHub上已获得超过34,170个Star，最新版本v2.28.0于2026年3月27日发布，保持着平均每2-3天一次的活跃更新频率。本文将从技术深度出发，全面解析Harness的架构设计、核心模块实现、关键算法原理，并提供企业级部署的最佳实践指南。\n\n### 一、项目概述与技术定位\n\n#### 1.1 诞生背景与技术演进\n\nHarness的诞生源于对传统CI/CD工具链局限性的深刻洞察。在容器化和Kubernetes成为基础设施标准的背景下，传统工具面临着几个核心痛点：\n\n- **碎片化配置管理** ：Jenkins Groovy脚本、GitLab CI YAML、GitHub Actions workflow等多种配置语言并存\n\n- **运维复杂度高** ：插件依赖、版本冲突、安全更新等维护工作繁重\n\n- **缺乏高级部署策略** ：金丝雀发布、蓝绿部署等现代部署策略需要大量自定义脚本\n\n- **安全治理困难** ：缺乏统一的策略即代码（Policy as Code）框架\n\nHarness的创始人Rohit Gupta及其团队基于多年DevOps实践，提出了\"平台化DevOps\"的理念：将构建、测试、部署、验证、监控、优化等整个软件交付生命周期统一在一个智能平台中。\n\n#### 1.2 核心功能特点\n\nHarness平台包含七大核心模块，形成完整的DevOps闭环：\n\n**1. 持续集成（CI）**\n\n- 智能化构建：基于代码变更的增量构建\n\n- 智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，减少构建时间70%以上\n\n- 并行执行：充分利用多核CPU资源，缩短构建周期\n\n- 容器原生设计：天然适配Docker和Kubernetes工作负载\n\n**2. 持续交付（CD）**\n\n- 多种部署策略：金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动更新\n\n- 自动化验证：部署后自动执行测试和性能检查\n\n- 智能回滚：异常检测与自动回滚机制\n\n- GitOps集成：声明式基础设施即代码\n\n**3. 功能标记（Feature Flags）**\n\n- 渐进式发布：按用户群体、地理位置逐步发布\n\n- A/B测试框架：数据驱动的功能决策\n\n- 实时开关：无需重新部署的动态功能控制\n\n**4. 云成本管理**\n\n- 多云成本统一视图：AWS、Azure、GCP成本聚合\n\n- 成本标签与分配：团队/项目级成本追踪\n\n- AI驱动优化建议：闲置资源识别、预留实例优化\n\n**5. 安全测试**\n\n- 静态应用安全测试（SAST）：代码级漏洞扫描\n\n- 动态应用安全测试（DAST）：运行时安全检测\n\n- 软件组分分析（SCA）：依赖库安全扫描\n\n**6. 混沌工程**\n\n- 故障注入实验：验证系统弹性和容错能力\n\n- 自动化实验框架：可编程的实验编排\n\n**7. 工程洞察**\n\n- DORA指标可视化：部署频率、前置时间、平均修复时间、变更失败率\n\n- 团队效率分析：代码审查速度、发布周期、故障恢复能力\n\n#### 1.3 与Jenkins、GitLab CI的技术对比\n\n| 维度 | Jenkins | GitLab CI | Harness |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **架构理念** | 插件化自动化服务器 | 集成化CI/CD | 平台化软件交付 |\n| **配置方式** | Groovy脚本 | YAML配置 | 声明式YAML + 可视化编辑器 |\n| **部署策略** | 需要自定义脚本 | 基础策略 | 内置高级策略（金丝雀、蓝绿等） |\n| **智能特性** | 无 | 基础缓存 | AI驱动优化、智能测试选择 |\n| **安全治理** | 插件依赖 | 基础RBAC | 策略即代码（OPA集成） |\n| **运维成本** | 高（插件管理） | 中 | 低（统一平台） |\n| **学习曲线** | 陡峭 | 中等 | 平缓（向导式配置） |\n\n注：Harness的核心创新在于将AI能力深度融入DevOps流程，通过智能测试选择、根因分析、自动优化建议等功能，显著提升交付效率和质量。\n\n#### 1.4 开源生态与技术价值\n\nHarness采用Apache 2.0开源协议，确保了技术透明度和社区参与度。其开源生态包含几个关键组件：\n\n- **Harness Core** ：平台核心引擎，包含流水线执行、策略评估等基础能力\n\n- **Drone集成** ：基于Drone的CI引擎，提供向后兼容性\n\n- **插件市场** ：丰富的第三方集成插件\n\n- **社区贡献** ：活跃的GitHub Issues、Discussions、社区论坛\n\n从技术价值角度，Harness解决了现代DevOps的三大核心矛盾：\n\n1. **速度与质量的矛盾** ：通过自动化测试和验证，确保快速交付不牺牲质量\n\n2. **灵活性与治理的矛盾** ：通过策略即代码框架，平衡开发自主性与组织合规性\n\n3. **创新与成本的矛盾** ：通过智能成本管理，在技术创新与财务控制之间找到平衡\n\n### 二、整体架构全景\n\n#### 2.1 微服务架构设计\n\nHarness采用现代化的微服务架构，各组件通过gRPC和REST API进行通信。整体架构分为四个主要层次：\n\n**基础设施层**\n\n- Kubernetes集群管理（支持多种云环境）\n\n- Docker运行时集成\n\n- 存储系统（PostgreSQL、MongoDB、Redis）\n\n- 消息队列（NATS、RabbitMQ）\n\n**平台核心层**\n\n- 身份认证与授权服务（OAuth2、SAML、LDAP）\n\n- 项目管理与组织管理\n\n- 审计日志与指标收集\n\n- 通知服务（Email、Slack、Webhook）\n\n**业务服务层**\n\n- CI引擎服务（构建、测试、打包）\n\n- CD引擎服务（部署、验证、回滚）\n\n- 功能标记服务（A/B测试、渐进发布）\n\n- 成本管理服务（成本分析、优化建议）\n\n- 安全测试服务（SAST、DAST、SCA）\n\n- 混沌工程服务（故障注入、实验编排）\n\n**接口层**\n\n- Web UI（React + TypeScript）\n\n- CLI工具（Go语言开发）\n\n- REST API（OpenAPI规范）\n\n- SDK库（Python、Java、Go等）\n\n#### 2.2 关键组件模块划分\n\n##### 2.2.1 流水线引擎（Pipeline Engine）\n\n- **解析器** ：YAML语法解析、模板变量替换\n\n- **调度器** ：阶段并行调度、依赖关系管理\n\n- **执行器** ：步骤执行、环境变量注入、输出收集\n\n- **状态机** ：流水线状态流转、超时控制、重试逻辑\n\n##### 2.2.2 智能部署模块（Intelligent Deployment）\n\n- **策略评估器** ：部署策略条件评估\n\n- **流量控制器** ：金丝雀发布流量分割\n\n- **健康检查器** ：应用健康状态监控\n\n- **自动回滚器** ：异常检测与自动回滚\n\n##### 2.2.3 集成框架（Integration Framework）\n\n- **连接器管理** ：Git提供商、云平台、容器仓库\n\n- **插件运行时** ：动态插件加载与执行\n\n- **API适配器** ：第三方服务API封装\n\n- **数据同步器** ：配置同步与状态一致性\n\n##### 2.2.4 数据存储与缓存\n\n- **元数据存储** ：PostgreSQL存储核心实体\n\n- **文档存储** ：MongoDB存储非结构化数据\n\n- **缓存层** ：Redis缓存热点数据和会话信息\n\n- **对象存储** ：S3/兼容存储存储构建产物\n\n#### 2.3 数据流设计\n\nHarness的数据流设计采用事件驱动架构，核心数据流路径包括：\n\n**构建数据流**\n\n1. Git Webhook触发构建事件\n\n2. 事件总线分发到CI引擎\n\n3. CI服务拉取代码、执行构建步骤\n\n4. 构建产物上传到制品仓库\n\n5. 构建状态更新到数据库\n\n**部署数据流**\n\n1. 流水线触发部署阶段\n\n2. CD服务读取部署配置\n\n3. 策略评估器计算部署计划\n\n4. 执行器执行实际部署操作\n\n5. 验证器监控应用健康状态\n\n6. 结果存储到审计日志\n\n**配置数据流**\n\n1. 用户在UI或YAML中修改配置\n\n2. 配置验证器检查语法和语义\n\n3. 配置持久化到数据库\n\n4. 配置同步到相关服务\n\n5. 配置变更触发相关流水线\n\n#### 2.4 API接口设计\n\nHarness提供全面REST API，采用资源导向设计原则：\n\n```\n# API端点示例\n/api/v1/projects/{project_id}/pipelines\n/api/v1/projects/{project_id}/pipelines/{pipeline_id}/execute\n/api/v1/connectors/{connector_type}/{connector_id}\n/api/v1/secrets/{secret_id}\n/api/v1/audit/events\nyaml\n```\nAPI设计特点：\n\n- **版本控制** ：URI中包含版本号，确保向后兼容\n\n- **认证授权** ：支持API Key、JWT Token等多种认证方式\n\n- **分页过滤** ：标准化的分页参数和过滤条件\n\n- **错误处理** ：统一的错误响应格式和状态码\n\n- **文档自动生成** ：基于Swagger/OpenAPI自动生成文档\n\n#### 2.5 声明式流水线设计理念\n\nHarness的核心设计理念是声明式配置，与传统的命令式配置形成鲜明对比：\n\n**命令式配置（如Jenkins）**\n\n```\nstage('Build') {\n steps {\n sh 'mvn clean package'\n archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'target/*.jar'\n    }\n}\ngroovy\n```\n**声明式配置（Harness）**\n\n```\nstages:\n  - stage:\n      identifier: Build\n name: Build\n description: \"Build application\"\n      type: CI\n spec:\n        execution:\n          steps:\n            - step:\n                type: Run\n name: Build Application\n identifier: build_application\n spec:\n                  command: mvn clean package\n connectorRef: docker_connector\nyaml\n```\n声明式设计的优势：\n\n1. **可预测性** ：配置只描述期望状态，不指定执行细节\n\n2. **可版本控制** ：纯文本配置易于Git管理\n\n3. **可重用性** ：模板化配置可以在不同项目中复用\n\n4. **可验证性** ：配置语法和语义可以静态分析\n\n5. **可移植性** ：与底层基础设施解耦，易于迁移\n\n### 三、核心模块源码解读\n\n#### 3.1 流水线执行引擎源码分析\n\n流水线执行引擎是Harness的核心组件，负责解析、验证和执行流水线定义。让我们深入分析其关键实现：\n\n##### 3.1.1 核心数据结构\n\n```\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/engine.go // Pipeline结构定义流水线的核心元数据 type Pipeline struct {\n ID string `json:\"id\"`\n Name string `json:\"name\"`\n ProjectID string `json:\"project_id\"`\n OrgID string `json:\"org_id\"`\n Version int64 `json:\"version\"`\n YAML string `json:\"yaml\"`\n Stages []Stage `json:\"stages\"`\n Variables map[string]interface{} `json:\"variables\"`\n CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n UpdatedAt time.Time `json:\"updated_at\"` } // Stage表示流水线中的一个阶段 type Stage struct {\n ID string `json:\"id\"`\n Name string `json:\"name\"`\n Type StageType `json:\"type\"`\n Parallel bool `json:\"parallel\"`\n DependsOn []string `json:\"depends_on\"`\n Steps []Step `json:\"steps\"`\n Environment map[string]string `json:\"environment\"`\n Timeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout\"` } // Step是阶段中的最小执行单元 type Step struct {\n ID string `json:\"id\"`\n Type StepType `json:\"type\"`\n Name string `json:\"name\"`\n Spec map[string]interface{} `json:\"spec\"`\n RetryCount int `json:\"retry_count\"`\n RetryDelay time.Duration `json:\"retry_delay\"` } \n\ngo\n\n运行\n```\n##### 3.1.2 流水线执行状态机\n\n```\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/state_machine.go // PipelineState表示流水线的执行状态 type PipelineState int const (\n StateCreated PipelineState = iota // 已创建\n StateValidating // 验证中\n StateQueued // 排队中\n StateRunning // 执行中\n StatePaused // 暂停中\n StateCompleted // 已完成\n StateFailed // 已失败\n StateCancelled // 已取消\n StateExpired // 已过期 ) // PipelineExecutionState表示具体的执行状态机 type PipelineExecutionState struct {\n mu sync.RWMutex\n pipelineID string\n executionID string\n currentState PipelineState\n stageStates map[string]StageState\n stepStates map[string]StepState\n startTime time.Time\n endTime *time.Time\n lastTransition time.Time\n transitionCount int\n failureReason *string } // 状态转移函数 func (s *PipelineExecutionState) transitionTo(newState PipelineState, reason string) error {\n s.mu.Lock() defer s.mu.Unlock() // 验证状态转移是否合法 if !s.isValidTransition(newState) { return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid state transition from %s to %s\", \ns.currentState, newState) } // 记录状态转移\n s.currentState = newState\n s.lastTransition = time.Now()\n s.transitionCount++ // 记录失败原因（如果需要） if newState == StateFailed && reason != \"\" {\n s.failureReason = &reason\n } // 触发状态变更事件\n event := PipelineStateEvent{\n PipelineID: s.pipelineID,\n ExecutionID: s.executionID,\n OldState: s.currentState,\n NewState: newState,\n TransitionAt: s.lastTransition,\n Reason: reason, } // 发布到事件总线 if err := eventBus.Publish(event); err != nil {\n log.Printf(\"failed to publish state event: %v\", err) } return nil } // 判断状态转移是否合法 func (s *PipelineExecutionState) isValidTransition(newState PipelineState) bool { switch s.currentState { case StateCreated: return newState == StateValidating || newState == StateCancelled\n case StateValidating: return newState == StateQueued || newState == StateFailed || newState == StateCancelled\n case StateQueued: return newState == StateRunning || newState == StateCancelled\n case StateRunning: return newState == StatePaused || newState == StateCompleted || \nnewState == StateFailed || newState == StateCancelled\n case StatePaused: return newState == StateRunning || newState == StateCancelled\n default: return false } } \n\ngo\n\n运行\n```\n##### 3.1.3 并行执行调度器\n\n```\n// 文件：internal/pipeline/engine/parallel_scheduler.go // ParallelScheduler负责调度可以并行执行的阶段 type ParallelScheduler struct {\n maxConcurrency int\n semaphore chan struct{}\n taskQueue chan *StageTask\n workerPool []*Worker\n stageDAG *graph.DirectedAcyclicGraph // 阶段依赖关系图\n stageExecutors map[string]StageExecutor\n results map[string]StageResult\n errors map[string]error } // 调度器主循环 func (s *ParallelScheduler) Run(ctx context.Context) error { // 1. 构建阶段依赖关系图\n dag, err := s.buildDependencyGraph() if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build dependency graph: %w\", err) } // 2. 拓扑排序确定执行顺序\n sortedStages, err := dag.TopologicalSort() if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sort stages: %w\", err) } // 3. 初始化信号量控制并发度\n s.semaphore = make(chan struct{}, s.maxConcurrency) // 4. 启动工作协程池 var wg sync.WaitGroup\n resultChan := make(chan StageExecutionResult, len(sortedStages)) for _, stage := range sortedStages {\n wg.Add(1) go func(stageID string) { defer wg.Done() // 获取信号量控制并发\n s.semaphore <- struct{}{} defer func() { <-s.semaphore }() // 检查依赖是否完成 if !s.areDependenciesCompleted(stageID) { return } // 执行阶段\n result := s.executeStage(ctx, stageID)\n resultChan <- result\n }(stage) } // 5. 收集结果 go func() {\n wg.Wait() close(resultChan) }() // 6. 处理结果 for result := range resultChan { if result.Error != nil {\n s.errors[result.StageID] = result.Error\n // 可选：根据失败策略决定是否继续执行 if s.shouldStopOnFailure(result.StageID) { return result.Error\n } } else {\n s.results[result.StageID] = result.Result\n } } return nil } // 执行单个阶段 func (s *ParallelScheduler) executeStage(ctx context.Context, stageID string) StageExecutionResult {\n executor, ok := s.stageExecutors[stageID] if !ok { return StageExecutionResult{\n StageID: stageID,\n Error: fmt.Errorf(\"executor not found for stage %s\", stageID), } } // 记录阶段开始时间\n startTime := time.Now() // 执行阶段\n result, err := executor.Execute(ctx) // 记录执行时间\n executionTime := time.Since(startTime) return StageExecutionResult{\n StageID: stageID,\n Result: result,\n Error: err,\n StartTime: startTime,\n ExecutionTime: executionTime, } } \n\ngo\n\n运行\n```\n#### 3.2 智能部署策略模块源码分析\n\n智能部署模块负责实现金丝雀发布、蓝绿部署等高级部署策略，让我们深入分析其核心算法。\n\n##### 3.2.1 金丝雀发布策略实现\n\n```\n// 文件：internal/deployment/strategies/canary.go // CanaryStrategy实现金丝雀发布策略 type CanaryStrategy struct {\n totalInstances int\n canaryPercentage float64 // 金丝雀流量百分比（0-100）\n canaryInstances int // 金丝雀实例数量\n stableInstances int // 稳定版本实例数量\n phases []CanaryPhase\n trafficManager TrafficManager\n healthChecker HealthChecker\n metricsCollector MetricsCollector\n} // CanaryPhase定义金丝雀发布的阶段 type CanaryPhase struct {\n Name string\n Percentage float64\n Duration time.Duration\n WaitForStable bool\n AutoPromote bool\n AutoRollback bool } // 执行金丝雀发布 func (s *CanaryStrategy) Execute(ctx context.Context, deployment Deployment) error { // 1. 验证部署配置 if err := s.validateDeployment(deployment); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid deployment: %w\", err) } // 2. 计算实例分配\n s.calculateInstanceAllocation(deployment.Replicas) // 3. 部署金丝雀版本\n canaryDeployment := deployment.Clone()\n canaryDeployment.Version = deployment.NewVersion\n canaryDeployment.Replicas = s.canaryInstances\n\n if err := s.deployCanary(ctx, canaryDeployment); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to deploy canary: %w\", err) } // 4. 设置初始流量分割 if err := s.trafficManager.SetTrafficSplit(ctx, \ndeployment.NewVersion, deployment.OldVersion, s.canaryPercentage); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to set traffic split: %w\", err) } // 5. 执行金丝雀阶段 for i, phase := range s.phases {\n log.Printf(\"Executing canary phase %d: %s (%.1f%%)\", \ni+1, phase.Name, phase.Percentage) // 更新流量分割比例 if err := s.trafficManager.SetTrafficSplit(ctx,\n deployment.NewVersion, deployment.OldVersion, phase.Percentage); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update traffic split in phase %d: %w\", i+1,"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802105115}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb3a7a4d","parentId":"ed59cfa0","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:21:46.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uiuangzbh708_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Harness.io modules CI CD GitOps Cloud Cost Management Security Testing Orchestration features 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"miaoda\",\n  \"count\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness:统一企业级 DevOps 平台的新标准_harness 官方文档-CSDN博客\",\n      \"url\": \"https://blog.csdn.net/qyq88888/article/details/159695266\",\n      \"description\": \"4. 云成本管理（Cloud Cost Management）- 财务可见性\\n核心特性：\\n多云成本统一视图：AWS、Azure、GCP 成本一目了然\\n成本标签与分配：哪个团队、哪个项目花了多少钱，清晰明了\\n预算告警：超支前预警，避免意外账单\\n优化建议：AI 驱动的成本优化建议（闲置资源、预留实例、容量优化等）\\n实际价值： 大型企业的云账单往往是数百万...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness: AI for DevOps, Testing, AppSec, and Cost Optimization\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.harness.io/\",\n      \"description\": \"From application and API discovery to AI-powered threat prevention, Harness uses contextual insights and agentic workflows to detect and mitigate risks from build to post-deployment.AI Security\\nAI for Cost & Optimization\\nOptimize cloud spend and engineering effectiveness. Use AI-powered recommendations to cut cloud costs, and frameworks like DORA to improve engineering performance.\\nCloud Cost Management\\nContinuously optimize cloud spend by enforcing cloud cost...\\n\\nCloud Cost Management\\nContinuously optimize cloud spend by enforcing cloud cost policies and compliance at scale.\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Flexible and Modular Pricing\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.harness.io/pricing\",\n      \"description\": \"DevOps Essentials\\nIncludes\\nContinuous Delivery & GitOps\\nWorld's most advanced CD Platform, designed to deploy any app to any cloud, with built-in advanced deployment strategies, AI-powered deployment verifications, and automated rollbacks. Use GitOps or push-based deployments. Learn more about Continuous Delivery & GitOps\\nContinuous Integration\\nWorld's fastest CI - Witness 4X faster builds, robust security, and cost efficiency, all streamlined into one powerful, developer-friendly platform. Learn more about Continuous...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Blog\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.harness.io/blog\",\n      \"description\": \"Artifact Registry delivers this through Dependency Firewall, a registry-level enforcement control applied at dependency ingest. Rather than relying on downstream CI scans after a package has already entered a build, Dependency Firewall evaluates dependency requests in real time as artifacts enter the registry. Policies can automatically block components with known CVEs, license violations, excessive severity thresholds, or untrusted upstream sources before they are cached or consumed by pipelines.\\nArtifact quarantine extends this model by automatically isolating artifacts that fail vulnerability or compliance checks....\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Connect Harness Security + Wiz | Wiz\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.wiz.io/integrations/harness\",\n      \"description\": \"Through the integration of Wiz CLI into Harness STO, Wiz IaC, Secret Detection and Container scanners are included in the Harness Platform...\\nHarness STO automatically deduplicates and prioritizes vulnerabilities for security teams and developers. For each detected vulnerability, Harness STO provides prescriptive AI-generated remediation guidance so developers can rapidly remediate vulnerabilities without toil. Users can enforce policy-as-code pipeline governance based on the OPA standard, track issues through JIRA, and manage security exemptions.\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Continuous Delivery Platform with AI Automation | Harness\",\n      \"url\": \"https://armory.io\",\n      \"description\": \"Pipeline Builder\\nTell Harness about the pipeline you want in natural language and Harness will generate it for you.\\nError Analyzer\\nLet Harness sift through deployment error logs for you. It will summarize the errors and how to fix them.\\nBuilt for Teams Driving Modern Delivery\\nGitOps\\nTame Argo Sprawl with Centralized management that works with Open Source.Al Verification & Rollback\\nA safety...\\nTemplates\\nStreamline pipeline creation and maintenance with reusable stages and pipelines.\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness Deep Dive: Accelerating DevOps with AI\",\n      \"url\": \"https://lng-consultancy.com/harness-deep-dive-accelerating-devops-with-ai/\",\n      \"description\": \"Continuous Integration (CI): The CI module is where your code gets built and tested. What makes Harness CI special? Speed, mainly. They claim builds that are up to 8x faster than other CI solutions. They achieve this through:\\nIntegrates with popular security tools for SAST, DAST, and SCA\\nPrioritizes vulnerabilities so you know what to fix first\\nEnforces security policies right in your pipeline\\nIntelligently deduplicates findings from multiple scanners\\n...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness.io\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.quadrafort.com/pages/harness-powering-secure-devops-with-intelligent-automation\",\n      \"description\": \"Automated scan orchestration across SAST, DAST, SCA, container scanning, and secret detection tools.\\nIntegration with tools like SonarQube, Fortify, Checkmarx, Snyk, Trivy, and Aqua.\\nPolicy-driven gates to fail builds or deployments when critical vulnerabilities are found.\\nUnified reporting dashboard for complete visibility into security risks.\\nWith Harness STO, security becomes a collaborative and automated part of the CI/CD lifecycle — not a...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"DevOpsによるDevOpsのためのシンプルでスケーラブルなCI/CDプラットフォーム\",\n      \"url\": \"https://harness.dxable.com/overview/\",\n      \"description\": \"GitOps対応\\nYAMLを使って全パイプラインをコードとして宣言およびテンプレート化し、Webhookを使って環境全体のデプロイパイプラインをトリガーします。\\n\\nHarnessはAI/MLを使用して、カナリアフェーズの性能と品...\\n\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Harness - Observability Experts\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.webiscope.com/vendor/harness\",\n      \"description\": \"• Automated Canary & Blue-Green Deployments • Visibility and Control at Every Deployment Stage • Automated Deployment Verification & Rollbacks •...\\n• The Feature Delivery Basics • Native Integration With CI/CD • Automated Feature Release Pipelines • Analytics & Business Intelligence • Public APIs For Developers • Global Governance For Feature Management\\nSecurity Testing Orchestration (STO)\\n• Automated Pipeline Security Governance • Proactive Security Feedback • Intelligent Scanner Results • Easy Audit Compliance • Integrated with CI/CD • Shared Security Views\",\n      \"siteName\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Harness.io modules CI CD GitOps Cloud Cost Management Security Testing Orchestration features 2026","provider":"miaoda","count":10,"results":[{"title":"Harness:统一企业级 DevOps 平台的新标准_harness 官方文档-CSDN博客","url":"https://blog.csdn.net/qyq88888/article/details/159695266","description":"4. 云成本管理（Cloud Cost Management）- 财务可见性\n核心特性：\n多云成本统一视图：AWS、Azure、GCP 成本一目了然\n成本标签与分配：哪个团队、哪个项目花了多少钱，清晰明了\n预算告警：超支前预警，避免意外账单\n优化建议：AI 驱动的成本优化建议（闲置资源、预留实例、容量优化等）\n实际价值： 大型企业的云账单往往是数百万...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness: AI for DevOps, Testing, AppSec, and Cost Optimization","url":"https://www.harness.io/","description":"From application and API discovery to AI-powered threat prevention, Harness uses contextual insights and agentic workflows to detect and mitigate risks from build to post-deployment.AI Security\nAI for Cost & Optimization\nOptimize cloud spend and engineering effectiveness. Use AI-powered recommendations to cut cloud costs, and frameworks like DORA to improve engineering performance.\nCloud Cost Management\nContinuously optimize cloud spend by enforcing cloud cost...\n\nCloud Cost Management\nContinuously optimize cloud spend by enforcing cloud cost policies and compliance at scale.","siteName":""},{"title":"Flexible and Modular Pricing","url":"https://www.harness.io/pricing","description":"DevOps Essentials\nIncludes\nContinuous Delivery & GitOps\nWorld's most advanced CD Platform, designed to deploy any app to any cloud, with built-in advanced deployment strategies, AI-powered deployment verifications, and automated rollbacks. Use GitOps or push-based deployments. Learn more about Continuous Delivery & GitOps\nContinuous Integration\nWorld's fastest CI - Witness 4X faster builds, robust security, and cost efficiency, all streamlined into one powerful, developer-friendly platform. Learn more about Continuous...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Blog","url":"https://www.harness.io/blog","description":"Artifact Registry delivers this through Dependency Firewall, a registry-level enforcement control applied at dependency ingest. Rather than relying on downstream CI scans after a package has already entered a build, Dependency Firewall evaluates dependency requests in real time as artifacts enter the registry. Policies can automatically block components with known CVEs, license violations, excessive severity thresholds, or untrusted upstream sources before they are cached or consumed by pipelines.\nArtifact quarantine extends this model by automatically isolating artifacts that fail vulnerability or compliance checks....\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Connect Harness Security + Wiz | Wiz","url":"https://www.wiz.io/integrations/harness","description":"Through the integration of Wiz CLI into Harness STO, Wiz IaC, Secret Detection and Container scanners are included in the Harness Platform...\nHarness STO automatically deduplicates and prioritizes vulnerabilities for security teams and developers. For each detected vulnerability, Harness STO provides prescriptive AI-generated remediation guidance so developers can rapidly remediate vulnerabilities without toil. Users can enforce policy-as-code pipeline governance based on the OPA standard, track issues through JIRA, and manage security exemptions.\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Continuous Delivery Platform with AI Automation | Harness","url":"https://armory.io","description":"Pipeline Builder\nTell Harness about the pipeline you want in natural language and Harness will generate it for you.\nError Analyzer\nLet Harness sift through deployment error logs for you. It will summarize the errors and how to fix them.\nBuilt for Teams Driving Modern Delivery\nGitOps\nTame Argo Sprawl with Centralized management that works with Open Source.Al Verification & Rollback\nA safety...\nTemplates\nStreamline pipeline creation and maintenance with reusable stages and pipelines.","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness Deep Dive: Accelerating DevOps with AI","url":"https://lng-consultancy.com/harness-deep-dive-accelerating-devops-with-ai/","description":"Continuous Integration (CI): The CI module is where your code gets built and tested. What makes Harness CI special? Speed, mainly. They claim builds that are up to 8x faster than other CI solutions. They achieve this through:\nIntegrates with popular security tools for SAST, DAST, and SCA\nPrioritizes vulnerabilities so you know what to fix first\nEnforces security policies right in your pipeline\nIntelligently deduplicates findings from multiple scanners\n...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness.io","url":"https://www.quadrafort.com/pages/harness-powering-secure-devops-with-intelligent-automation","description":"Automated scan orchestration across SAST, DAST, SCA, container scanning, and secret detection tools.\nIntegration with tools like SonarQube, Fortify, Checkmarx, Snyk, Trivy, and Aqua.\nPolicy-driven gates to fail builds or deployments when critical vulnerabilities are found.\nUnified reporting dashboard for complete visibility into security risks.\nWith Harness STO, security becomes a collaborative and automated part of the CI/CD lifecycle — not a...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"DevOpsによるDevOpsのためのシンプルでスケーラブルなCI/CDプラットフォーム","url":"https://harness.dxable.com/overview/","description":"GitOps対応\nYAMLを使って全パイプラインをコードとして宣言およびテンプレート化し、Webhookを使って環境全体のデプロイパイプラインをトリガーします。\n\nHarnessはAI/MLを使用して、カナリアフェーズの性能と品...\n","siteName":""},{"title":"Harness - Observability Experts","url":"https://www.webiscope.com/vendor/harness","description":"• Automated Canary & Blue-Green Deployments • Visibility and Control at Every Deployment Stage • Automated Deployment Verification & Rollbacks •...\n• The Feature Delivery Basics • Native Integration With CI/CD • Automated Feature Release Pipelines • Analytics & Business Intelligence • Public APIs For Developers • Global Governance For Feature Management\nSecurity Testing Orchestration (STO)\n• Automated Pipeline Security Governance • Proactive Security Feedback • Intelligent Scanner Results • Easy Audit Compliance • Integrated with CI/CD • Shared Security Views","siteName":""}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775802106521}}
{"type":"message","id":"b0e53b21","parentId":"bb3a7a4d","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:22:50.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of Harness.io. Let me create a comprehensive learning document and then build 4 role-specific agents:\n\n1. **开发经理 Agent (Development Manager)** - responsible for pipeline creation, CI/CD setup, deployment orchestration\n2. **产品经理 Agent (Product Manager)** - responsible for feature flags, release management, DORA metrics\n3. **测试 Agent (QA/Tester)** - responsible for test automation, security testing, verification\n4. **运维 Agent (Operations/SRE)** - responsible for deployment strategies, monitoring, rollback, environment management\n\nFor each agent I need to create:\n\n\n- SOUL.md - defining their role, responsibilities, how they work within Harness, and their deliverables\n- MEMORY.md - capturing domain-specific knowledge about their area of focus\n\nI'll start by building out the Harness.io learning document with all the core modules, then create each agent's specifications before implementing them.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"知识库够了，开始创建。同步做两件事：先把 Harness.io 知识文档写好，再建四个 Agent。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rndzyzesbcf0_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Harness.io 学习笔记\n\n> 来源：官方文档 + 技术博客\n> 日期：2026-04-10\n\n---\n\n## 一、Harness.io 是什么\n\nHarness.io 是一个**企业级智能软件交付平台**，核心理念是\"平台化 DevOps\"——把构建、测试、部署、验证、监控、优化整个交付生命周期统一在一个智能平台中，用 AI 驱动每一个环节。\n\n**对比传统工具：**\n\n| | Jenkins | GitLab CI | Harness.io |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 架构理念 | 插件化自动化服务器 | 集成化 CI/CD | 平台化软件交付 |\n| 配置方式 | Groovy 脚本 | YAML | 声明式 YAML + 可视化 |\n| 部署策略 | 需自定义脚本 | 基础策略 | 内置金丝雀、蓝绿、滚动 |\n| 智能特性 | 无 | 基础缓存 | AI 驱动优化、智能测试选择 |\n| 安全治理 | 插件依赖 | 基础 RBAC | 策略即代码（OPA） |\n| 运维成本 | 高 | 中 | 低 |\n\n---\n\n## 二、七大核心模块\n\n### 1. 持续集成（CI）\n\n**职责：** 代码构建、测试、打包\n\n**核心能力：**\n- 增量构建：基于代码变更只构建受影响部分\n- 智能缓存：避免重复下载依赖，构建时间减少 70%+\n- 并行执行：充分利用多核 CPU\n- 容器原生：天然适配 Docker 和 Kubernetes\n\n**典型流程：**\n```\n代码提交 → Git Webhook 触发 → 拉取代码 → 执行构建步骤 → 运行测试 → 推送镜像到制品库\n```\n\n### 2. 持续交付（CD）\n\n**职责：** 把构建产物部署到目标环境\n\n**核心能力：**\n- 多种部署策略：金丝雀（Canary）、蓝绿（Blue/Green）、滚动更新（Rolling）\n- 自动化验证：部署后自动执行测试和健康检查\n- 智能回滚：异常检测与自动回滚\n- GitOps 集成：声明式基础设施即代码\n\n**CD 建模四要素：**\n```\nPipeline（流水线）\n  └── Stage（阶段）\n        ├── Service（部署什么）\n        ├── Environment（部署到哪）\n        └── Execution（如何执行）\n```\n\n**部署策略详解：**\n\n- **滚动更新（Rolling）：** 逐批替换旧版本实例，简单但风险高\n- **蓝绿部署（Blue/Green）：** 两套环境并行，切换流量，无缝回滚\n- **金丝雀发布（Canary）：** 小流量验证，逐步放大，发现问题快速回滚\n\n### 3. 功能标记（Feature Flags）\n\n**职责：** 渐进式功能发布、A/B 测试\n\n**核心能力：**\n- 按用户群体、地理位置逐步发布\n- 无需重新部署的动态功能控制\n- 数据驱动的功能决策\n\n### 4. 云成本管理（Cloud Cost Management）\n\n**职责：** 多云成本可视化、优化建议\n\n**核心能力：**\n- AWS、Azure、GCP 多云成本统一视图\n- 团队/项目级成本追踪与标签分配\n- AI 驱动的优化建议：闲置资源识别、预留实例优化\n- 预算告警：超支前预警\n\n### 5. 安全测试编排（STO）\n\n**职责：** 把安全扫描集成到 CI/CD 流水线\n\n**核心能力：**\n- SAST（静态应用安全测试）：代码级漏洞扫描\n- DAST（动态应用安全测试）：运行时安全检测\n- SCA（软件组分分析）：依赖库安全扫描\n- 策略即代码（OPA）：安全策略自动化执行\n\n### 6. 混沌工程（Chaos Engineering）\n\n**职责：** 故障注入实验，验证系统弹性\n\n**核心能力：**\n- 自动化故障注入实验\n- 验证系统容错和恢复能力\n\n### 7. 工程洞察（Engineering Insights）\n\n**职责：** 交付效能可视化\n\n**核心能力：**\n- DORA 指标：部署频率、变更前置时间、恢复时间、变更失败率\n- 团队效率分析\n\n---\n\n## 三、核心概念速查\n\n### Connector（连接器）\n\n连接 Harness 与外部资源的桥梁：\n- **Kubernetes Cluster Connector**：连接 K8s 集群\n- **Git Connector**：连接 GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket\n- **Docker Registry Connector**：连接镜像仓库（Docker Hub、ECR、GCR、ACR）\n- **Cloud Connector**：连接 AWS/Azure/GCP\n- **Secret Manager**：存储密钥（SSH Key、Access Token 等）\n\n### Delegate（代理）\n\n运行在用户自己基础设施中的轻量级代理，负责：\n- 在目标环境执行部署命令\n- 连接制品仓库、云平台\n- 所有操作通过 HTTPS 出站，防火墙友好\n\n### Trigger（触发器）\n\n自动化流水线执行的条件：\n- Git Webhook 触发（代码提交/PR）\n- 制品变更触发\n- 定时触发（cron）\n- 手动触发\n\n### Approval（审批）\n\n在流水线中插入人工审批步骤：\n- 任意阶段可加审批门\n- 支持邮件/Slack 通知\n- 审批后可继续或终止流水线\n\n### Template（模板）\n\n可复用的流水线组件：\n- **Pipeline Template**：整个流水线模板\n- **Stage Template**：阶段模板（Golden Stage）\n- 模板支持参数化，通过 `templateInputs` 传入变量\n\n---\n\n## 四、流水线执行状态机\n\n```\nCreated → Validating → Queued → Running → Completed\n                ↓           ↓        ↓\n            Failed      Cancelled  Paused → Running\n                                   ↓\n                               Failed/Cancelled\n```\n\n---\n\n## 五、环境类型\n\n| 类型 | 用途 |\n|------|------|\n| Production | 生产环境 |\n| Pre-Production | 预发布/灰度环境 |\n\nEnvironment 中定义 Infrastructure（基础设施定义），关联具体的 K8s 集群/VM/云服务。\n\n---\n\n## 六、声明式配置示例\n\n```yaml\npipeline:\n  name: Deploy to Production\n  stages:\n    - stage:\n        name: Build and Deploy\n        type: Deployment\n        spec:\n          deploymentType: Kubernetes\n          services:\n            values:\n              - nginx-service\n          environments:\n            values:\n              - production\n          execution:\n            steps:\n              - stepGroup:\n                  name: Pre-Deploy\n                  steps:\n                    - step:\n                        type: K8sApply\n                        name: Apply Manifests\n              - stepGroup:\n                  name: Post-Deploy\n                  steps:\n                    - step:\n                        type: Http\n                        name: Health Check\n```\n\n---\n\n## 七、DORA 指标\n\n| 指标 | 定义 | 优秀标准 |\n|------|------|----------|\n| 部署频率 | 代码提交到生产的频率 | 按需（一天多次） |\n| 变更前置时间 | 提交到生产的时间 | < 1 小时 |\n| 恢复时间（MTTR） | 故障后恢复时间 | < 1 小时 |\n| 变更失败率 | 变更导致生产失败的比例 | < 15% |\n\n---\n\n## 八、与 Harness Engineering 的区别\n\n| | Harness Engineering（驾驭工程） | Harness.io（DevOps 平台） |\n|---|---|---|\n| 定位 | AI Agent 的运行管控系统 | CI/CD 持续交付平台 |\n| 解决的问题 | 让 AI 可靠地完成复杂任务 | 让软件可靠地交付到生产环境 |\n| 核心公式 | Agent = Model + Harness | Pipeline = Build + Test + Deploy + Verify |\n| 层级框架 | 约束层→信息层→验证层→修正层 | CI → CD → GitOps → STO |\n","file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/HARNESS_IO.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":6963,"output":1838,"cacheRead":56891,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65692,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775802106527,"responseId":"chatcmpl-3380d5cf-acda-483d-936c-9d0053f994bf"}}
