{"type":"message","id":"974ec750","parentId":"c5ca810a","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:52:27.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to \"activate\" these agents. In OpenClaw context, this likely means making these agents discoverable/usable in the UI. But I'm not sure exactly what the user means by \"activate\" - it could mean:\n\n1. Register them as skills so they show up in the skill list\n2. Create sessions/threads for each of them\n3. Configure them in some way\n\nLet me check how OpenClaw agents work - are they skills? Looking at the system prompt, I see there's a `clawhub` skill for installing skills, and skills are what appear in the available_skills list. Agents created as directories with SOUL.md and AGENTS.md might need to be registered as skills.\n\n\nI should look at the clawhub skill to understand the registration process, and then check the OpenClaw documentation to see if there's a specific way to activate or publish agents in the workspace. The key question is whether \"activating\" these agents means converting them to skills through clawhub, or if there's a different mechanism like `openclaw agents register` for this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"先看一下 OpenClaw 怎么注册 Agent。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bif9k3lhbrns_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw help 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":494,"output":267,"cacheRead":93627,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94388,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775803936591,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0954f407-7e3c-47f5-826e-18aadfac6022"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a49c6f3","parentId":"974ec750","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:52:31.099Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bif9k3lhbrns_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext] logLevel=info[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][peak-shaving] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][keepalive] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][feishu-greeting] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][innerapi] client initialized[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][media-understanding] active (provider, openclaw=2026.3.24)[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][image-generation] active (provider, openclaw=2026.3.24)[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][doc-parser] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][web-search] active (provider, openclaw=2026.3.24)[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][web-crawl] active[39m\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.24 (cff6dc9) — I'm like tmux: confusing at first, then suddenly you can't live without me.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --container <name>   Run the CLI inside a running Podman/Docker container\n                       named <name> (default: env OPENCLAW_CONTAINER)\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts guided\n                       setup.\n  configure            Interactive configuration for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  feishu-diagnose      运行飞书插件诊断，检查配置、连通性和权限状态\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3562,"aggregated":"[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext] logLevel=info[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][peak-shaving] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[miaoda-ext][keepalive] active[39m\n[35m[plugins][39m [36m[