{"type":"message","id":"69e255e8","parentId":"6ac170f0","timestamp":"2026-04-10T06:57:43.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No routing bindings - so these agents aren't bound to any channel. The control UI might only show agents that have routing bindings, or there might be another issue.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The control UI might be the OpenClaw web dashboard. Looking at the channel metadata, the user is coming through `webchat` channel. \n\nMaybe the control UI only shows agents that are accessible through the current channel setup, and the new agents need to be bound to show up there. But binding is typically per-channel, and webchat might not support multiple agents in the same UI way.\n\nAlternatively, maybe the Control UI just doesn't show multiple agents in the way the user expects. \n\nI should ask where exactly they're looking - whether it's the OpenClaw Control UI, the Feishu app, or somewhere else - and suggest they try refreshing the page or checking the dashboard directly. Let me also look at the current gateway config to see if there's something relevant about how agents are displayed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_roklt9sd7r14_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels status 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"^\\[35m\" | grep -v \"^$\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":1827,"output":254,"cacheRead":101243,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103324,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775804247283,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e5724616-6279-4ee0-9f9b-c313b2ff2aa0"}}
