{"type":"message","id":"9f1a263a","parentId":"19f9a906","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:04:29.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Mock MinIO is running. The health check returned a 404 for /health because I didn't handle the /health endpoint in the main server. Let me fix that in mockMinio.ts, or just test with a direct HEAD request.\n\nActually looking at the code, the main server (port 9000) handles /health, but the result shows a NoSuchKey - that's because `parts[parts.length - 1]` of \"/\" is empty, so it's trying to look up an empty object name. Let me fix that.\n\nActually wait - looking at the output more carefully, the server IS running, but the issue is with the `curl -s http://localhost:9000/health` - the main server doesn't have a /health handler, it goes to the extraServer on port 9001. \n\nSo the curl to port 9000 is hitting the object handler instead of the health endpoint. The `{\"Code\":\"NoSuchKey\"...}` response confirms the request reached the object handler with an empty object name, which means the routing isn't set up correctly.\n\nThe Mock MinIO server is actually running fine - I just need to curl port 9001 instead to access the health check properly. Let me start the Express backend now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Mock MinIO 起来了，health 接口在 9001。再测一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jgqchr0pfwhk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:9001/health"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":429,"output":303,"cacheRead":112443,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113175,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775804659098,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a0ab5739-f8f3-480c-9662-dee31afc53da"}}
