{"type":"message","id":"7b7d64ef","parentId":"5fda1411","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:07:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even dynamic imports are statically resolved by Rollup. The issue is that Rollup analyzes dynamic imports too. The solution is to use a different approach - maybe configure vite to not bundle certain modules, or use a factory function pattern that doesn't statically import minio.\n\nThe cleanest approach for Vite is to add `optimizeDeps.exclude` and `build.rollupOptions.external` for the minio package, OR to use a proxy/placeholder pattern.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: just don't import minio at all in the source - instead have two separate files: `scanService.ts` (mock) and `scanServiceReal.ts` (real). Or configure vite.config.ts to handle this.\n\n\nLet me configure vite.config.ts to exclude minio from dependency optimization and externalize it during the build, so Rollup won't try to resolve it statically even within dynamic imports.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Rollup 会静态分析动态 import。用 `vite.config.ts` externalize 掉：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_069ord9evq39_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue'\nimport { resolve } from 'path'\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [vue()],\n  resolve: {\n    alias: {\n      '@': resolve(__dirname, 'src'),\n    },\n  },\n  build: {\n    // 真实 MinIO 包仅在 USE_MOCK=false 时需要，避免 build 报错\n    rollupOptions: {\n      external: ['minio'],\n    },\n  },\n  optimizeDeps: {\n    exclude: ['minio'],\n  },\n  server: {\n    port: 5173,\n    proxy: {\n      '/api': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:3001',\n        changeOrigin: true,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n})\n","path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/vite.config.ts"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"inpu