{"type":"message","id":"867d2738","parentId":"2a26c0f7","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:37:58.957Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`api.github.com` is reachable but `github.com` (the web UI) is not reachable. This is a common issue in sandboxed environments - some IPs/ports are blocked. The git push would need to connect to `github.com` which is blocked.\n\nLet me try using the GitHub API to push the files instead. I can:\n1. Use GitHub API to create a commit2. Or use the git-upload-pack via API\n\nActually, the best approach would be to push through the API. But this is getting complex. Let me try a few more approaches:\n1. Try with `git://` protocol (port 9418) - unlikely to work\n2. Try using a different approach to push - maybe the issue is specific to the git daemon\n\n\n3. Since the GitHub API itself is accessible, I could leverage that to create the repository and commits directly, though this is getting quite involved. The core issue is that `github.com` itself isn't reachable from here, only `api.github.com` works, so I need to find a way to work around this limitation.\n\nActually, thinking about it more - the GitHub web UI works in the browser, which means the user's machine can reach GitHub fine. The sandbox itself is the one with the network restriction. So instead of trying to push directly from the sandbox, I should just tell the user to clone the repo locally and handle the push from there.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"沙箱无法直连 `github.com`（网络受限），但 GitHub API (`api.github.com`) 是通的。换策略——用 GitHub API 推文件：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4czvuwwvm3wl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 通过 GitHub API 获取仓库信息，确认可以用 API 推\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: token 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\" \\\n  \"https://api.github.com/repos/wangyang962996947/yaxin\" 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nr=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('仓库:', r['full_name'])\nprint('默认分支:', r['