{"type":"message","id":"e8cd6b3e","parentId":"c6d79ed3","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:45:28.981Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `--timeout` flag doesn't exist for `git push`. The issue is that the previous attempts timed out after about 30 seconds, but the user says github.com is reachable (ping works). \n\nLet me check if there's a DNS issue - the remote URL uses `github.com` but maybe there's an HTTP proxy issue. Let me also check if `git` uses a different port.\n\nActually, the problem might be that the sandbox can `ping github.com` but HTTP/HTTPS traffic goes through a proxy or is blocked. The ping uses ICMP which might bypass the HTTP proxy.\n\nBut wait - git push uses HTTPS (port 443), not ping (ICMP). \n\nThe previous attempts with `curl` to `github.com` also timed out even with `--connect-timeout 5`, so connectivity to port 443 is definitely blocked. Though the user mentioned ping works, which could mean the proxy allows ICMP but blocks HTTPS, or there's intermittent connectivity. Let me try running the push command in the background and waiting longer to see if it eventually succeeds, or I should check if there's a system proxy configured that's causing issues.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vpor29cfh8n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查是否有HTTP代理（git会使用系统代理）\nenv | grep -i proxy\necho \"---\"\n# git 网络测试\ntimeout 10 git ls-remote https://github.com/wangyang962996947/yaxin.git HEAD 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":878,"output":318,"cacheRead":143355,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":144551,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807116271,"responseId":"chatcmpl-31f90e3a-bc06-4f6a-bec9-39d7d5254b1f"}}
