{"type":"message","id":"72258d09","parentId":"20f78a4e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:45:54.789Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still timing out. `git ls-remote` also hangs. This confirms that HTTPS port (443) to github.com is blocked. But the user insists ping works and wants me to keep retrying.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe git is using SSH instead of HTTPS, or there's a way to configure git to use a different approach. Or maybe I should try using SSH instead of HTTPS.\n\nActually, wait - `git ls-remote` over HTTPS (port 443) is timing out. But the user says ping works. This means:\n- ICMP (ping) works\n- HTTPS (port 443) is blocked\n\nBut earlier `curl https://api.github.com/zen` worked fine. \n\nSo the issue is specific to `github.com` domain - `api.github.com` works because it resolves to a different IP that might be whitelisted. Let me verify that `api.github.com` is actually reachable.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qzmqxdfwmnvo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 api.github.com 是否通（之前是通的）\ncurl -s -o /dev/null -w \"api.github.com: %{http_code}\\n\" --connect-timeout 5 https://api.github.com/zen 2>&1\n\n# 对比 github.com\ncurl -s -o /dev/null -w \"github.com: %{http_code}\\n\" --connect-timeout 5 https://github.com 2>&1\n\n# 查看 github.com 解析到的IP\nhost github.com 2>&1 | head -3","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":448,"output":338,"cacheRead":144251,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145037,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807144071,"responseId":"chatcmpl-66f097d1-eb7e-4915-bef4-044e5036a48a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c242650","parentId":"72258d09","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:46:00.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qzmqxdfwmnvo_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"api.github.com: 200\ngithub.com: 000\ngithub.com has address 20.205.243.166\ngithub.com mail is handled by 0 github-com.mail.protection.outlook.com."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5673,"aggregated":"api.github.com: 200\ngithub.com: 000\ngithub.com has address 20.205.243.166\ngithub.com mail is handled by 0 github-com.mail.protection.outlook.com.","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775807160478}}
{"type":"message","id":"f93e2125","parentId":"8c242650","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:46:34.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! `api.github.com` is reachable (200), but `github.com` is not (000). However, `github.com` resolves to IP `20.205.243.166`. This IP might be blocked by the sandbox's firewall. The API endpoints (like `api.github.com`) might resolve to a different IP that's whitelisted.\n\nSince I can reach `api.github.com` but not `github.com`, and the Git remote uses `github.com`, I need to try a different approach.\n\nOne option: Use the GitHub API to push files directly (contents API), bypassing git protocol entirely. This is possible via the `PUT /repos/{owner}/{repo}/contents/{path}` endpoint.\n \nI'll go with the GitHub Contents API approach - I can authenticate with my token and push files directly to the repository without needing the git protocol to work.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"`github.com` IP 被封，`api.github.com` 是通的。换方案——用 GitHub Contents API 直接推文件：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k6r14yegtd0m_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * push-to-github.mjs\n * 通过 GitHub Contents API 把本地文件推送到仓库\n * 绕过 git 协议，直接用 REST API\n *\n * 用法: node push-to-github.mjs\n */\n\nimport fs from 'fs'\nimport path from 'path'\nimport crypto from 'crypto'\n\nconst TOKEN = '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'\nconst OWNER = 'wangyang962996947'\nconst REPO = 'yaxin'\nconst BASE_URL = `https://api.github.com/repos/${OWNER}/${REPO}/contents`\n\nconst BRANCH = 'main'\n\nconst headers = {\n  'Authorization': `Bearer ${TOKEN}`,\n  'Accept': 'application/vnd.github+json',\n  'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28',\n  'User-Agent': 'yaxin-agent'\n}\n\nasync function fileExistsOnRemote(filePath) {\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}/${filePath}?ref=${BRANCH}`, { headers })\n    if (res.status === 404) return null\n    const data = await res.json()\n    return data.sha || null\n  } catch {\n    return null\n  }\n}\n\nasync function uploadFile(filePath, content) {\n  const encodedPath = filePath.replace(/\\\\/g, '/')\n  const url = `${BASE_URL}/${encodedPath}?ref=${BRANCH}`\n\n  const body = {\n    message: `feat: add ${filePath}`,\n    content: content.toString('base64'),\n    branch: BRANCH\n  }\n\n  const sha = await fileExistsOnRemote(encodedPath)\n  if (sha) {\n    body.sha = sha\n  }\n\n  const res = await fetch(url, {\n    method: 'PUT',\n    headers,\n    body: JSON.stringify(body)\n  })\n\n  const data = await res.json()\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    throw new Error(`Failed to upload ${filePath}: ${JSON.stringify(data)}`)\n  }\n  return data\n}\n\nasync function walkDir(dir, base = '') {\n  const entries = fs.readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })\n  const files = []\n  for (const entry of entries) {\n    if (entry.name === 'node_modules' || entry.name === '.git') continue\n    const full = path.join(dir, entry.name)\n    const rel = path.join(base, entry.name)\n    if (entry.isDirectory()) {\n      files.push(...(await walkDir(full, rel)))\n    } else {\n      files.push(rel)\n    }\n  }\n  return files\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const workspaceDir = '/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace'\n  const targetFiles = [\n    'HARNESS_ENGINEERING.md',\n    'HARNESS_IO.md',\n    'agents',\n    'projects',\n    'code-scanning-plugin',\n    'HARNESS-AGENT',\n    '.gitignore'\n  ]\n\n  console.log('🚀 开始推送到 GitHub...\\n')\n\n  // 获取当前 commit SHA（用于作为 tree 的 base）\n  const refRes = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}?ref=${BRANCH}`, { headers })\n  const refData = await refRes.json()\n  console.log('仓库当前commit:', refData.commit?.sha || '无现有提交')\n\n  let pushed = 0\n  let skipped = 0\n  let failed = 0\n\n  for (const relPath of targetFiles) {\n    const fullPath = path.join(workspaceDir, relPath)\n    if (!fs.existsSync(fullPath)) {\n      console.log(`⏭️  跳过（不存在）: ${relPath}`)\n      skipped++\n      continue\n    }\n\n    const stat = fs.statSync(fullPath)\n\n    if (stat.isDirectory()) {\n      const files = await walkDir(fullPath, relPath)\n      for (const file of files) {\n        const fileFull = path.join(workspaceDir, file)\n        const content = fs.readFileSync(fileFull)\n        try {\n          await uploadFile(file, content)\n          console.log(`  ✅ ${file}`)\n          pushed++\n        } catch (err) {\n          console.log(`  ❌ ${file}: ${err.message}`)\n          failed++\n        }\n        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)) // 限速\n      }\n    } else {\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(fullPath)\n      try {\n        await uploadFile(relPath, content)\n        console.log(`✅ ${relPath}`)\n        pushed++\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.log(`❌ ${relPath}: ${err.message}`)\n        failed++\n      }\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500))\n    }\n  }\n\n  console.log(`\\n📊 推送完成:`)\n  console.log(`  成功: ${pushed}`)\n  console.log(`  跳过: ${skipped}`)\n  console.log(`  失败: ${failed}`)\n}\n\nmain().catch(console.error)\n","path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/push-to-github.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":396,"output":1326,"cacheRead":144699,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":146421,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807160492,"responseId":"chatcmpl-cdfa99c5-4147-4314-90b3-233ffb9965eb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a9f08f4","parentId":"f93e2125","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:46:34.768Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_k6r14yegtd0m_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 3756 bytes to /home/gem/workspace/agent/push-to-github.mjs"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775807194748}}
{"type":"message","id":"9de9ff51","parentId":"5a9f08f4","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:46:56.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, this approach has a problem - the GitHub Contents API uploads files individually, but the files will be \"unconnected\" - they'll be uploaded as separate commits, not as a coherent tree from a single commit. Also, GitHub Contents API creates individual commits for each file, which means we'll get 81 individual commits.\n\nA better approach would be to create a proper git commit with a tree structure and push it. But that requires creating a proper git commit object, which is complex.\n\nActually, for this use case, individual file commits are fine. The goal is to get the code into the repository. Let me proceed with the Contents API approach but simplify it to just push the files.\n \nHold on - I'm realizing the Contents API creates orphaned commits with no parent connection to the existing repository history, so the commit graph will be disconnected. Plus there's a 5 concurrent request rate limit, and uploading 81 files would generate 81 separate commits. The best approach would be to either force-push a complete commit tree using the Git Data API, or switch to using `git push` with SSH instead.\n\nSince HTTPS is blocked but git protocols might work differently, let me just try running `git push` again with a longer timeout. If that fails, I'll fall back to the Contents API - the orphaned commits are better than nothing, and the user can reorganize later with a force push.\n\nLet me test whether `git-upload-pack` works directly to see if the git protocol itself is accessible.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jk1m25ezgagm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 git-upload-pack 端口（git push 实际用的是这个）\nnc -z -w5 github.com 443 2>&1 && echo \"443端口通\" || echo \"443端口不通\"\n\n# 测试 SSH 端口\nnc -z -w5 github.com 22 2>&1 && echo \"22端口通\" || echo \"22端口不通\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":3103,"output":414,"cacheRead":143355,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":146872,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807194780,"responseId":"chatcmpl-2c3da3dc-af33-4ca9-9c3a-18da55bc3922"}}
{"type":"message","id":"25c5212d","parentId":"9de9ff51","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:46:56.975Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jk1m25ezgagm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Connection to github.com (20.205.243.166) 443 port [tcp/https] succeeded!\n443端口通\nConnection to github.com (20.205.243.166) 22 port [tcp/ssh] succeeded!\n22端口通"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":221,"aggregated":"Connection to github.com (20.205.243.166) 443 port [tcp/https] succeeded!\n443端口通\nConnection to github.com (20.205.243.166) 22 port [tcp/ssh] succeeded!\n22端口通","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775807216966}}
{"type":"message","id":"01a30047","parentId":"25c5212d","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:47:02.365Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Port 443 is accessible now! And port 22 is also accessible. So the network is fine now. The previous timeouts were just because the connection was slow to negotiate.\n\nLet me try the git push again.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"端口 443 和 22 都通了！马上重试 push：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c3f9l16w2614_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent && git push origin HEAD:main -v 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":449,"output":114,"cacheRead":146491,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147054,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807216979,"responseId":"chatcmpl-dd6e9aed-4e0c-4835-a694-e6854e98bd1b"}}
