{"type":"message","id":"65a7751b","parentId":"a9fcd379","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:47:12.286Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The push is failing because the remote URL format with embedded token is not being recognized. The issue is that `origin` is set to `https://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@github.com/wangyang962996947/yaxin.git`, but `git push origin HEAD:main` is trying to resolve it and failing.\n\nThe problem might be that git is interpreting the URL differently. Let me check the remote URL and try to debug this.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that `git push origin HEAD:main` with the verbose flag shows \"origin does not appear to be a git repository\". This suggests git can't resolve the remote properly. \n\nThe embedded credentials might not be working as expected with this URL format. Let me verify the remote is actually configured and pointing to the right repository.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mqsaptearup8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent\ngit remote -v\necho \"---\"\n# 测试能否读取远程\ngit ls-remote --heads origin 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":181,"output":256,"cacheRead":146939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147376,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807222403,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c3f1c222-814c-4d9a-8e8f-7dad06f0d32d"}}
