{"type":"message","id":"5cbd888f","parentId":"91d108e1","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:50:34.543Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I generated an SSH key pair. Now I need to add the public key to the user's GitHub account. But I can't do that through the API easily - I would need to use the GitHub API to add an SSH key, which requires different permissions or a different token scope.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Since HTTPS is working (curl confirmed), maybe the git push is just slow because it's uploading many files. Let me try git push with `--progress` and a very long timeout, and see if it eventually makes progress.\n\nOr wait - let me check if maybe the issue is that git is trying to use `git-upload-pack` and it's not responding fast enough. Let me use `curl` to test the git-upload-pack endpoint directly.\n \nLet me test the git protocol endpoint directly with curl to see if it's responding at all.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h8oc5fwe92id_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 git-upload-pack\ncurl -s --connect-timeout 10 \\\n  \"https://github.com/wangyang962996947/yaxin.git/info/refs?service=git-upload-pack\" \\\n  -H \"Accept: application/x-git-upload-pack-advertisement\" \\\n  2>&1 | head -5","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":531,"output":277,"cacheRead":149627,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150435,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807424242,"responseId":"chatcmpl-10d7e90c-e4d4-44af-9724-4346f8b75602"}}
