{"type":"message","id":"ebf2f531","parentId":"618beb76","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:50:47.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The git-upload-pack is responding correctly. So the protocol is working. The issue is that git push is taking too long to negotiate or upload.\n\nLet me try a different approach - use `git push` with verbose output and in the background, checking its output periodically. Or let me try using `git push` with specific options to make it faster.Actually, looking at the previous git push attempts - they were all exiting with \"signal SIGTERM\" (timeout). Let me check if maybe there's a very long timeout somewhere. The exec tool might have a hard timeout of 30 seconds that I need to override.Let me check the exec tool docs again - I see there's a `timeout` parameter. \n\nI need to push this up to its maximum value and attempt the operation again.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Git 协议完全正常！之前超时是因为 exec 默认 30 秒 limit。换 SSH 方式重新 push：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jakpdy33j25z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent\n\n# 用 SSH remote 方式 push\ngit remote add ssh-origin git@github.com:wangyang962996947/yaxin.git 2>/dev/null || \\\n  git remote set-url ssh-origin git@github.com:wangyang962996947/yaxin.git\n\n# 配置 SSH 使用临时密钥\nexport GIT_SSH_COMMAND=\"ssh -i /tmp/yaxin_push_key -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null\"\n\n# 先测试 SSH 连通性\nssh -i /tmp/yaxin_push_key -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ConnectTimeout=10 git@github.com 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":478,"output":365,"cacheRead":150075,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807435158,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c508d9d0-bab8-45f8-b001-b0fac44ff939"}}
