{"type":"message","id":"334285fa","parentId":"94d20613","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:51:03.815Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"SSH is connecting but public key authentication is failing because the public key hasn't been added to the GitHub account. That's expected.\n\nLet me go back to HTTPS. Since the git-upload-pack is working, the issue might be git's credential handling. Let me try using `git credential` to properly store the token.\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach: directly use `git push` with the token embedded in a cookie file or use `git push` with `--config` to set the credential.\n\nActually, the most direct approach: use the `GIT_ASKPASS` environment variable to provide the token, or use a `.netrc` file which is more reliable.\n \nWait, I think I've been overcomplicating this. GitHub supports token-based authentication via HTTPS, and the issue is likely that git isn't properly using the token from the remote URL. Let me set up a `.netrc` file with the token instead, which is the most straightforward way to handle HTTPS authentication.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vbxo3jj6tdng_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent\n\n# 用 .netrc 方式（最可靠）\ncat > ~/.netrc << 'EOF'\nmachine github.com\n  login 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\n  password x-oauth-basic\nEOF\nchmod 600 ~/.netrc\n\n# 重新设置 remote 为标准 HTTPS URL（不含 token）\ngit remote set-url origin https://github.com/wangyang962996947/yaxin.git\n\n# 清除 credential store\ngit config --unset credential.helper 2>/dev/null || true\n\n# 验证\ngit remote -v\necho \"---\"\n\n# 测试 ls-remote\ntimeout 20 git ls-remote --heads origin 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":455,"output":404,"cacheRead":150523,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151382,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cac