{"type":"message","id":"b6bcbbee","parentId":"18b187ad","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:51:35.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`git ls-remote` is still timing out even though curl to github.com works. The issue might be that git is trying to resolve the SSH hostname `github.com` first (because ssh-origin is set to git@github.com which SSH), even though we're using the HTTPS URL. Or git is doing some DNS lookup or credential helper that's blocking.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach: directly use the GitHub API to push the files as individual commits. This bypasses the git protocol entirely and uses the HTTPS API that I know works.\n\nI'll use the GitHub Contents API to push each file. This will:\n1. Check if the file exists (GET) - get its SHA\n\n\n2. Upload/update the file (PUT) with the SHA if it exists, otherwise create it fresh\n\nThis approach will create individual commits per file rather than preserving the tree structure, but it's the most reliable method since the API works and doesn't require git protocol support.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\nGit 协议一直卡住，换 Contents API 方式直接推文件（API 是通的）：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qsmmas7qgzst_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent\n\n# 先测试 API 基本连通性\ncurl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer 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\" \\\n  \"https://api.github.com/repos/wangyang962996947/yaxin/contents/\" 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":195,"output":332,"cacheRead":151419,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807483951,"responseId":"chatcmpl-fdb89800-37bc-44b6-8967-f5a8adb2a428"}}
{"type":"message","id":"44d46527","parentId":"b6bcbbee","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:51:36.571Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qsmmas7qgzst_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"message\": \"This repository is empty.\",\n  \"documentation_url\": \"https://docs.github.com/v3/repos/contents/#get-contents\",\n  \"status\": \"404\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":611,"aggregated":"{\n  \"message\": \"This repository is empty.\",\n  \"documentation_url\": \"https://docs.github.com/v3/repos/contents/#get-contents\",\n  \"status\": \"404\"\n}","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775807496559}}
{"type":"message","id":"64e373e6","parentId":"44d46527","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:52:08.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API is working. The repository is empty. Now let me use the Contents API to push files. Let me write a proper script that uploads files one by one.\n\nActually, let me first try to create a single commit using the Git Data API (create a tree and commit), then push the refs. This would create a proper git history.\n\nBut for simplicity, let me start with the Contents API to push a README.md first to make the repository non-empty, and then push all other files.\n\nActually, the Contents API for an empty repo should allow creating files directly. Let me write a proper upload script.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the issue is that git protocol is hanging but HTTPS API calls work. Let me write a comprehensive script that:1. \n\nI'll create a script that pushes the entire workspace using the Contents API, uploading all files with proper paths and checking for existing files to get their SHAs for updates. The rate limit is 5000 requests per hour for authenticated users, so I have plenty of room to push the 81 files without any issues.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fyqox83o0t57_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * push-via-api.mjs\n * 通过 GitHub Contents API 推送文件到仓库\n * 绕过 git 协议，用 HTTPS REST API\n */\nimport fs from 'fs'\nimport path from 'path'\nimport https from 'https'\n\nconst TOKEN = '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'\nconst OWNER = 'wangyang962996947'\nconst REPO = 'yaxin'\nconst BRANCH = 'main'\n\nconst BASE_URL = `https://api.github.com`\n\nfunction api(method, path2, body = null) {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const url = new URL(path2, BASE_URL)\n    const opts = {\n      hostname: url.hostname,\n      path: url.pathname + url.search,\n      method,\n      headers: {\n        'Authorization': `Bearer ${TOKEN}`,\n        'Accept': 'application/vnd.github+json',\n        'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28',\n        'User-Agent': 'yaxin-agent',\n      }\n    }\n    if (body) {\n      opts.headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/json'\n    }\n    const req = https.request(opts, res => {\n      let data = ''\n      res.on('data', c => data += c)\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          resolve({ status: res.statusCode, data: JSON.parse(data) })\n        } catch {\n          resolve({ status: res.statusCode, data })\n        }\n      })\n    })\n    req.on('error', reject)\n    if (body) req.write(JSON.stringify(body))\n    req.end()\n  })\n}\n\nasync function getSha(filePath) {\n  const res = await api('GET', `/repos/${OWNER}/${REPO}/contents/${filePath}?ref=${BRANCH}`)\n  if (res.status === 404) return null\n  if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error(`getSha ${filePath} failed: ${JSON.stringify(res.data)}`)\n  return res.data.sha || null\n}\n\nasync function uploadFile(filePath, content) {\n  const encodedPath = filePath.replace(/\\\\/g, '/')\n  const body = {\n    message: `feat: add ${encodedPath}`,\n    content: content.toString('base64'),\n    branch: BRANCH\n  }\n  const sha = await getSha(encodedPath)\n  if (sha) body.sha = sha\n\n  const res = await api('PUT', `/repos/${OWNER}/${REPO}/contents/${encodedPath}`, body)\n  if (res.status !== 200 && res.status !== 201) {\n    throw new Error(`${res.status}: ${JSON.stringify(res.data)}`)\n  }\n  return res\n}\n\nasync function walk(dir, base = '') {\n  const entries = fs.readdirSync(dir, { withFileTypes: true })\n  const files = []\n  for (const e of entries) {\n    if (e.name === 'node_modules' || e.name === '.git') continue\n    const fp = path.join(dir, e.name)\n    const rp = path.join(base, e.name)\n    if (e.isDirectory()) files.push(...(await walk(fp, rp)))\n    else files.push(rp)\n  }\n  return files\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const base = '/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace'\n  const items = [\n    ['HARNESS_ENGINEERING.md', 'HARNESS_ENGINEERING.md'],\n    ['HARNESS_IO.md', 'HARNESS_IO.md'],\n    ['.gitignore', '.gitignore'],\n  ]\n\n  // 添加 agents 目录\n  const agentsDir = path.join(base, 'agents')\n  if (fs.existsSync(agentsDir)) {\n    const files = await walk(agentsDir, 'agents')\n    for (const f of files) items.push([f, f])\n  }\n\n  // 添加 projects 目录\n  const projectsDir = path.join(base, 'projects')\n  if (fs.existsSync(projectsDir)) {\n    const files = await walk(projectsDir, 'projects')\n    for (const f of files) items.push([f, f])\n  }\n\n  // 添加 code-scanning-plugin\n  const csDir = path.join(base, 'code-scanning-plugin')\n  if (fs.existsSync(csDir)) {\n    const files = await walk(csDir, 'code-scanning-plugin')\n    for (const f of files) items.push([f, f])\n  }\n\n  // 添加 HARNESS-AGENT\n  const harnessDir = path.join(base, 'HARNESS-AGENT')\n  if (fs.existsSync(harnessDir)) {\n    const files = await walk(harnessDir, 'HARNESS-AGENT')\n    for (const f of files) items.push([f, f])\n  }\n\n  console.log(`📦 共 ${items.length} 个文件待推送\\n`)\n\n  let ok = 0, fail = 0\n  for (const [srcPath, dstPath] of items) {\n    const fullSrc = path.join(base, srcPath)\n    if (!fs.existsSync(fullSrc)) continue\n    try {\n      const content = fs.readFileSync(fullSrc)\n      await uploadFile(dstPath, content)\n      console.log(`  ✅ ${dstPath}`)\n      ok++\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.log(`  ❌ ${dstPath}: ${e.message}`)\n      fail++\n    }\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300))\n  }\n\n  console.log(`\\n📊 完成: 成功 ${ok} / 失败 ${fail}`)\n}\n\nmain().catch(console.error)\n","path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/push-via-api.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":134,"output":1485,"cacheRead":151867,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153486,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse"