{"type":"message","id":"f6b354d0","parentId":"3a5360e7","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:52:28.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, there's a naming conflict. I have two different files:1. `push-to-github.mjs` (Node.js script using fetch)\n2. `push-via-api.mjs` (Node.js script using https module)The second one is more reliable since it doesn't depend on fetch (Node.js 18+ has native fetch but might have issues). Let me run the push-via-api.mjs script.Actually, wait - the issue with the first approach was using the GitHub Contents API which creates individual commits. But actually, this is fine for getting the code into the repository. Let me run the script.But wait, there's a problem - the Contents API will create one commit per file, which will result in 81+ commits. This is messy. \n\nI should use the Git Data API instead - creating a proper commit with all files in a tree structure. But that's more complex. Let me try the simpler approach first and see if it works. Actually, the most straightforward solution is to use `git push` over HTTPS since curl can connect to github.com fine. The issue before was git hanging, which suggests the problem might be with git's credential handling or protocol negotiation rather than the connection itself. Let me run the push-via-api script and see if it works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_15yjqiv3thet_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent && node push-via-api.mjs 2>&1","timeout":300,"yieldMs":60000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":151489,"output":329,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151818,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775807528950,"responseId":"chatcmpl-33722665-e5ab-47c4-ae19-f0a60768d7b3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e49f480","parentId":"f6b354d0","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:53:15.390Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好，持续重试推送：`github.com` IP 被封，`api.github.com` 是通的。换方案——用 GitHub Contents API 直接推文件：端口 443 和 22 都通了！马上重试 push：远程配置丢了，重新设：`gh` CLI 可用！用它来认证并推送：HTTPS 能连通但 git 协议卡住。试试 SSH 方式：Git 协议完全正常！之前超时是因为 exec 默认 30 秒 limit。换 SSH 方式重新 push：Git 协议一直卡住，换 Contents API 方式直接推文件（API 是通的）："}],"timestamp":1775807595371,"stopReason":"stop","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"gateway-injected","idempotencyKey":"3c9d098b-ef3d-410e-aa6f-18cc05f0b92a:assistant","openclawAbort":{"aborted":true,"origin":"rpc","runId":"3c9d098b-ef3d-410e-aa6f-18cc05f0b92a"}}}
