{"type":"message","id":"e1ed2897","parentId":"747c6909","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:36:01.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the tests ran! There are 3 failures:\n\n1. **提示词末尾缺少 MinIO 上传指令** — The test checks if the prompt contains \"MinIO\" or \"10.28\", but in the Mock mode, the `buildPromptWithUploadInstruction` was modified to always append the MinIO instruction. But the test's check in `testTemplateButtons` clicks the template button and then manually checks the text - this doesn't go through `submitScan()`. The MinIO instruction is only appended when `submitScan()` calls `buildPromptWithUploadInstruction()`. So the template just loads the text, not the enriched version. I need to fix the test to call `submitScan()` and check the prompt that was actually submitted.\n\n\n2. **轮询等待失败** — The mock minio seed is called at `/mock/seed?uuid=${uuid}` on port 9001, but the actual `waitForResult` polls `fileExists(uuid)` which calls the minio client at `localhost:9000` for the GET request, not the seed endpoint. So the flow is: user clicks submit → POST to backend → backend returns 202 → frontend starts polling → waitForResult polls fileExists → fileExists calls GET localhost:9000/{uuid} → should return 404 initially and then 200 after seed. But the seed is at port 9001 not 9000, so the polling endpoint never sees the seeded file.\n\nThe real problem is that `waitForResult` polls the GET endpoint on port 9000, but the file only gets seeded to port 9001. The backend's 60-second timeout is what eventually seeds to port 9000, so if I manually seed to port 9001, the frontend's polling still fails because it's watching the wrong port. The port mismatch means the manual seed doesn't actually trigger the frontend's polling logic. The issue is that my test calls the seed endpoint after the submit, but the backend's actual file creation happens at the 60-second mark on port 9000. When I check the status immediately after seeding to port 9001, the GET request to port 9000 still returns 404, so the waitForResult loop times out before the backend ever gets around to creating the file.\n\nTo fix this, I should either wait for the backend's natural 60-second delay, or poll the seed status endpoint on port 9001 instead of relying on the port 9000 GET request. The seed endpoint isn't being polled by the frontend, so that approach won't work. I'll go with waiting for the backend's natural delay and adjusting the test timeout accordingly, then update the test to call `buildPromptWithUploadInstruction` directly to verify the MinIO instruction is appended correctly.\n\nFor the third issue with the reset button, I need to understand what state the page is actually in when the 30-second timeout occurs and why the `.btn-secondary` selector isn't finding the element.\n\nLooking at the flow: after submitting, the page should show the waiting state, then display results after the backend responds. But if the result step fails to render due to the polling issue, clicking reset tries to go back to step 1, which requires being in either step 4 or error state first.\n\nSo the real problem is the timeout on that last assertion. The previous step failed to show Step 4, so we're stuck in step 3 with no valid reset path available. The `waitFor` function polls until the condition is true or the timeout hits. The real problem is that it returns `false` on timeout, but the test expects it to throw, so the error gets caught and counted as a failure instead of actually failing the test. This掩盖了真正的问题：轮询逻辑可能根本没有正确等待文件出现。\n\nI need to restructure the test to wait for the backend's natural 60-second delay instead of trying to manually seed a file, and then fix the timeout assertion so it properly fails instead of catching the error. The core issues are that `waitForResult` polls the GET endpoint on port 9000 for the UUID file, but if I seed the file to port 9001, it won't be visible there. The backend creates the file on port 9000 after 60 seconds, so my manual seed on port 9001 doesn't help the polling succeed. I could modify the mock server to seed on port 9000 instead, or create a separate seed endpoint that writes to port 9000.\n\nBut really, the simplest approach is to just wait for the backend's natural 60-second delay during the test rather than trying to manually seed the file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"测试发现 3 个问题。逐个分析：\n\n**问题 1**：模板测试只读了原始文本，没有走 `buildPromptWithUploadInstruction()` 追加逻辑\n**问题 2**：Mock 手动注入了端口 9001，但 `waitForResult` 轮询的是端口 9000，两者不通\n**问题 3**：Step 4 没出现导致重新扫描按钮也找不到\n\n先修复 Mock MinIO 的 seed 端——注入到 9000 才有效：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2e580w0q1re3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"filePath":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/server/mockMinio.ts","limit":40,"offset":110}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":1134,"output":1116,"cacheRead":83323,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85573,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775810076962,"responseId":"chatcmpl-f45e1a36-0654-4b89-9cf0-643b87aa4d9a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd86748e","parentId":"e1ed2897","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:36:01.826Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2e580w0q1re3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    }\n    return\n  }\n\n  // PUT /bucket/objectName — 上传文件\n  if (req.method === 'PUT' || req.method === 'POST') {\n    const chunks: Buffer[] = []\n    for await (const chunk of req as AsyncIterable<Buffer>) {\n      chunks.push(chunk)\n    }\n    const body = Buffer.concat(chunks)\n\n    // 解析 query 参数（uploadId、partNumber 等，简化为直接写文件）\n    fs.writeFileSync(filePath, body)\n    const stat = fs.statSync(filePath)\n\n    sendJSON(res, 200, {\n      ETag: `\"${objectName}\"`,\n      Size: stat.size,\n      Location: `/${BUCKET}/${objectName}`,\n    })\n    return\n  }\n\n  sendJSON(res, 405, { error: 'Method not allowed' })\n})\n\n// ============= 辅助命令接口 =============\n\n/**\n * GET / — 状态页\n * GET /health — 健康检查\n * POST /mock/seed?uuid=xxx — 往 MinIO 注入一个 MD 文件（用于测试）\n */\nconst extraServer = http.createServer(async (req: http.IncomingMessage, res: http.ServerResponse) => {\n  const url = new URL(req.url || '/', `http://localhost:${PORT}`)\n  const pathname = url.pathname\n\n  if (pathname === '/health') {\n    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' })\n\n[103 more lines in file. Use offset=150 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775810161822}}
{"type":"message","id":"67a77fb5","parentId":"fd86748e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:37:00.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The extraServer (port 9001) handles the seed endpoint. But it writes to the same DATA_DIR (/tmp/code-scanning-mock). Both port 9000 and port 9001 read from the same directory. So actually, seeding to port 9001 should work since both ports use the same DATA_DIR.Wait, let me re-read the code. Port 9000 server uses `getObjectPath(objectName)` which returns `/tmp/code-scanning-mock/${objectName}`. The extraServer on port 9001 also uses `getObjectPath(objectName)` from the same closure. So both should write to the same file path.\nSo the seeding mechanism should theoretically work—both servers write to the same directory, and when the file appears there, the GET request on port 9000 should find it. But something's still not clicking with why the test is failing. Oh right, the CORS issue! Port 9000 is sending `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`, so that should be fine.\n\nLet me trace through what actually happened in the test: the seed endpoint returned success at 16:33:51 with a 15-second timeout, then the wait started polling GET on port 9000. By 16:34:06 (15 seconds later), the condition still wasn't met and the wait timed out. The backend's natural file creation wouldn't happen for another 45 seconds, so the file genuinely wasn't there when we checked.\n\nThis tells me the seed mechanism isn't working as expected—either the file isn't being written to the right location, or there's a timing issue with how the file becomes available after the seed call returns.\n\nThe most straightforward fix is to either extend the test timeout to 65 seconds to let the backend's natural 60-second delay handle it, or create a dedicated seed endpoint on port 9000 that the frontend can poll directly. I'll go with the first approach since it's simpler, but I should also verify that the seed endpoint is actually creating the file synchronously before returning.\n\nLooking at the seed handler, it does write the file synchronously before sending the response, so the file should definitely exist by the time the test starts polling. The issue might be something else entirely—let me reconsider what's actually happening here.\n\nOh wait, I think I see it now. Both the mock server on port 9000 and the extra server on port 9001 are writing to the same filesystem path, but they're separate HTTP servers. When the extra server handles the seed request and writes to `/tmp/code-scanning-mock/UUID`, the mock server on port 9000 should be able to read that same file immediately since they're accessing the same location on disk.\n\nThe real problem might be something more subtle. Let me reconsider what the test is actually doing and whether the file operations are really happening the way I think they are. The issue is that both servers write to the same DATA_DIR, so the file should be accessible from port 9000's GET endpoint. I'm wondering if there's a filesystem sync delay or perhaps the request is being cached somehow. Rather than continue debugging this, the simplest fix is to make the backend's setTimeout much shorter for testing—around 5 seconds instead of 60—or add a test mode flag that controls this delay.\n\nActually, the better approach is to add a dedicated seed endpoint directly to the main server on port 9000, so the test can reliably trigger file creation without relying on the extra server's path.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"seed 端在 9001，轮询在 9000——虽然写同一目录但为可靠测试，加一个 9000 上的 seed 接口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y9oehyik7dga_1","name":"read","arguments":{"filePath":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/server/mockMinio.ts","limit":20,"offset":96}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":344,"output":806,"cacheRead":85563,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86713,"cost"