{"type":"message","id":"cbdba55f","parentId":"305d0257","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:50:16.647Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file is at `/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts`. But the workspace context is `/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace`. So the workspace-relative path is `projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts`. Let me add a console.log to debug.\n\nActually, the issue might be that the Playwright test is running in the browser context. The browser makes requests to `localhost:9000` but the CORS headers on 404 responses might be causing the browser to reject the response.\n\nLet me add `console.log` to the frontend's `fileExists` function and see what it logs.\n\n\nNow I need to check what CORS configuration the mockMinio server is applying to those 404 responses.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vfq8ves8rg1b_1","name":"read","arguments":{"filePath":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanning-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts","limit":10,"offset":100}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":148,"output":230,"cacheRead":107963,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108341,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775811009420,"responseId":"chatcmpl-22f36f3f-5ea7-4322-9a16-f646ee854ad7"}}
