{"type":"message","id":"3a499a45","parentId":"5609dbaf","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:56:36.468Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still the same failures. The console.log from waitForResult isn't showing up in the test output because the test captures console output only from the Node.js process, not from the browser. Let me add a different approach - intercept the browser console in the Playwright test.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Instead of debugging the waitForResult from the test, let me use Playwright to directly navigate to the page, use the browser console to:\n1. Submit a task\n2. Seed the file\n3. Wait for the result\n\nThis way I can capture browser console logs in the Playwright test itself.\n\nActually, I just realized something crucial. Looking at the debug script output again:\n\n\nThe test submits a UUID and then checks for the result, but the polling logic is checking for a `.result` class that might not be appearing on the `.step-card` element. I'm wondering if the issue is that `step.value = 4` is being set in Vue but the DOM isn't updating properly, or if the polling is actually succeeding and the result is being set, but something else is preventing the test from detecting it.\n\nActually, I think I've found it - the `submitScan` function is async, and when Playwright clicks the submit button, it waits for the async operation to complete. But inside `submitScan`, after calling `submitScanTask` and `waitForResult`, the `step.value = 4` might be getting set, but then the error handler in the catch block is also executing, which could be overwriting the result or causing a race condition.\n\nWait, but `return` in the try block should prevent the catch from running. Let me reconsider - maybe the issue is that `waitForResult` is returning before the file actually exists, or the file content is empty and `marked()` is failing silently.\n\nActually, I think the real problem is that `submitScan` isn't actually completing. Playwright's click resolves once the button's click handler starts executing, but since it's an async function, the promise might not have settled yet when Playwright moves on to the next assertion. That would explain why the step value isn't changing as expected.\n\nBut wait, the test shows `testSubmitScan` passes in 1 second, which suggests the button click did complete. So something else is happening. Let me trace through the actual flow: after the file is seeded, `waitForResult` should detect it and set `step.value = 4`. The test waits 20 seconds for `.step-card.result` to appear, but it never does. So either the file isn't being found, or there's an error happening that I'm not seeing. Let me check if there's an error being thrown in the console.\n\nActually, I should just add some logging to see what's really happening with the UUID and file existence checks.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xdxpk5lbsjsr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /tmp/pw-log-debug.mjs << 'EOTEST'\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright'\n\nconst browser = await chromium.launch({\n  headless: true,\n  executablePath: '/usr/bin/chromium-browser',\n})\nconst context = await browser.newContext()\nconst page = await context.newPage()\n\npage.on('console', msg => {\n  const text = msg.text()\n  if (text.includes('waitForResult') || text.includes('fileExists') || text.includes('poll')) {\n    console.log(`[BROWSER] ${text}`)\n  }\n})\npage.on('pageerror', err => console.log(`[PAGE ERROR] ${err.message}`))\n\n// 监听 fetch 请求\npage.on('response', async resp => {\n  const url = resp.url()\n  if (url.includes(':9000')) {\n    const status = resp.status()\n    const method = resp.request().method()\n    console.log(`[FETCH ${method} ${status}] ${url}`)\n  }\n})\n\nawait page.goto('http://localhost:5174', { waitUntil: 'networkidle' })\n\n// 上传文件、填提示词\nconst testFile = '/tmp/test-code.zip'\nawait page.locator('#file-input').setInputFiles(testFile)\nawait page.locator('.btn-primary', { hasText: '下一步' }).click()\nawait page.waitForSelector('.prompt-input', { timeout: 3000 })\nawait page.locator('.prompt-input').fill('安全扫描测试')\nawait page.locator('.btn-primary', { hasText: '提交扫描' }).click()\nawait page.waitForSelector('.step-card.waiting', { timeout: 5000 })\n\nconst uuid = (await page.locator('.status-value.uuid').textContent()).trim()\nconsole.log(`[UUID] ${uuid}`)\n\n// seed\nawait fetch(`http://localhost:9000/seed?uuid=${encodeURIComponent(uuid)}`)\nconsole.log(`[SEED] Done`)\n\n// 等待 Step 4\ntry {\n  await page.waitForSelector('.step-card.result', { timeout: 20000 })\n  console.log('[SUCCESS] Step 4 appeared!')\n} catch(e) {\n  const elapsed = await page.locator('.elapsed-badge').textContent().catch(() => 'n/a')\n  console.log(`[FAIL] Step 4 did not appear. Elapsed: ${elapsed}`)\n  \n  // Check what's on the page\n  const stepCard = await page.locator('.step-card').first().getAttribute('class')\n  console.log(`[STATE] step-card class: ${stepCard}`)\n  \n  // Check poll count\n  const pollText = await page.locator('.status-value').nth(3).textContent().catch(() => 'n/a')\n  console.log(`[STATE] poll text: ${pollText}`)\n}\n\nawait browser.close()\nEOTEST\ncp /tmp/pw-log-debug.mjs /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/ && node /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/pw-log-debug.mjs 2>&1","timeout":40,"yieldMs":35000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":1058,"output":1270,"cacheRead":116923,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775811362482,"responseId":"chatcmpl-fdbd35fc-3a61-4f66-a4aa-4526f5b8bee0"}}
