{"type":"message","id":"f047b360","parentId":"65bba85f","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:57:52.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both `downloadTextFile` and `downloadBuffer` use `Buffer` which is not available in the browser. I need to:1. `downloadTextFile`: Replace `Buffer.from(ab).toString('utf-8')` with `new TextDecoder().decode(ab)`2. `downloadBuffer`: For browser, return `Uint8Array` instead of `Buffer`. Since the caller only uses `downloadTextFile`, I only need to fix that one.Actually, `downloadBuffer` is only used in `minio.ts` (the real MinIO client). In the mock mode, only `downloadTextFile` is used. Let me check what calls `downloadBuffer`...Actually, looking at the scanService.ts:```typescriptconst { fileExists, downloadTextFile } = await getMinioClient()\n\n\n```\n\nSo `downloadBuffer` is not used in the mock mode. But I should still fix it for consistency. For `downloadTextFile`, the fix is simple: `new TextDecoder().decode(ab)`. For `downloadBuffer`, in the browser context it returns `Uint8Array` instead of `Buffer`, but since it's not actually called in mock mode, it won't matter. Now I'll apply these fixes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8lcl2s1eorvt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -i \"s/return Buffer.from(ab).toString('utf-8')/return new TextDecoder().decode(ab)/\" \\\n  /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts\n# Also fix uploadBuffer which uses Buffer\nsed -i \"s/return Buffer.from(ab)/return new Uint8Array(ab)/\" \\\n  /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts\ngrep -n \"Buffer\\|TextDecoder\\|Uint8Array\" /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/mockMinioClient.ts","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":363,"output":425,"cacheRead"