{"type":"message","id":"31a7e609","parentId":"f047b360","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:57:52.850Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8lcl2s1eorvt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"40:  const ab = await res.arrayBuffer()\n41:  return new TextDecoder().decode(ab)\n44:/** 下载 Buffer */\n45:export async function downloadBuffer(objectName: string): Promise<Buffer> {\n48:  const ab = await res.arrayBuffer()\n49:  return new Uint8Array(ab)\n54:  const buffer = Buffer.from(content, 'utf-8')\n63:/** 上传 Buffer */\n64:export async function uploadBuffer(\n66:  buffer: Buffer,\n72:    body: new Uint8Array(buffer),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":26,"aggregated":"40:  const ab = await res.arrayBuffer()\n41:  return new TextDecoder().decode(ab)\n44:/** 下载 Buffer */\n45:export async function downloadBuffer(objectName: string): Promise<Buffer> {\n48:  const ab = await res.arrayBuffer()\n49:  return new Uint8Array(ab)\n54:  const buffer = Buffer.from(content, 'utf-8')\n63:/** 上传 Buffer */\n64:export async function uploadBuffer(\n66:  buffer: Buffer,\n72:    body: new Uint8Array(buffer),","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775811472844}}
{"type":"message","id":"86074d2b","parentId":"31a7e609","timestamp":"2026-04-10T08:58:11.876Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are still `Buffer` usages in `uploadTextFile` and `uploadBuffer`. Let me fix them too:\n\nLine 54: `const buffer = Buffer.from(content, 'utf-8')` - used in `uploadTextFile`\nLine 72: `body: new Uint8Array(buffer)` - this is already using `Uint8Array` but `buffer` is `Buffer` from the caller\n\nFor the upload, I should use:- `uploadTextFile`: `new TextEncoder().encode(content)` instead of `Buffer.from(content, 'utf-8')`\n- `uploadBuffer`: `new Uint8Array(buffer)` is fine if buffer is a Buffer/Uint8Array, but the `Buffer` type annotation might cause issues\n\n\nActually, `uploadTextFile` doesn't even use the buffer variable - it just passes `buffer` directly to the fetch body, which accepts ArrayBufferView. So I could use `new TextEncoder().encode(content)` directly instead of creating the intermediate buffer variable. Wait, `new TextEncoder().encode(content)` returns `Uint8Array` and `buffer` in the original code is also used in `uploadBuffer`. Let me check: `uploadBuffer` has parameter `buffer: Buffer` and uses it as `new Uint8Array(buffer)`.\n\nSo `uploadBuffer` receives a `Buffer` and converts it to `Uint8Array`, which should work fine since both are ArrayBufferViews. For `uploadTextFile`, the simplest approach is using `new TextEncoder().encode(content)` to get a `Uint8Array` directly. The issue is that the test runs in a browser where `Buffer` isn't available, so I need to replace all instances with `Uint8Array` and `TextEncoder`/`TextDecoder`. I'm checking whether `new Uint8Array(buffer)` actually works when `buffer` is a Node.js Buffer—the Buffer class inherits from Uint8Array, so converting it should be safe and produce a plain Uint8Array without the Buffer-specific methods.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2jj4mhn