\"@types/node\": \"^22.13.9\",\n    \"@types/uuid\": \"^10.0.0\",\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"playwright\": \"^1.59.1\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.19.3\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.8.2\",\n    \"vite\": \"^6.2.1\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.13\",\n    \"vue-tsc\": \"^2.2.8\"\n  }\n}","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775813312992}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d092e81","parentId":"16e46e97","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:28:41.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to clean up package.json:- Remove `mock-server` and `mock-minio` scripts\n- Remove `cors`, `express`, `multer`, `uuid` from dependencies\n- Remove `@types/cors`, `@types/express`, `@types/multer`, `@types/uuid`, `tsx` from devDependencies- Keep `axios`, `marked`, `uuid` (for generateUUID)- Keep `@types/node`, `@vitejs/plugin-vue`, `playwright`, `typescript`, `vite`, `vue`, `vue-tsc`\n\nWait, the scanService.ts uses `uuid` from `uuid` package. But in the simulator, I'm not using uuid. \n\nI should double-check if CodeScanner.vue actually imports uuid directly. Looking at what scanService.ts exports, `generateUUID` comes from the uuid package, but the simulator has its own implementation, so I might be able to remove the dependency if uuid isn't used elsewhere.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8i1bhpvj4159_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"uuid\\|UUID\\|generateUUID\" /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/src/CodeScanner.vue","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":643,"output":262,"cacheRead":121851,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122756,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775813313009,"responseId":"chatcmpl-08bf4161-81bd-4e50-a940-8726ff3c092f"}}
