{"type":"message","id":"49675967","parentId":"65676da6","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:28:52.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`CodeScanner.vue` imports `uuid` directly. I need to either keep `uuid` in dependencies or replace with a self-contained UUID generator. Let me add a simple UUID v4 implementation in a utils file and use that.\n\nActually, the simplest approach: keep `uuid` in dependencies since it's just for generating UUIDs client-side and doesn't add much weight. But since we're removing server deps, I should keep it.\n\nLet me just remove the server-related dependencies (cors, express, multer, @types/cors, @types/express, @types/multer, tsx) and keep uuid, axios, marked.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h42mxehfql7w_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"{\n  \"name\": \"code-scanner-plugin\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"前端代码扫描插件 - Vue3 + MinIO 异步处理\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"axios\": \"^1.7.9\",\n    \"marked\": \"^18.0.0\",\n    \"uuid\": \"^11.1.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.13.9\",\n    \"@types/uuid\": \"^10.0.0\",\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"playwright\": \"^1.59.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.8.2\",\n    \"vite\": \"^6.2.1\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.13\",\n    \"vue-tsc\": \"^2.2.8\"\n  }\n}\n","path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin/package.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":601,"output":405,"cacheRead":122299,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775813322040,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a4f451a7-cc63-4605-ac3d-a9f7ed3e0d