{"type":"message","id":"87fdebbf","parentId":"5caad493","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:50:34.397Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update scanService.ts to import from simulator properly. Let me also check that there are no issues with the scanService.ts import.\n\nAlso, I need to update the E2E test to:\n1. After page loads, call `window.__simulatorSeed(uuid, items)` to pre-seed the fileStore\n2. Then the 5~8 second delay will be bypassed because the data is already in the store\n\nWait - actually there's still a problem. The `submitScanTask` function will still wait 5~8 seconds before setting the fileStore. If we pre-seed with the same UUID before submitting, the `submitScanTask` will overwrite it after 5~8 seconds. But since we want to test immediately, we can just:\n\n\n1. Call `submitScanTask` which starts the timer\n2. Immediately seed the fileStore with `window.__simulatorSeed` with the same UUID\n3. The polling will find the data immediately and return\n\nSo the E2E test just needs to call `window.__simulatorSeed(uuid, items)` after `submitScanTask` starts the timer, and the data will be ready before the polling loop even checks. Let me compile and test this out.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i1x30p59pdu2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/projects/code-scanner-plugin && npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"miaoda","model":"miaoda-model-auto","usage":{"input":68,"output":307,"cacheRead":103931,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104306,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775814625512,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e311d0e3-4aa3-414c-9e5c-d9d76b55dcca"}}
